volumes.title: Blues Vol 2
volumes.desc: A wide range of blues styles from from rock and jazz to southern slide and Texas Blues.

volumes.title: James Wilson Vol 1
volumes.desc: A diverse palate of music ranging from orchesrtal tracks with choir voices to upbeat electronica and blues.

volumes.title: Hip Pop Vol 1
volumes.desc: A smooth mixtutre of Hip-Hop, Pop, and modern R&B.;

volumes.title: Pop Vol 3
volumes.desc: Pop styles ranging from 50's sock hop to latin and jazz influences.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 3
volumes.desc: New hip hop stlyes ranging from agressive upbeat to slow and slinky.

volumes.title: Jams & Bands Vol 1
volumes.desc: A collection of modern rock bands, electronica, and a touch of hip-hop.

volumes.title: Jams & Bands Vol 2
volumes.desc: From funky soul rock to electronic dub this new collection of Jams & Band rocks!

volumes.title: Moods & Grooves Vol 1
volumes.desc: Some cool jazz, some upbeat grooves, some moody tracks and a few  eclectic ethnic rythms round out this new collection.

volumes.title: Rockin Hop Vol 1
volumes.desc: From agressive hip-hop to feel-good rock, Rockin hop has a track for every mood!

volumes.title: Moods & Grooves Vol 2
volumes.desc: Moods and Grooves Vol 2 features vocalists singing in the styles of modern R&B;, swing, lounge, plus a beautiful ballad. Also includes instrumental music in the styles of agressive techno and world music.

volumes.title: Mark Cally Vol 1
volumes.desc: Beautifully composed classical pieces, groovy rock and roll, and many other styles are featured on this well-rounded collection. Plus, some added salsa and a great sax driven r&b; track add up to a great selection of tunes!

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 2
volumes.desc: From heraldic horns to sweet strings, with suspenseful builds and a little persian flavor, this new selection from Freeplaymusic brings you modern orchestral sounds from the cutting edege!

volumes.title: Ethereal Movements
volumes.desc: This new collection of atmospheric tracks fuses a wide range of styles and sounds. Ambient, world, rock and orchestral all come together beautifully in this ethereal selection of tunes.

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Heavy techno, driving rock and even some surf are featured on this new volume. This new collection, put together from a fresh pallet of sounds, has a wide variety of textures and dynamics.
Another heavy-hitter from Freeplaymusic.

volumes.title: Tropical Vibes Vol 1
volumes.desc: Tropical Vibes is a brand new collection featuring upbeat island melodys. From sunshiny Reggae to sultry Bossa Nova to Latin tinged rock this is a lush set of tracks straight from the beach.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 1
volumes.desc: This new volume, Dark Dimensions, brings you tracks from the darkside. Brooding dirges, thunderous marches and forboding cinematic atmospheres are featured, plus an amazing psychedellic jam.

volumes.title: Dance & Pop Vol 4
volumes.desc: Freeplaymusic is proud to bring you another installment in our dance & pop catalogue. Dance & Hop Vol 4 Offers 12 fresh new tracks, from dance r&b; to dance pop. These tracks are modern, uplifting, and motivating.

volumes.title: Dance and Pop Vol. 5
volumes.desc: Upbeat  R&B; tracks are featured on the latest installment of Dance & Pop Vol. 5. Modern urban sounds and styles plus a great slow jam.

volumes.title: Hip Pop Vol. 2
volumes.desc: Fresh new beats, a little r&b;, & a little reggae are features of Hip Pop Vol 2. Smooth and savy rhythms are accented by fresh melodies and new sounds.

volumes.title: Gary Philips Vol. 2
volumes.desc: Gary Philips Vol 2 brings some great new rock tracks to the freeplay library. From southern fried rock to brushed drums and lovely acoustic guitar. A wide range of feelings and a wide range of styles.

volumes.title: Deluxe Rhythm & Blues Vol. 1
volumes.desc: From silky to strutting,   Deluxe Rhythm & Blues Vol. 1 is a great new collection of tracks. A bit of reggae, a a touch of street, a little dance and a lotta' soul combine in this fresh new volume of urban sounds.

volumes.title: Trance-Floor Vol. 1
volumes.desc: Trance-Floor Vol. 1 is a hot new set of modern electronic music. From trance to IDM (intellegent dance music) to ambient, this new volume is chock-full of hip sounds, avant beats and killer breaks.

volumes.title: Drama Vol. 2
volumes.desc: Drama Vol. 2 is a dynamic new set of tracks. From melancholy to uplifting, this volume is full of beautiful melodies and excelent instrumentation. Great guitar playing and fabulous string arrangements are key features in this new collection.

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol. 3
volumes.desc: The third collection of Electro-Rock tracks runs the gammut- from hip hoppy beats with blusey guitar licks to some retro 80's fun. Great musicianship and fresh sounds keep this collection vital.

volumes.title: Dance & Pop Vol. 6
volumes.desc: The newest update in our Dance & Pop series, volume 6, brings you more hip shaking beats. With an international flair and some lovely upbeat melodies, this new set of tracks will get you grooving!

volumes.title: Sunny Summer Rock Vol. 1
volumes.desc: Warm and breezy summertime tracks shine on this new collection. Heartfelt melodys and happy bouncy beats are featured on Sunny Summer Rock Vol. 1. With groovy guitar strumming and charming piano leads, this new volume brings you some sweet happy tunes!

volumes.title: Breeding & Peterson Vol. 1
volumes.desc: Composers Breeding and Peterson bring a great variety of styles to this new volume, from orchestral and solo piano pieces to smokey blues and grooving rockabilly. This collection touches many genres with style and grace.

volumes.title: Todd Haberman Vol. 3
volumes.desc: Great modern rock is featured on Todd Haberman Vol. 3, but, there are also some neat orchestral pieces and interludes. From punky to grunge to flat-out thrashing there's alot of rock, and some world and orchestral pop included just for fun.

volumes.title: Piano Solos Vol. 2
volumes.desc: Piano Solos Vol. 2 is a rich new volume of solo tracks.These wonderfully melodic arrangements both complex and engaging or simple and sublime can enhance any atmosphere. A charmingly quiet and sophisticated set of tracks.

volumes.title: World Chill Vol. 1
volumes.desc: World Chill Vol. 1 is a dynamic new volume that garners influences from many places, instruments and feelings. Soulful and sexy vocals harmonize over amazing backing tracks with modern and authentic sounds, giving an intriguing new shine to the term world music. With Latin and Mediterranean flair and lovely arrangements, World Chill Vol. is a diverse and fascinating set of tracks.

volumes.title: Bangin Beats Vol 1
volumes.desc: Banging Beats Vol 1 is our first collection from Ysoul, 10 tracks of killer hip-hop beats with fresh sounds, smart production and an ear for the sound of the streets. Not only great beats, there is alot of imaginitive synth play and hip new sounds in this collection. From west coast hype to lo key thumps, this is a speaker slammin volume.

volumes.title: Oriental Grooves Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Oriental Grooves Vol 1 is a 
new collection of fusion tracks. Modern rhythms topped with lovely Oriental instruments, from micro-beat to trip-hop breaks this volume grooves but the interesting instrumentation, shamsen and koto, takes it to another singluar and expressive level.

volumes.title: Oriental Stings Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Oriental Stings Vol 1 is a 
collection of 4 second 'stings' culled from the tracks on Oriental Grooves Vol 1.
Great for Buttons or Powerpoint screen segues.

volumes.title: Bangin Beats Vol 2
volumes.desc: Bangin Beats Vol 2 is our second collection of slammin hip hop beats. Put together by a major level producer this set of tracks has street cred. Heavy beats accented by melodic nuances and subtle touches, with some classic 80's synth sounds and some imaginitive samples, this volume is sure to get your head nodding.

volumes.title: Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Steve Glotzer's excellent guitar playing is showcased on Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 1 . From samba to solo to swing the melodies and musicianship on this collection shine.
Lovely vibes, keys, and percussion add texture and depth to this great collection of contemporary jazz tracks.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 2
volumes.desc: Paul Andrews' uncanny musical vision is the key feature of Dark Dimensions Vol 2, mixing ambient, tribal, electronic and orchestral instrumentation in deft touches he builds amazing soundscapes that feel dimensional and otherworldly yet still organic. From chaotic tribal rhythms to metronomic industrial breakbeats to spacious ambient atmospheres, Dark Dimensions Vol 2 provides cinematic pieces rich in spirit and feeling with intensity and vision.

volumes.title: Kids Songs Vol 1
volumes.desc: Kids Songs Vol 1 is a delightful selection of fun tunes- some classic, and some you may have never heard. From circus music, to silly jazz, to a vocal round are a few of the styles you will find on this amusing volume.

volumes.title: Pop Vol 4
volumes.desc: Sweet guitar playing is featured on our newest addition to the pop catalogue, Pop Vol 5, with warm melodies and a full, well-rounded sound, this new collection gives you many styles - from an anthemic ballad, to a sexy sax theme to a swelling flaminco and strings piece. This new volume has lush production and lovely melodies that will warm and comfort you.

volumes.title: Techstep Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Brooklyn based collective 12Tone
Studios produced this excellent set of tracks for Techstep Vol 1. Electronic drum and bass with an intelligent bent. Great grooves built with innovative sounds and techniques. From funk and reggae flavored drum and bass, microhouse, dance techno, and neurofunk many facets of electronic music are explored. There is also an intense dramatic violin piece rounding off Techstep Vol 1, a collection of electronic music at its' freshest, innovative best.

volumes.title: Dance & Pop Vol 7
volumes.desc: From hip-hop to house to electronic, Dance & Pop Vol 7 brings in the modern beats, flavored by many different vibes- "Missed Out" has a ballywood feeling, "Chinese Flute" has a world-tribal edge, "So Cold"  is a smooth R&B; glide. Dance & Pop Vol 7 fuses all these styles with tight beats and fresh sounds.

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 2
volumes.desc: Looking for something a little different?  If you are then look no further!  World Chill Vol 2 is a percussion-heavy volume of international folk music styles, with an emphasis on West African rhythmic figures.  Drums and marimbas lock horns throughout, creating striking tension and excellent rhythmic interplay.  If you want to broaden your musical horizons, then be sure to check out World Chill Vol 2.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 4
volumes.desc: More Fat Thumpin' Beats are to be found on Hip Hop Vol 4. Nuanced by understated, sonically exciting samplers and synths that create tension and dynamics, these tracks have alot of flair. The tuff and gritty rhythms on Hip Hop Vol 4 rounded out by deep 808 bass. Check out the cool use of needle drops on 'Big Poppa'  and the finger poppin funk of 'Let Me In'.

volumes.title: American Standards Vol 1
volumes.desc:
From the composer who put together Sunny Summer Rock Vol 1 comes: American Standards Vol 1. This 
is a collection of real American Rock & Roll, with smart production, smart arrangements, and excelent musicianship. I love his guitar playing, it's understated but imaginitive and progressive. The bass and drums are solid and share the stage well with the broadminded guitaring. Track by track, with shades of country, alternative, and just solid rock and roll, American Standards Vol 1 serves up some great tracks.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 1
volumes.desc: Evocative sound-scapes are featured on Ambient Figures Vol 1. Not just synth-pad based drones, there are some completely alien sounds and amazing use of deep sub-bass on these tracks and, underlying it all you will find a bit of melody or a passing pulse of rhythm. Sublime and cinematic, Ambient Figures Vol 1 provides deep atmospheric touches and intense sonic backgrounds.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 2
volumes.desc:
More great industrial soundscapes are featured on Ambient Figures Vol 2. Unreal, yet organic sounds 
create tension in these simmering atmospheric tracks. Odd rhythmic figures build and dissolve in a warm wash of noise, deep bass tones ebb under a frost of distortion while metal shards clank in a sonic wind. Perhaps not as stark as Ambient Figures Vol 1, Vol 2 is as cinematic and adds some more delecate melodic  nuances to the mix.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 1
volumes.desc: Australian DJ duo Mar N' Dean produced this shimmering, dancefloor rocking techno collection, Electrofied Vol 1. Seriously slammin kicks are the pulse, thick ropey basslines are the sinew and layers of intense synths weave complex paths through the stereo field. No samples here, heavy tape-generated beats and inspired synthplay give Electofied Vol 1 heft, sparkle and booty-shaking bottom.

volumes.title: Moods & Grooves Vol 3
volumes.desc: Steven Becket's guitaring and sense of rhythmic play are key to Moods & Grooves Vol 3, the off-kilter intro to "Tino" leeds into a smooth salsa and the dirgy strings of "Sunny & Overcast" are warmed by rays of piano melody. Moody and smooth is the nature of the beats here and some understated use of string and horn samples in all the right places keeps Moods & Grooves Vol 3 a vital collection of tracks.

volumes.title: Promos Vol 3
volumes.desc: Simon Brewer writes from a broad palate of styles with an upbeat and and progressive ear, Promos Vol 3 is awash in subtle yet solid tunes. The propulsive rhythms on "M Spices" motivate, the smooth drums and piano of "Accenture" lend a thoughtful air, and the warming vibe of "Into The Light" gives a reassuring and graceful pulse to Promos Vol 3. Also included on this volume are underscore tracks that focus on different elements of the pieces, bringing another level of creativity to Promos Vol 3 .

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Picturesque melodies are key on Brian Casels new collection; Music For Pictures Vol 1. Spacious and sublime instrumentation to frame any scene. These 10 melodic rock tracks have a joyous, 
unpretentious feel, plenty of warmth and a little humor as well. Check 'Kalimba' for a happy rolling tune or 'Grand Strings' for a joyful sweeping melody. Music For Pictures Vol 1 is full of lovely, understated melodies and will provide delightful background for situations of all kinds.

volumes.title: Techstep Vol 2
volumes.desc: -The folks at 12tone bring another great set of tracks for Techstep Vol 2. Mainly comprised of intense glitch techno with wild breaks and out of this world synths, there are other flavors here too: from the dramatic violin piece 'Between The Bookshelves' to the cool reggae step of 'Shadow Dub' and the soulful jam of 'Positively 4th And Prospect', this volume has depth. The intense headphone nodders, 'Clubthumper' and 'Stoneknuckle', will get the floor rocking...Techstep Vol 2 has a lot to offer any mood.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 2
volumes.desc: More vibrant cinematic tracks from the Music For Pictures series. Volume 2 brings you more lush melodies and excellent production from Brian Casel. His understated use of keys and synth on the rock oriented tracks adds depth and flavor- check 'Stomp' for a heavy wah-wah ride and 'Bangin Horns' for an inspired techno influenced rock track. For a bit of atmospheric drama be sure to check 'Piano Stripped' and for a groovy laid back reggae feel look to 'Fallback'. Music For Pictures brings solid workmanship and inspired production to the plate along with a healthy imagination.

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 4
volumes.desc: Ben Kopec, leader of Intricate Unit, has put together some heavy industrial tracks for Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 4. Rocking, dramatic riffs and intense drum work are key to the "heavyosity" of this new collection. Using dynamics and the stereo field to its fullest, he gives these tracks breath and intense atmosphere. Wonderfully taut and aggressive synths top it off with a sheen that is expressive and creative.

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Vol 1
volumes.desc: Brooklyn DJ Casual T brings some kickin' world influenced tracks that are off the record. With imaginitive use of melody and rhythm, these selections are full of sonic surprises. Check "Isotope Scope" for a smoking dub, find the funk with "Flash Pipe" and dig the funky spy hits of "Yo My Foes". Casual T drops crazy phat breaks and lays a mean groove, dancy and upbeat. Eclectic Beats Vol 1 has a lot of vibe and groove to liven any event.

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 1
volumes.desc:
From Marco 
Mastrocola, who brought us Oriental Grooves Vol 1 & Oriental Stings Vol 1, brings another set of volumes featuring regular length tracks plus a second volume of 4 second stings. Showcasing his versitility and considerable song writing skills these melodic rock tracks really shine. Lovely guitars, excellent drums and killer bass, this is the work of a real honest rock & roll band. Check "New Day" for a driving upbeat track, or the sparkling, sunny feel of "Here With You" and the warm, emotive charm of "Hear Me Calling. Rock Grooves Vol 1 is full of spacious, gently rocking songs, brimming with emotion and warmth.

volumes.title: Rock Stings Vol 1
volumes.desc: Featuring 4 second "stings" of the excellent tracks on Rock Grooves Vol 1.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 2
volumes.desc: Another great set of tracks from Aussie DJ's Mar & Dean. Heavy drum & bass tracks with flair and abandon, intense and hypnotic dance tracks with style and groove- Electrofied Volume 2 is an amazing collection! Check out the disco flavors of 'Up' and feel the groove, for some mind-bending electonic styles.  See 'Re-creation' & 'Plutonic Dance' for straight up dancefloor blasts see 'Destination' & 'NRG'. Electrofied Vol 2 brings mad crazy hip shaking grooves that will blow the floor up!

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 3
volumes.desc:
An excellent touch of feeling and light is a key element in Vincent Varco's compositions for Orchestral Vol 3. Some lovely, rich modern pieces with anthemic touches and cinematic flourishes, plus a bunch of neat retro-cartoonish pieces that are allot of fun. Selections from Orchestral Vol 3 include: "American Militare" where a somber marching rhythm is swept through with waltzing strings, on "Meadow Dreams" over a lush bed of plucked strings and bells, flutes flutter like birds, and harmonic glasses make a magical melody come alive in the imagination. On a lighter note, the classic feel and humorus touches on tracks like "Tippy Toes" and "Ducky" make for a fun time.
Included are 5 second stings of the cartoon tracks which could be used in some interesting situations, all in all, Orchestral Vol 3 has allot of dynamics to choose from and an enchanting feel throughout.

volumes.title: Cosmic Tronic Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Cozmic Rocker Stewart B.'s excellent upbeat, grooving tracks comprise Cosmic Tronic Volume 1. These jammin tracks, while modern and current have an amazing 80's dance music feel- the rhythms are somehow classic but the instrumentation is updated. The great production features clean bright mixes and fun, expressive stereo-field play. Cosmic? indeed, lots of futuristic synth sounds that touch on many genres, but still hold a great dance groove. Key tracks include; "Electro Step" with it's brazen disco stomp and "The Future Is Now" with it's warm straight to the heart of the dancefloor rush. Killer breaks and stop/start hooks give dynamics and tension,
lending to the groovyness of Cosmic Tronic Vol 1.- an excellent source of dance groove fun!

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 3
volumes.desc:
Freeplays newest volume "World Chill Vol 3" is another great set of tracks from Vincent Varco (see Orchestra Vol 3). 
This diverse set showcases his range as a composer.  Included styles are; Ska, Caribbean, Tribal, and Latin- all touched with his style of happiness and light. Check the smooth simmer of "Wicked Ways" or the lovley latin tango of "Latina Spirit". These upbeat and well produced tracks on World Chill Vol 3 add an elegant, smooth touch to any situation and the diverse styles will keep you surprised.

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Vol 1
volumes.desc: Tech Grooves Vol 1 brings creative synth work to it's peak on this diverse bunch of tracks- From the smooth funk of "So Low" to the brooding electronica groove of "Cool Martian" to the intense stuttered beats of the glitchy "Zoom" the amazing synth sounds keep this volume fresh.Tech Grooves Vol 1 brings allot of creative sounds to the plate and mixes them up for a fresh new feel.

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Vol 2
volumes.desc: Eclectic Beats Vol 2 is another styling collection of tracks from Casual T (see Eclectic Beats Vol 1). Featuring excellent synth work and rhymic feel, this new volume has grooves for any occasion.  Check the electronica charm of "Muse" and "Less Infants" or the smokey haunting vibe of "Mellow Souls". From electronica to dance to trip-hop there is a great variety of moods and feelings on Eclectic Beats Vol 2. s, composed by Jon Chilton delivers a diverse menu of feelings and textures. From enchanting to dramatic the imaginative melodies and excellent use of rhythm lend dramatic flair both light and dark. Check the lovelorn "Our Hope" for vibrant romance, "Storm Intro" has an eerie foreshadowing build with great Filmic potential, "Pursued" is a tense ride through a dark night. The compositions are dynamic and arrangements sweeping. These dramatic and cinematic qualities abound in Orchestral Vol 2 and are sure to set the scene in many applications.

volumes.title: Electronica Transmissions Vol 1
volumes.desc: From the same composer who brought us the Ambient Figures series comes something a little more beat oriented: Electronica Transmissions Vol 1, a sparse gentle touch with melody and a calm sense of space give these electronic tracks a zen feel. With lovely interplay, varied sampled instruments impart richness and depth of feeling on Electronica Transmissions Vol 1. Check "Tragic Door" for a charming melody, hit up "Homecoming" for its calm, reassured beats and smoky sax and dig the atmospheric "Farewell All" for an introspective dose of ambience. This spacious volume has subtle hooks and warm atmospheres to frame any situation.

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Vol 2
volumes.desc: Upbeat motivational dance grooves and sparkling synth work are key elements on Tech Grooves Vol 2. From the bright dancy sheen of "Fresh" to the bouncy melody of "Butterflys", the upbeat rhythms and and shiny synths are addictive and the dance grooves will get you moving, Tech Grooves Vol 2 will add an uptempo shine to any situation.

volumes.title: Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 1
volumes.desc: The composer who brought us "Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 1", Steve Glotzer, brings a new volume with a more pop oriented direction. Modern Pop & Lyric Vol 1 contains acoustic based tracks with catchy melodies sure to have you tapping your foot.  "We Will Be Together Soon" features a soulful female vocal over a funky rhythm section and bluesy electric guitar that you can't sit still to. Many of the tracks feature a sincere male vocal, but are also available without.  The tracks are often introspective and reflective, but are also driving and grooving.  Give Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 1 a listen you won't be disappointed!

volumes.title: Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 1
volumes.desc: The composer who brought us "Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 1", Steve Glotzer, brings a new volume with a more pop oriented direction. Modern Pop & Lyric Vol 1 contains acoustic based tracks with catchy melodies sure to have you tapping your foot.  "We Will Be Together Soon" features a soulfull female vocal over a funky rhythm section and bluesy electric guitar that you can't sit still to. Many of the tracks feature a sincere male vocal, but are also available without.  The tracks are often introspective and reflective, but are also driving and grooving.  Give Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 1 a listen, you won't be disappointed!

volumes.title: Moods And Grooves Vol 3
volumes.desc: Steven Becket's guitaring and sense of rhythmic play are key to Moods & Grooves Vol 3, the off-kilter intro to "Tino" leeds into a smooth salsa and the dirge like strings of "Sunny & Overcast" are warmed by rays of piano melody. Moody and smooth is the nature of the beats here and some understated use of string and horn samples in all the right places keeps Moods And Grooves Vol 3 a vital collection of tracks.

volumes.title: Classic Jazz Vol 1
volumes.desc: Jeff Curry brings excellent musicianship and lovely melodies to the spotlight on Classic Jazz Vol 1, with the style and grace of cool jazz from the 50's. Currys ear for arrangement and the smooth soft tones and rhythms of the players really makes this collection shine. Check the dulcet sax riffing on "Blue Seasons" or the elegant three piece in the reflective "Mallu" Classic Jazz Vol 1 is a wonderful set of tracks with magnificent musicians, astute arrangements and charming melodies that oozes with cool atmospheres.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 3
volumes.desc:
DJs Mar & Dean have put together another intense set of tracks for Electrofied Vol 3. The beats on this volume are a little more finessed so the amazing synth sounds and nuances really shine. There is a modern cinematic feel from the hypnotic synths noises and rhythms on tracks like "Realm Of Darkness (N.S. Mix)" and "Stratosphere"." Warped" has a playful rhythm and feel while underneath darkness lurks. Electrofied Vol 3 takes Drum &
Bass a little further, with subtle touches and hypotic soundscapes. You will find some intriguing atmospheres on this intense new volume.

volumes.title: Moods And Grooves Vol 4
volumes.desc: Another great set of tracks in many genres comprises Moods And Grooves Vol 4. From the heraldic horns of "Call To Arms" to the atmospheric "Dreaming" there is a wide range of styles and moods to choose from. Composer Mark Hewer's picturesque style shines on tracks like "Green Earth" with it's winsome guitars and on the organic cinematic pulse of "Film At Eleven". Moods And Grooves Vol 4 is a great bunch of atmospheric and creative tracks sure to accent any scene.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 4
volumes.desc: D.J. Mar and Dean keep the joint popping with their intense techo beats, but, these tracks are more like sonic playgrounds for the shifiting synth-scapes they weave. From the funky synth and guitar skronk of "New York Groove" to the intense shifting pulse of "Fused" the complex and mesmerizing sounds and patterns in these tracks give a propulsive cinematic and feeling throughout. Electrofied Vol 4 is a hot set of tracks with an upbeat happy feel and it's futuristic textures will enhance any scene.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 4
volumes.desc: Phillip Guyler put together a dramatic set of tracks featuring orchestral elements like strings and horns to build classic styled melodies underpinned by modern rock influenced rhythms- check the suave euro style feel of "Distant Spirit" or the lush, smooth pace of "Perpetual State". Music For Pictures Vol 4 brings rich atmospheric tracks together with dramatic flair and gentle intelligence to create a warm and thoughtful new volume.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 3
volumes.desc: Composer David Flavin brings a wide variety of styles and feelings on this new volume, from the dark cinematic pulse of "Tensor" to the rocking guitar jam of "Unhinged Flavor" there are many motivational tracks. Also find some fun 80s styles on tracks like "We Will Make It" and some world rock on "Jungle Book". Music For Pictures Vol 3 touches a wide range of styles with a motivational feel and excellent arrangements.

volumes.title: American Standards Vol 2
volumes.desc:
From Joi Veer, the composer who put together Sunny Summer Rock Vol 1 and American Standards Vol 1, comes another great set of excellent rock and roll tracks; American Standards Vol 2. This new collection showcases his upbeat rockin' attitude and lovely guitar melodies. With solid rhythms accented by just the right touches of synth and percussion his tracks have flair and style.
Dig the jamming "Purple Punch" for a spunky, punky feel, or the kooky whistled lead on "Summer Kisses" for a rockin' whirl.
The vocal boppin' on "Scoop De Doo" adds a fun hook to the bouncy track. American Standards Vol 2 is a diverse set of tracks with good old guitar, bass and drums as the centerpiece, adorned with thoughtful and spirited synth and percussion elements- all brimming with happy melodies and feelings.

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Joel Stein brings engaging melodies and a solid backing band to Rock Grooves Vol 2, the arrangements are innovative and sonically intriguing. The recording itself has a rich beautiful warmth and the instruments are played lovingly. Check the misty Americana of "Hideaway" for a poingant backdrop, or the hopeful flair and sunshiny groove of "Remember Me" , the solo piano piece "Ft Green" has a warm resolve in it's moody melody, or chill to the easy skank of "Happy Day". Rock Grooves Vol 2 is a great set of rock tracks with excellent production and great heartfelt melodies that really shine.

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 4
volumes.desc: This new volume of orchestral tracks, composed by Jon Chilton delivers a diverse menu of feelings and textures. From enchanting to dramatic the imaginative melodies and excellent use of rhythm lend dramatic flair both light and dark. Check the lovelorn "Our Hope" for vibrant romance, "Storm Intro" has an eerie foreshadowing build with great Filmic potential, "Pursued" is a tense ride through a dark night. The compositions are dynamic and arrangements sweeping. These dramatic and cinematic qualities abound in Orchestral Vol 2 and are sure to set the scene in many applications.

volumes.title: Tropical Vibes Vol 2
volumes.desc: Composer Pete Calandra brings some beach-y sunshine fun on this new collection- Tropical Vibes Vol 2, full of vacation vibes and sweet rhythms. Dig the sultry swoon of "Its A Samba Day", "Romance" has a sexy piano over a smoky jazz backdrop and check the spaced out, cinematic jams of "Thumb Piano Groove". Tropical Vibes Vol 2 delves into many genres and delivers fun in the sun and delightful melodies to enhance and motivate any situation.

volumes.title: Classic Jazz Vol 2
volumes.desc: This excellent collection of jazz tracks, composed by Pete Calandra, is built on his love of the genre and skills as a musician and writer. Lovely piano, subtle drumming, stylish horns, and great bass playing set the stage for a dynamic and emotionally rich set of of songs. Groove on the cool jazz tip of "Modal Mood", dig the metropolitan feel of "City Streets" with it's bouncy piano/xylophone dialogue, "Looking Out The Window" works at right angles and features a great juxtaposition between oboe and strings. The delightful moods and melodies explored on Classic Jazz Vol 2 provide delightful jazz atmospheres with sophisticated textures and excellent musicianship.

volumes.title: Blues Vol 3
volumes.desc:
Another great set of tracks from the multitalented Pete Calandra, this time in the gernre of blue: Blues Vol 3. Great guitar is key to the colorful, upbeat tunes found on this new collection; check the sparkling jump of "Down Home Again" or dig the motivational, cinematic air of "Brother Duane", the track "One For Willie" has a winsome feel and a southern country flavor.
Blues Vol 3 is a great collection of sincere tracks with a blusey R&B; feel that is sure to please.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 5
volumes.desc: DJ's Mar and Dean are back with another block rocking set of dance tracks for Electrofied Vol 5 this new bunch is mostly on the dance techno tip featuring their signature intensely layered synth lines that shift and shimmer through the stereo field, layered with dark insistent drum stomps. See "Get Down Yo" for a floor thumping beat, or check "Night Fire" for a suspenseful, cinematic build and dig the amazing vocal effects floating over "Shake (Mary Vox Mix)" for some tweeked aural textures. Electrofied Vol 5 is full of cinematic computerized soundscapes that will intrigue and make you shake your hips too.

volumes.title: Piano Solos Vol 3
volumes.desc: Pete Calandra excellent sense of melody and space are key to the beautiful piano playing on Piano Solos Vol 3. The  delightful melodies are rich and heartfelt with an earthy, intelligent air. Look to "Love Life" for warm heartache, check "Not This Time" for it's complex melancholy. Dramatic and cinematic touches abound on Piano Solos Vol 3, a great set of tracks which tug at heartstrings and warm the soul.

volumes.title: Moods And Grooves Vol 5
volumes.desc:
Pete Calandra's guitar is featured with a delightful backing band for Moods And Grooves Vol 5. Uptempo Americana jams with acoustic guitars and keys, a solo acoustic song along with some interesting funk and a little electronic music too.  Dig the jammin "Boulder Rock" for a countryfied rock tune,
check "Little Paws" for a rich uplifting Amaricana rock feel
the solo acoustic piece "My Mom Wore Pink" has a thoughtful tension that hides a warmth behind the shadowy melody. Moods And Grooves Vol 5 has great motivational rock jams, picturesque melodies and loads of style and spirit.

volumes.title: Moods And Grooves Vol 6
volumes.desc: Another strong, diverse set of tracks from composer David Flavin, Moods and Grooves Vol 6 brings punchy production, diverse instrumentation and varied styles to the plate. Check the rocking, heroic "Soldier" for a grand rock blast, The track "Flap Jack" is a country hoe-down with lovely accordion and slide guitar. "Autumn Leaves" is a melancholy picturesque dirge and "Tip Off" is a great spy-fueled action track- Great selection of genres and excellent instrumentation gives Moods and Grooves Vol 6 versatility and depth. A delightful set of tracks full of feeling and verve.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 5
volumes.desc: New writer Maxwell Walker brings an eclectic mindset and creative use of instrumentation to this new set of cinematic and emotive set of tracks. Check the campfire feeling of the acoustic guitar driven "Orange Moon" with it's charming ooh-aah harmonies, dig the intense synth skronk of the action-packed "Blow Up Buddhas". The dusty acoustics on "Tumbleweed" lend a desert feel to the sun burnt track. Musi arpeggio and synth hits give a "coming up next' flavor. Musicjag's excellent production and smart song writing are featured on Funk And Soul Vol 2- an easy, smooth set of soulful tracks that soothe and move the spirit.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 6
volumes.desc: Electrofied Vol 6 finds DJ's Mar And Dean reaching for more cinematic heights with their signature hypnotic electronic dance-scapes. More body-shock than body-rock these cerebral tracks ooze with intensity and heart racing suspense. Check out the cinematic pulse of "Darkness Awaits" for dark tones and dramatic push, The tweaked synths and edgy pound of "Night Runner" weaves eerie throbs and convulsing noises into a  thumping sonic headtrip. Electrofied Vol 6's aggressive and cinematic tracks give a propulsive, edgy, electronic feel to any situation.

volumes.title: Electronica Transmissions Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Electronica Transmissions Vol 2, a collection of tracks from new composer Benjamin Riordan, features charming, dramatic melodies enriched with an enigmatic, uplifting feel.
Dig the  positive, happy electro-groove of "Night Calling" with it's cool breaks and heartwarming piano line. On "Endless Gaze" it's winsome melody rides the percolating rhythm and sparkling synth effects with warm and motivational feel. Electronica Transmissions Vol 2 is a uplifting set of electronica tracks sure to motivate and illuminate any situation.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 1
volumes.desc: Composer Gary Phillips (see the excellent Gary Phillips Vols 1+2 in our library) brings the crunching guitars on this new volume- from grunge to southern stomp this is one blazing set. Check the cinematic rave-up "Spy Rite" for some action-adventure, the track "Up Side Down" has mindblowing stop-starts and intense knetics in its guitar riffing, "Craze" has a highway vibe in its driving pulse. Gary Phillips spot-on guitaring is intense but melodic, giving Rocked Up Vol 1 motivation, dynamics and full-on rocking attitude.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 7
volumes.desc: On Electrofied Vol 7 DJ's Mar & Dean Bring you the darker side of techno. With spooky atmospheres and eerie sound-scapes the Aussie duo makes dance music compelling and cinematic- check the "Temple Of Fear" for a mezmerizing head trip, "Sadness Within" has a simmering dark edge that has suspenseful cinematic touches, "Fear Within"'s claustrophobic beats and pulse really push the techno tag to the limit. Electrofied Vol 7 goes beyond the dance floor and explores some intense, inner worlds.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 1
volumes.desc: New composer Gregory Nicolett's dynamic orchestral compositions are highlighted on Orchestral Dimensions Vol 1-at times epic and ohers thoughtful his dynamic pieces utilize the orchestra to it's full extent- Check the simmering push of "Last Attack" for a highlight reel piece, "Icarus Cry" rides a dynamic melody with epic proportions, and the track "Into The Sun" adds electric guitar for a rocking, heroic track. Orchestral Dimensions Vol 1 takes the standard orchestral set to a whole new level.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Scott Jones Brings his heavy 80's tinged guitar to the fore for Rocked Up Vol 2- some great guitar soloing and harmonics add heft to the moody, slamming grooves. Dig the anthemic melody of "Iris" for an midtempo stadium rocker, "LD 50" has a psychedellic touch in it's gnarly guitars, "You, To Me" is a classic ballad with heavy guitars in all the right places. Rocked Up Vol 2 is a set of tracks that will make you get your lighter out and raise a fist for rock and roll.

volumes.title: Groove Masters Vol 1
volumes.desc: Neil Jason and John McCurry tag team the blues on Groove Masters Vol 1, dig the funky grind of "Funky Peppers" or the sweet roadhouse guitars on "Free As A Bird", "Electric Dreams" has a cool psychedellic swing to it's gritty groove. From clean and sweet to down and dirty Groove Masters Vol 1 brings you the no-messing-around BLUES.

volumes.title: Groove Masters Vol 2
volumes.desc: Neil Jason and John McCurry are back again for Groove Masters Vol 2- with a more modern take on the blues with this set, check out the rich, winsome Americana feel on "Park After Dark" bust your booty on the heavy groove of "Funk Mode" and dig the classic roadhouse blues of "Freewheelin", also find a techno suprise on the track "Rave On" just to mix it up a little.  From classic to modern there are plenty of well produced, smartly played tracks to be found on "Groove Masters Vol 2.- jump in and check it out.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 2
volumes.desc:
New composer Eric Roberts' lovely guitar playing is showcased on Acoustic Guitar Vol 2. His feel for the instrument shines in his gentle, graceful melodies.
In "Gently Falling Snow" two guitars weave an imaginative
melody and explore it with warm nimble soloing, "Rolling River" is a mystical journey with bass and percussion adding a charming texture, featuring a soulful violin solo. "Ebb And Flow" is a gently gliding tune with a tender touch. Acoustic Guitar Vol 2 has lovely lilting tunes with a mystic flair and graceful atmosohere.

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Vol 3
volumes.desc: New composer Paul Bickerdike brings pop sensibilities merged with modern, indy styles and fresh sounds to Tech Grooves Vol 3- Dig the fresh beats and snarky voice of "What Is Love" for a hip little piece, "Red Sunset" is a rolling number with a modern take on Americana with its acoustic guitar and catchy rhythms, "Return The Ace" has a great pop beat with shimmering synths and a great break with strings and piano giving a mellow vibe. The neat breaks and upbeat vibes on Tech Grooves Vol 3 provide modern takes on classic pop structures, with fun and wit. This new collection of tracks is sure to make you shake your hips and refresh your ears as well.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Pablo Schmitt brings world flavors to his grand and expansive orchestral compositions for Orchestral Dimensions Vol 2. Creative use of instruments and subtle touches and textures add depth to his creations- dig the grand, heroic "Storm Chaser" for an action/adventure track, "Angel's Descent" has dark percussion elements, choral voices and strident strings in its potent, cinematic melody. "On The Way To Ireland" has a celtic feel in it's romantic, majestic melody. Orchestral Dimensions Vol 2 brings exotic melodies and cinematic textures together with excellent orchestration and vivid soundscapes.

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Felix Miklik newest set, Tech Grooves Vol 4, features his dynamic rhythms, intellectual sonic atmospheres and great sense for the hook. Dig the hip tech beat and cool fuzz synth bass hook of "Break This", "Smoov"'s spacy textures and dubby feel is accented by trashy drums and squelched synths giving a great cinemtic feel. The intelligent writing and dynamic modern sounds give "Tech Grooves Vol 4" a hip sheen that will move you, and stick in your head.

volumes.title: Electronica Transmissions Vol 3
volumes.desc: New Composer Jorn Lavoll brings an exciting array of styles to Electronica Transmissions Vol 3- from space pop to ambient, with a cinematic touch and smart production, this new set will provide dynamic backdrops for many applications. Dig the ambient spaciousness of "Factory Void"- the echoing slide guitar provides an earthy counterpoint to the industrial noise behind, "Right Alone"'s dramatic emptiness is enhanced with a mournful kyoto and solemn drums. Electronica Transmissions Vol 3 is an enchanting set of electronic tracks sure add dynamics and texture to any scene.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 8
volumes.desc:
DJ Mar N' Dean continue to blow up the dance floor with this collection of techo-centric dance tracks. Electrofied Vol 8 hits you physically and motivates dynamically. Dig the dark pounding pulse of "Techno Fury" with it's triple fast kicks.
"High Fire" is a tummultious shuffle of patterns and speed shifts- a real head-trip. With Electrofied Vol 8 Mar and Dean have engineered another intense set of soundscapes with dynamic, motivational synths and heart pounding rhythms.

volumes.title: Electronica Transmissions Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Jorn Lavoll's second collection brings more of his quirky, poppy, hook laden tunes. His smart use of effects and rhythm is key to this volume, check out "Buzzbug" with its syncopated synth buzzes and wild filter effects, "Goldie Bar" is a wicked jumped-up beat and slamming snares, "Vindaloo's' wacky vocal samples and intense effects are riding a stick-in-your-head beat that is fun and motivational. Electronica Transmissions Vol 4 has well executed pop underpinnings topped off with fun, hip instrumentation- a delightful combination.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 3
volumes.desc: Composer Gregory Nicolett's dramatic soundscapes are key to this new volume, Orchestral Dimensions Vol. 3, from mysterious to uplifting many feelings are explored and enhanced by Gregory's fantastic instrumental arrangements.Check the innocent air of the uplifting "Joyous Homecoming", "Mysterious Voyage" has an tense feel hilighted by flute and harp, the feel good track "Pleasent Passings" features a jaunty acoustic guitar accented by woodwinds and horns adding a happy feel. Orchestral Dimensions Vol. 3 updates the classical with cinematic flavors and creative compositional skill.

volumes.title: Cinematic Electronic Vol 1
volumes.desc: Composer Dean Barrett, better known as DJ Mar+Dean of the Electrofied series steps out on this new volume, Cinematic Electronic, to deliver some excellent cinematic tracks with a diverse palate of textures and emotions. His great synth work and ear for stereo dimensions gives this collection the sheen and drive that we've come to expect but he proves he has more flavor than just techno- dig the laid back groove of "A Little Hip Hop" the track "Sunrise" starts from mangeled bird calls and dark textures and ends in a shiny warm wash of synth pads- really very sunrise-like! Cinematic Electronic Vol 1 Is a heady set of modern sounds and delightful textures sure to catch your ear!

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 6
volumes.desc:
Composer David Flavin's new collection, "Music For Pictures Vol 6" brings together diverse genres brushed with his
fluid sense of melody and fun with the hook. The pastoral "Hope Holds Hands" is an easy rock jam with ringing guitars and a positive, reassuring melody. Icy synths and tumbling effected drum machines fall into an upbeat melody when chiming guitars and bell synths join in on the electronica track "Hideyplace". On the jumped up "BC Boogie" souped up dragstrip sax and pounding honkeytonk piano bring down the house. Music For Pictures Vol 6 brings more filmic melodies and modern textures replete with smart hooks and great musicianship.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 5
volumes.desc: Fresh new beats with methodical production and sly, purposeful rhythms flavor the hot tracks on Hip Hop Vol 5, warm, fluid  synths add dynamic, syncopated melodies. Check out the exotic "Go Glow East"- Arabian flavors with a dark vibe groove hypnotically over driving beats and sparkling percussion effects. "Pop The Cork" has growling synth stabs and buzzing bass riding a dark, grimy rhythm and a dramatic feel. "Acoustic Beat" has an uptempo lo-fi beat with a rustic guitar line and subtle sway in the synth drums. The deft production and clean, bright synths on Hip Hop Vol 5 will bring a driving backbone to any scene.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 6
volumes.desc:
Composer Michael Genato (Techstep Vols 1 & 2) brings his tech savvy style to Hip Hop Vol 6, attacking the genre from a different angle with flashy, poppy results. "Chic Chick" is a syncopated, upbeat groove with style and cheek to spare, "Easy As That's" groovy beat will add an uptempo smile along with a dynamic push perfect for motion scenes. "Breadwinner" brings a funk feel
with it's dirty guitar sample and punchy congas. The dynamic tracks on Hip Hop Vol 6 will bring a streetwise, groovy and modern feel to your scenes or project,
please click the link above to check it out!

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 5
volumes.desc:
Composer Paul Andrews brings burly, grungy guitars to Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 5, along with a tight clockwork rhythm section, intense atmospheres and pounding, emotional dynamics. Check the wired beats and edgy syncopated guitars on "Hour Of Need" for a tense grinding groove, the track "Atomizer" has razor gleam melody underneath the grind-core guitars, "Shredder" is a punky rave-up with a winning melody.
The great production adds a nice bright, sheen to the beefy guitars and rhythm section and synths enhance the underlying melodies. Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 5 is a rich set of heavy jams full of dynamic possibilities.

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 4
volumes.desc: The first in a series from international production company MusicJag- World Chill Vol 4- brings you flavors of  world music infused with hip beats, edgy sound design and excellent musicianship. Check the breezy "Exotic Islands" featuring lovely flute soloing and gently swaying rhythms, The rich, worldly melody of "Mixed Up Blood" is enhanced by an exotic female vocal and subtle instrumental accents, together making a languid, sultry disco.  MusicJag's excellent production ensures great sound and dynamics, and the compositions are original and creative. World Chill Vol 4 features great chill-out, lounge and world fusion tracks to warm the soul. Keep checking our website for the latest MusicJag releases!

volumes.title: Waltz And Tango Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Another selection from MusicJag, Waltz And Tango Vol 1, brings international flavors and charming accordion melodies.
Check out "Quick Occasions'" waltzing, romantic accordion and organ melody accented by sweetly swelling strings, "Tangonini Dance" is a stuttered tango with humorous conversations between oboe, accordion and piano, "The Second Bastringue" is a tango with a twist- a techno backbeat updates the genre and adds syncopated momentum. The great selection of international flavors and lovely melodies on "Waltz And Tango Vol 1"are sure to inspire and delight!r player with an ear for heart warming melodies and a compositional style all his own. His acoustic rock tracks bring fields of green and warm breezes to mind with a gentle touch and an easy sway. Check the poignant lyrics in "Of The Moment Vocal"- a relaxed delivery, backed by a warmly rocking band enriches this track with love and introspection. "Going Gathering" is another acoustic rocker with a gentle touch and an emotive grace. There are also several short tag pieces "Mumbai Morning", "New Moon" and "Come On In" that would be iddeal segue pieces. The pristine production brings out subtle nuances of the guitar and really brings the music to life. Modern Pop Annd Lyric Vol 2 is a gentle batch of emotive tracks that will warm and uplift your soul.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 3
volumes.desc: Progressive instrumentation and thoughtful composition are key to the stirring and heartfelt tracks on Acoustic Guitar Vol 3. The dusky, intertwining guitar lines on "Lady El Monica" weave a gentle, meditative tapestry. "Seize Two" is a wistful tone poem for acoustic and alto sax with an unpretentious earthy yearning. The introspective track "And Bip" adds a touch of electronica into the mix with it's understated machine drum and synth accents. The rich, thoughtful tunes on "Acoustic Guitar Vol 3" will intrigue and frame lovely moments.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 3
volumes.desc: Composer Marco Mastrocola's newest collection, Rocked Up Vol 3, brings plenty of in your face rock and roll attitude and packs a heavy punch. A tight knit rhythm section compliments Marco's melodic but heavy chording. Great pop wit gives the songs kick and pulse, The souped up "Eliminator's" punky edge rocks fast and clean, "Spirit Electric" has an LA gleam in it's hard rock rush, "MugShot's" grungy burn and ripping guitars will get you moving. Also included are 5 second stings for each track. Check out "Rock Grooves Vol 1" and "Oriental Grooves Vol 1" for more great work by Marco.

volumes.title: Soultronic Vol 1
volumes.desc:
New Composer Jarvis Gutter' s soulful R&B; stylings are key to Soultronic Vol 1. Smooth, warm melodies flow over the lush, embracing rhythms with an easy grace. The fresh sounds and subtle nuances are enhanced by the clean, shiny production.
Dig "The Big Jump" with it's smooth syncopated rhythms and romantic sunny melodies. The track "The Candy Song" has a relaxed step beat and a mellow romantic feeling. Soultronic Vol 1 updates R&B;'s sounds while still staying true to the classic, groovy R&B; vibe.

volumes.title: Soultronic Vol 2
volumes.desc: More soulful tracks from Composer Jarvis Gutter: Soultronic Vol 2 another great selection of tracks with a classic soul-R style and feel. Great fidelity and subtle use of modern sounds and production techniques updates the ingredients but these tracks still retain a soulful feel and love for the classic genre. Soultronic Vol 1&2s' lush and embracing tracks are sure to put you in the mood.

volumes.title: World Mix Vol 6
volumes.desc: Another great set of tracks from Musicjag Productions, World Mix Vol 6, brings emotive world-influenced tracks with excellent instrumentation, original melodies and great production. Dig the transcendental rhythms of the hypnotic "Mister Bendidi". The track "Lady Nora" is an intense, cinematic piece with filtered drums and amazing dynamics. Kyoto and flute give romantic swoons to the Asian influenced "One Song To Suzie" Musicjags insightful compositions are a delightful addition to Freeplays' catalog- stay tuned for more!ading and regenerating with a sinister feel. The picturesque and mellow tracks on New Age Ambient Vol 1 feature pristine production and a harmonious vibe sure to calm the most restless spirit.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 4
volumes.desc:
Rocked Up Vol 4's hard edged guitars and aggressive rhythms don't outweigh the fine production and dynamic sensibilities
inherent to Musicjag's team. From punked up pop "No Trust", to blusey garage "It Is So Good", to some killer hair-band antics "Heavy Drop Theme" many bases of rock are tagged- hard. Rocked Up Vol 4 has smoking hot guitars and heavy beats ready to fill any metalic needs.

volumes.title: Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Ron Gamache's excellent guitar playing and and wonderful compositions are featured on Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 2. His charming and understated guitars add lovely flavors to the spot-on backing instrumentation. Dig the wonderful bossa, "Sea And Sun," with its sexy breeze. "Hero's Melody" is a warm, charming tune with rich double tracked guitars. "When I Think Of Mary Ann" is a poignant reminiscence with a heartfelt melody played on piano, strings and nylon stringed guitar. Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 2 has wonderful compositions, crystal clear production, and fantastic instrumentation that all add up to charming, delightful tunes.

volumes.title: World Mix Vol 7
volumes.desc: Another great set of tracks from Musicjag- World Mix Vol 7 brings you more great world beats with exotic melodies and ethnic instrumentation. Dig the earthy, warm vibe of the Afro-beat "Tribaloo" and it's uplifting group vocals and driving percussion. "Traveling To Asia" has a sinister, simmer in it's dark strings and clanking, ghostly percussion accented by a thunderous horn blast. "Summer In Istanbul" has a humid, mysterious edge in it's plucked oud, bells and percussion adding an otherworldly feel. The sterling production adds to the excellence found on World Mix Vol 7- an enriching and atmospheric set of tracks.

volumes.title: Cinematic Electronic Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Jody Friedman brings driving, syncopated electronica tracks to Cinematic Electronic Vol 2. His clean, sparse production does not hamper the soulful, upbeat glide of these tracks. With cinematic flair he balances the robotic beats with shifting effects, heartfelt melodies and an ear for tension and texture. Dig the driving pulse of "Monster Truck Rally" with it's motor-like motivational feel. "I Saw The Figure" has a clean economy in it's driving edge. The strident strings and propulsive, glitchy beats of "Ghosts And Ghouls" give a modern edgy feel to the dark track. Cinematic Electronic Vol 2 is packed with picturesque tracks with hip drive and melodic soul.

volumes.title: Classical Vol 1
volumes.desc: The quality musicianship and warm production makes this new collection from Musicjag shine. Classical Vol 1 is an enriching and melodic new set of tracks- Check the heroic, battle-worn majesty of "Majestic Challenge" with it's comanding percussion and uplifting melodies."Frenjik Performers" is a cinematic lament with emotional strings weaving a poignant melody. "A Song For Jean" is a loving waltz between strings and piano with a delightful air. Classical Vol 1 is a great set of dramatic, cinematic tracks that will enrich any special moment.

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 5
volumes.desc:
New Composer Mark Taylor weaves exotic Middle-Eastern elements into his spirted compositions for World Chill Vol 5. With a compelling and spacious mix, these pieces have cinematic depth and emotional dynamics- "Old Country Memories" is a striking desert waltz with an urgent gypsy violin and a smokey female vocal. "Through The Gates" cinematic atmosphere of eerie synth and foreign vocal is accented by echoing percussion and 
punctuated by clamorous string lines.  Resonating choral voices give a ghostly depth to "Untill The End Of Time", echoing piano and synth weave a humid, rainy atmosphere for the reverberating voices. The fantastical and vivid compositions found on World Chill Vol 5 are a delight and will add adventurious flavor to any scene.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 4
volumes.desc: Love for his instrument and joy in composition are qualities that shine on new composer Peter Hawkes tracks for Acoustic Guitar Vol 4. Traditional folk stylings are enhanced by  lovely dialogues between guitar and violin on the romantic "Adas Best" and the proud Irish reel "Not Even A Nip". Amazing slide guitar is joined by soulful violin and harmonica for the picturesque "Cracked Up Rag's" country ramble. "Lazy In Spain" is a languid tropicalia track featuring a softly blown trumpet and breezy violin. Beautiful melodies and a joyous warmth permeate Acoustic Guitar Vol 4, a great set of emotional and sublime tracks.

volumes.title: Industrial Glitch Vol 1
volumes.desc: This new, aggressive and dynamic set of tracks from our friends at Musicjag, Industrial Glitch Vol 1, is loaded with brash, motivational sounds. Dig the filmic, heavy hitting groove of "Exterminators" with it's raging machine pulse. "Particle Accelerator" is a driving, glitched-out noise fest with intense metalic synth textures. "Ooozzz Theme" has tension building breaks and furious rhythms when the beats kick in. The synth manipulation is amazing and you'll wonder where they got those sounds and the glitched beats add a edgy modernism. Industrial Glitch Vol 1 a dynamic, motivational new volume that will raise your pulse and get you moving.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 7
volumes.desc:
Composer David Flavin is back with more heartfelt, melodic, genre-jumping tracks for Music For Pictures Vol 7.
Clean production and emotional melodic arrangements are key features of David's pieces and this new set does not disappoint-
check the dramatic lament "Should Have Known" with it's winding, emotional strings and piano. "Heavy Matter" is a dynamic, rocking little piece with cool, spaced-out breaks. "Full Tank" is a jamming blues with big popping horns, funky guitars and a steady, thumping rhythm section. Well thought and emotional, the tracks on Music For Pictures Vol 7 bring dynamic auditory flavors to any scene.

volumes.title: Classical Vol 2
volumes.desc: Musicjag brings more emotive, elegant, light orchestral tracks for Classical Vol 2. From the forboding impending doom of "The Judgement" to the lighthearted, eloquent "Roadside Walk" many moods are explored- "Number One" is a mysterious waltz "The Empire At War" is a dynamic, foreshadowing anthem with a courageous attitude. Another excellent contribution from Musicjag Productions, Classical Vol 2 is full of rich, thoughtful compositions.

volumes.title: Circus Fun Vol 1
volumes.desc: Circus Fun Vol 1 features rollicking, clowning, classic circus tunes. With tongue firmly in cheek these charming tracks will suprise and delight! Check the colorful, coy "Funny Story" for a wonderous tune, "Circus Games" is a tumbling goofy melody with a clowning vibe. "The Staccati Song" is a quirky march with an upbeat shine. Circus Fun Vol 1 is chock full of lighthearted, fun tracks- a perfect backdrop for any party scene.

volumes.title: Techno Vol 2
volumes.desc: Musicjag Productions upgrade the dance floor for Techno Vol 2 with dynamic synth-work and smart production. Groovy, hip and cheeky, these fun, upbeat tracks will get you moving! Dig the phased synths and heart-pause beats of the neon "Nostalgic Days", "Water Flower" is an odd, percolating track with a sunny feel. "To Die For" features a scrambled, dubby beat with a happy laid-back groove. Techno Vol 2 brings you happy, hip shaking tracks to brighten and motivate any scene.

volumes.title: Electronica Transmissions Vol 5
volumes.desc:
Dynamic and entrancing, Electronica Transmissions Vol 5 is a great new set of  electronica tracks with a modern edge. Check out the skipping snares of "Bossing Around" with it's motivational groove accented by dj sratching and bubbling bass.
"Hitting The Road" is a smooth grooving track with a soulful, calm vibe. "Gypsum" has warm, enveloping pads and a syncopated beats with odd spoken lines adding an enigmatic twist. Electronica Transmissions Vol 5 is a rich, energetic collection sure to add a dashing edge to any situation.

volumes.title: Funk And Soul Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Another set by Musicjag productions featuring tight production and imaginative compositions. Easy grooving and smooth stepping rhythms are key elements of Funk And Soul Vol 1. dig the simmering push of "The Fourth Crusade", a dynamic track with 
cool, smokey vibe. Stand-up bass provides a deep warmth for a calm rim-shot beat on "Seven Men Dreaming" with jazzy guitars sketching a sublime melody. Funk And Soul Volume 3 is a rich and upbeat set of funk kissed tunes sure to bring light and an easy sway to any scene.

volumes.title: Intelligent Dance Music Vol 1
volumes.desc: Dynamic and moody, atmospheric and ruminating are all fitting tags for Intelligent Dance Music Vol 1, Another professional set of tracks from Musicjag. Glitchy beats and exotic synwork is key to progressive tracks like the exotic "Secret Hidden Message" and the dark "Sir J". The eerie and ethereal synths on "Moments" gell into a seductive chillout track with a subtle, uplifting groove. Intellegent Dance Music Vol 1 is a emotive and cinematic set of tracks sure to add depth and dynamics to any scene.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 3
volumes.desc: Composer Patrick James Slattery's dark imagination and keen sense of dynamics are key elements of Dark Dimensions Vol 3. Eerie synths and deep dark rhythms are the building blocks for his intense soundscapes- check out the tense "Brooding" -the cavernous synths are accented by clockwork percussion enhancing the white knuckle vibe. The track "Ruby Quest" has an unearthly chorus and pounding, rythmic string lines giving a scarry end of the world vibe. Dark Dimensions Vol 3 is a rich, dynamic set of tracks sure to add depth and tension to any scene.

volumes.title: Solid Rock Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Composer Leroy Bocchieri is back with killer guitars and rocking rhythms for Solid Rock Vol 1.- with warm production and an upbeat outlook, these driving tracks provide positive motivation and propulsive dynamics. Dig the sunny "Soaring Towards The Full Moon"  with it's open road feel, "Fully Saturated" is a jamming romp that will push the clouds out of the sky. "Retired Sheriff" is a lighthearted jaunt featuring a happy, whistled lead.
Solid Rock Vol 1 is a positive set of rock tracks sure to brighten and enhance any scene.

volumes.title: Deluxe Rhythm And Blues Vol 2
volumes.desc: Musicjag productions brings on the smoking blues for Deluxe Rhythm And Blues Vol 2, featuring excellent production, professional chops and imaginative songwriting, this set is sweet. Dig the subtle rock blues of "A Gift For Martin" with languid guitars and smooth rhythms. "Lonely James" is a gut-bucket blues for sweetly stroked acoustic guitar. "I Need You Now" features hot female vocals over a smokey R&B; jam. Deluxe Rhythm And Blues Vol 2 is a sexy set of tracks that ooze the blues.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 9
volumes.desc:
Dj Mar and Dean strike back with more heavy galactic techno from the bleeding edge for Electrofied Vol 9. Intense soundscapes and driving rhythms are key features on this bold new set. Amazing synth sounds and effects over staccato beats make you feel as if the dancefloor will lift off into outerspace! Dig the aggressive pulse of "Galactic Energy" and feel the turbulent beats and swirling synths. Rising flitered synths and dark beats give "Dark Force" a propulsive, motivational drive.
Electrofied Vol 9 is a bangin techno set sure to get the party started right!

volumes.title: Trance-Floor Vol 2
volumes.desc: Musicjag hits the spot with some cool, hip electronica tracks for Trans- Floor Vol 2. Dynamic, picturesque and inventive, this collection brings electronic styles from trip-hop ("Trip Top Sounds") to electronica ("The Soft Hat") to hip-hop ("In The Microphone"). Excellent production is enhanced by great sounds and creative composition, making Trance-Floor Vol 2 a great set of electronica tracks that will bring modern melodies and dynamic rhythms to any scenic situation.

volumes.title: Electric Love Vol 1
volumes.desc: DJ Mar And Dean give the techno a little love flavor for Electric Love Vol 1, as heavy, imaginative and danceable as ever. These hot new tracks feature vocals and samples in the mix. "Keep It Steady" features frantic vocals and samples amidst the disco swirl. "Feel The Rhythm's" jungle beats are enhanced by wordless female vocals, achieving a perfect groove. The masterful mixes of DJ Mar and Dean keep getting hotter, making Electric Love Vol 1 a must have set of upbeat, killer techno.

volumes.title: Funk And Soul Vol 2
volumes.desc: The latest in a series of volumes from the awesome Musicjag Productions, Funk And Soul Vol 2, brings you easy grooving soul, funk, and r&b; styled tracks. Dig the quick stepping jack beat and jazzy guitar of "The Next Morning"- with it's calm syncopation and mellow groove, "Incoming Mail" is a smooth jazz with a bit of a theme feel, neat arpeggio and synth hits give a "coming up next' flavor. Musicjag's excellent production and smart song writing are featured on Funk And Soul Vol 2- an easy, smooth set of soulful tracks that soothe and move the spirit.

volumes.title: Deluxe Rhythm & Blues Vol 2
volumes.desc: Musicjag productions brings on the smoking blues for Deluxe Rhythm And Blues Vol 2, featuring excellent production, professional chops and imaginative songwriting, this set is sweet. Dig the subtle rock blues of "A Gift For Martin" with languid guitars and smooth rhythms. "Lonely James" is a gut-bucket blues for sweetly stroked acoustic guitar. "I Need You Now" features hot female vocals over a smokey R&B; jam. Deluxe Rhythm And Blues Vol 2 is a sexy set of tracks that ooze the blues.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Patrick James Slattery's intense, dynamic soundscapes are key elements of Dark Dimensions Vol 4. This is a propulsive, cinematic set of tunes, check the epic, driving "Last Warrior Standing" featuring an unearthly choir with dark undertones over suspenseful, demonic rhythms. The Thundering, staccato rhythms and pulsing string lines of "Protecting The Hull" rage with cinematic furor. The aggressive "The Last Military Decision" has an apocalyptic, gripping pulse that will have you on the edge of your seat. Dark Dimensions Vol 4's crisp production and cinematic dynamics will add tense and suspenseful flavors to any scene.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 5
volumes.desc: New Composer Timothy Ziesmer's dynamic and intelligent rock compositions are key elements on Rocked Up Vol 5- along with excellent guitar playing and a great rhythm section. The tracks touch genres from grindcore to easy country tinged rock. The track "Face Time" has swaggering guitars and rocking, insistent pulse,  "Kill Em All" features excellent lead guitar, flicking out solos like dealing cards, and neat little work outs of the riff, driving on an accent and then laying in the groove nicely. On "Country Wide" ringing chords and sweet slide guitars bring a shade of country as the song morphs thru different grooves and accents with joy and delight. Rocked Up Vol 5 is a dynamic and colorful set of tracks and the upbeat and boisterous mood of the band will impart a rocking and lively pulse to any situation.

volumes.title: New Age Ambient Vol 1
volumes.desc: Lush, atmospheric chill-out tracks are featured on New Age Ambient Vol 1- another excellent set from Musicjag Productions. "First Date" has a relaxing vibe, accented by chimes and a slowly stepping chill beat, the track floats like a warm summer day. "Jan The Second" features an evocative melody with a shimmering nostalgic feel.  "Agoraphobia" takes a darker turn- it's cascading synth lines weave a dark melody, fading and regenerating with a sinister feel. The picturesque and mellow tracks on New Age Ambient Vol 1 feature pristine production and a harmonious vibe sure to calm the most restless spirit.

volumes.title: Jazz And The City Vol 1
volumes.desc: From smooth jazz to gypsy guitar jazz this varied set showcases great musicianship and creative composition. Dig the alto sax and acoustic guitar interplay on the cinematic "Gamma Field", for a more modern sound, check "Memei Notes" with it's relaxed groove and sassy sax blowing hot licks. "Jijola Melody" is classic jazz with lovely guitar soloing and a charmed vibe. Jazz And The City Vol 1 is an engaging set of picturesque tracks sure to frame any scene with a sophisticated, cool vibe.

volumes.title: Classical For Film Vol 1
volumes.desc: Drama, suspense and elegiac beauty are featured elements of Classical For Film Vol 1. Deftly executed and masterfully produced these elegant tracks will enhance emotive scenes with magic and mystery. Check the dynamic and suspenseful "Larrys Car"- strident strings giving push and rumbling synth rhythms adding a dynamic atmosphere. "Keoline Tune" is a mystical track with a childlike wonder. Classical For Film Vol 1 was put together by Musicjag productions and features excellent production and compositional dexterity sure to bring dynamic and emotive grace to any scene.

volumes.title: Euro Disco Vol 1
volumes.desc: Happy and carefree jams are key to Euro Disco Vol 1's international flavor- you could be in a swank club in Monaco or on the beach in Ibiza. A pleasure and lightness pervades these funky beats dig the hot distorted guitar leads of "My Third Eye"- featuring cow belled beat and funk bass adding groovy syncopation. Positive synth arpeggio and skipping step beats give "Start The Dance" an upbeat motivation that will rock the dance floor. Euro Disco Vol 1 is a great collection of dance blasts that will keep the party rocking.sure to warm and intrigue your soul.

volumes.title: Moving Images Vol 1
volumes.desc:
New Composer Jonathan Geer has a joyful touch with melody and dynamic, his expressive moods and textures shift with grace and imagination. "The Toy Makers Dream" magical circus instruments weave a complex, shambling melody at once childish and darkly introspective, strings bring a growing suspense that erupts suggesting a great and frightening discovery. "Heirloom"
is a poignant piece for piano that evokes a quiet resolve and a gentile, nurturing love. The track "Town Square" is a charming country folk tune with singing violin lines and a saucy dobro solo. Moving Images Vol 1 is a fascinating set of earthy, emotional will take you on a journey infused with the beauty and might of nature and beyond.

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Vol 8
volumes.desc: Composer David Flavin's ebullient style shines on the diverse new set Music For Pictures Vol 8, from jolly children's tracks like "Whats The Rumpus" and "Dog Days" to the beach party rave-up "Here Comes Good Times", to the sweet, soloing acoustic guitar in he easy rocking "Free To Fly" many different styles are touched, but all overflowing with light hearted emotion. Great instrumentation and rich production add dynamics and warmth to Music For Pictures Vol 8, a refreshing and upbeat set of tunes sure to uplift and motivate.

volumes.title: Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 2
volumes.desc: Composer Steve Glotzer, (Modern Pop And Lyric Vol 1, Contemporary Jazz Guitar Vol 1) is a masterful guitar player with an ear for heart warming melodies and a compositional style all his own. His acoustic rock tracks bring fields of green and warm breezes to mind with a gentle touch and an easy sway. Check the poignant lyrics in "Of The Moment Vocal"- a relaxed delivery, backed by a warmly rocking band enriches this track with love and introspection. "Going Gathering" is another acoustic rocker with a gentle touch and an emotive grace. There are also several short tag pieces "Mumbai Morning", "New Moon" and "Come On In" that would be iddeal segue pieces. The pristine production brings out subtle nuances of the guitar and really brings the music to life. Modern Pop Annd Lyric Vol 2 is a gentle batch of emotive tracks that will warm and uplift your soul.

volumes.title: New Age Ambient Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Mellow, atmospheric, downtempo grooves are featured on New Age Ambient Vol 2., a sublime new set of tracks from Musicjag Productions. Subtle, flowing rhythms accented with world elements and gentle melodic synths are key elements of tracks like "Miss Sedona" and "Sunrise At Dawn". The gentle downcast piano melody of "Nostalgia" is accented by an atmospheric church organ and  fuzzy drum machine beat. Crisp production enhances the warm nuances of this calm and cerebral set of tracks and the soporific melodies are calming and warm.
New Age Ambient Vol 2 is an emotive volume sure to bring a warm, delicate feel to any scene.

volumes.title: Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 1
volumes.desc:
New composer Steve Kornicki imbues his orchestral pieces with a sophisticated emotional grace. Beautiful arrangements and a lovely orchestra really make this set of tracks shine. The driving bells, piano and timpani of "Majestic Brilliance" weave a lovely mesmerizing rhythmic melody that has avant-garde flavors and a great filmic feel. A chorus of discordant flutes offsets the defiant, graceful swell of horns on Resonant Solitude with a natural balance that is almost terrifying. The wise majesty of "Flowing Grandeur"  
breathes with a virtuous dignity and grace. Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 1 is a sweeping, cinematic new volume who's wondrous melodies and fantastic compositions will enrich your soul.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol. 6
volumes.desc: New composer Darko Saric delivers powerful, ebullient rock with new tracks now available on Rocked Up Vol. 6.  These compositions ring with exuberance and contemplation, and add a touch of smooth, balmy beat flavor.   For example, Early Morning Tea is an infectious trance groove that lays sultry keyboard synths over a heavy hitting backbeat and a guttural clavinet hook.  The driving guitar riffs on Born Again make this triumphant tune sparkle with bold emotion.  Its wide-open, down-the-road flavor is profoundly uplifting.  In contrast, Tristeza is a dark, mystifying venture into the unknown, incorporating ominous electric drums and weeping electric guitar for an absolutely enchanting thematic aura.  Check out Rocked Up Vol. 6 for a great collection of rocking tracks that will set any scene brilliantly.

volumes.title: Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 2
volumes.desc: With Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 2, new composer Goffredo Orlandi presents a diverse palette of haunting melodies and cinematic moods. The exquisite orchestral arrangement and strong emotional pull of Orlandis compositions is ever present on this captivating volume. For instance, delicate strings and soft piano carry a beautiful melody with an introspective, reminiscent feel on The Moon of Italy. The boisterous call-and response between woodwinds, timpani, strings, and voices on Over the Stars is spellbinding.  With a turbocharged horn section bolstered by furious percussion and forebodingly dissonant piano, He Never Sleeps is fueled by a tone of urgency. The picturesque musical atmospheres to be found on Orchestral Soundscapes Volume 2 are sure to inspire passion and transport audiences.

volumes.title: Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 3
volumes.desc: Goffredo Orlandi brings more of his gracefully nuanced melodies to Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 3, rich, sky-reaching strings and  elegant orchestral percussion are key elements of his delightful compositions. Check the golden-hued strings leading "Castle On The Hill", with it's earthy rhythms gently swaying beneath the lilting melody. "Breath Of Life"' features  luxurious string lines that are pushed by a modern rhythm played on orchestral percussion- a nice contrast that enhances the heartfelt swelling strings and horns. Also found on Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 3 are a few excellent orchestral "stings" with dignified, driving elements perfect for intros or bumpers. Orchestral Soundscapes Vol. 3 is a lovely set sure to capture any listeners ear and tug the heartstrings.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol. 5
volumes.desc: Composer Patrick James Slattery brings haunting, intense soundscapes and his gothic, artful style full force on  Dark Dimensions Vol 5. Metallic clangs and bass notes are manipulated to create wicked, evil atmospheres that are deftly colored with dark, ebbing synths and effected rhythms. Dig the intense "Alley Rat", the effected noises open with a thunderous clang but the ringing echoes Fade to a claustrophobic hum. In "Druk Gyalpo", percussion and flute add an exotic edge to the dark underpinnings. "Reliquary" is a cinematic, simmering groove that beats underneath a humid,  worldly mix of chanted male vocals, flute and and dusty synths. The great production of the intense, dynamic music adds an edgy sheen. Dark Dimensons Vol 5 is a trove of wicked atmospheres sure to add depth and drama to any production.

volumes.title: Sunny Summer Rock Vol 2
volumes.desc: David Flavin's compassionate melodies and easy rock flair are key to the upbeat rock grooves found on Sunny Summer Rock Vol 1. The gentle, breezy "Love Is All Around" has a winsome, beachy feel and a charming pulse, "Coming Up" has an easy drive with jangling acoustic and a ringing electric lead. "Flexible Flyer" has an interesting, shifting rhythm under melodic,  atmospheric electric guitar. Warm and embracing melodies are at the root of all the delightful tracks on Sunny Summer Rock Vol 2, and it's upbeat rock pulse will add vibe to any situation.

volumes.title: Electrofied Vol 10
volumes.desc: DJ Mar and Dean are back with another slamming set of house and techno tracks sure to get the dancefloor jumping and your blood pumping. Dig the killer house beats of "Dark Rift" with bouncy synth arpeggios and robotic noises pushing the cranked beat. On "Devils Triangle" syncopated toms and snares build a hypnotic rhythm with intense laser synths and crazy arpeggio lines. Wicked, careening synths bounce across the soundfield on "Heatwave", with popping bass and rapid fire snare laying down the groove. Awesome production and fresh sounds keep the intense tracks on Electrofied Vol 10 cutting edge- these heavy tracks will add momentum and push to any scene.

volumes.title: Rockin Pop Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Ernie Lake's productions (Dance and Pop Series, Hip Hop Vol 5, Trance-Floor Vol 1 to name a few) trend towards sultry disco and glossy, expressive beats, but his tracks always have a sparkle and smooth glide that make them memorable. He brings that touch to Rocking Pop Vol 1 with more of a full band feel, check out the easy slice of Americana "My Country Groove" a warm and worn melody and a heartfelt groove. The reverb-ed guitar of "Driving Sideways" adds a dynamic vibe over a pushing snare.  "Avoid Floyd" features a slamming post-psychedelic
guitar soaring over an acid-washed jam. The sparkling production and motivational push of the rhythms of Rockin Pop Vol 1 will add dynamic flavors to any situation.

volumes.title: Dance  Pop Vol 8
