volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Concerto 8 Pathetique
volumes.desc: Beethoven's solo piano works really show his brilliance, The Frequency Orchestra doesn't disappoint with this delightful masterwork. Incredible piano playing brings this composition to life- seething with intense emotion and played with artful joy.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 9
volumes.desc: This lighthearted and colorful work for solo piano sings of a lust for life and the joy of composing for the piano. You can feel the love Beethoven has for the instrument in this work. Dave Greendale's steady hand sets this sonata aflame with it's reverent production and spirited playing.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Bizet Selections
volumes.desc: Bizet's colorful compositions are reverently played by the Frequency Orchestra in this dramatic volume. The heartfelt emotions of the operatic "Angus Dei" shine on the fantastic male vocal lead. The sweet and golden-hued strings of "Church Bells" flow with a spiritual joy.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Boccherini Minuet
volumes.desc: Boccherini's delightful waltz dances in all it's glory. The Frequency Orchestra's stately and sublime rendition will lift the darkest spirits and clear the shadows from the corners. Majestic and charming.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 14
volumes.desc:
Beethoven's enthralling and dexterous workout for piano, The Moonlight Sonata,
is a good way to get to know the m
 September, 5, 2008 - Frequency Orch. Bizet Selections 
Bizet's colorful compositions are reverently played by the Frequency Orchestra in this dramatic volume. The heartfelt emotions of the operatic "Angus Dei" shine on the fantastic male vocal lead. The sweet and golden-hued strings of "Church Bells" flow with a spiritual joy.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 21
volumes.desc: Beethoven's fierce work, dedicated to the Count of Waldstein, is a challenging and dynamic work. The opening begins minimally, gradually crescendoing to ferocious, virtuosic modulations, the second movement expounds on the main theme with artistic and playful ornamentation.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 25
volumes.desc:
Minimal and unadorned by Beethoven's standards, this sonata, Opus 79 (Cuckoo) features a reflective and subtle hand, accented by sweeping harmonies and constant tempo swings. Bouncy, playful and memorable the delightful theme 
is repeated with energetic joy.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 26
volumes.desc: Beethoven's brilliant use of E-flat as the base for this otherwise sad and lonely work adds glimmers of hope and light through what might be a overly dramatic, run-of-the-mill dirge. Flowing from simple motifs, often with extravagant elaborations, in the first piece, to the quiet and reverent sadness in the second piece there remains an underlying warmth, which springs to life in the hopeful and rousing closing movement. A delightful work that speaks to the emotions of life, loss and love.

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 6
volumes.desc:
Composer Jerome Langlois' second orchestral collection, Volume 6, is a really unique and beautiful set of tracks. Equal parts classical and jazz inspired, the unclassifiable music features sublime atmospheres, cinematic structures and joyful, childlike melodies. "Floating In The Air" does just that, with rising string lines and soaring flute, creating a delightful feel. A clarinet dances through the piece with an effortless ease giving a delightful aural sensation.
More of Jerome's music can be found on Orchestral Volume 5, these tracks will bring a totally unique, yet classic feel to your project or scene.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 8
volumes.desc: Beethoven's solo piano works really show his brilliance, The Frequency Orchestra doesn't disappoint with this delightful masterwork. Incredible piano playing brings this composition to life- seething with intense emotion and played with artful joy.

volumes.title: Digital Dreaming Volume 3
volumes.desc: New composer Simon Smart brings grooving downtempo beats to Digital Dreaming Volume 3, featuring warm, bright synth atmospheres, calm melodies and subtle machine drum rhythms. Hints of soul and glitch accent the ethereal tracks but above all- easy gliding beats and synths lead this mellow set. Check out "Larger Than Life"- An easy stepping machine beat with glitchy accents moves under a humid atmosphere, as synth pads, arpeggio bass lines and synth organ add smooth elements. "Street Smart" features funky, glitched beats rolling under dark booming sounds and synth effects to weave a moody, syncopated track. Simon's synth sounds are fresh and sublime and the production is top notch, so these tracks really stand out, Digital Dreaming Volume 3 will add relaxed and innovative atmospheres to any scene or project.

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 1
volumes.desc:
New composer Stephen Akina's cinematic compositions will lend themselves perfectly for film and backgrounds. On Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 1 his inspired melodies ride dramatic atmospheres that will enhance your project with emotional soundscapes. On "Magic Hotel", a dark, brooding soundscape of belled synths and dynamic strings moves with a mysterious menace. "Indian Lullaby" features lovely ethereal synth and echoing flute together weaving a charming, dreamy track brimming with a natural warmth. Stephens spot-on production gives these tracks warmth and verve and his melodies are fresh yet memorable.
Check out Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 1 by clicking the link above and immerse yourself in these lovely emotive tracks.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 30
volumes.desc: Following the sonata structure Beethoven takes us through dynamic and at times, surprising changes, the calmness of the first movement leads to an action packed second, full of musical conversations reflecting a question and answer feel, slowly building and veering back and forth.The third movement introduces unexpected drama at times. It  starts out slow and calm and all of the sudden out of nowhere comes a lifting moment, then back to where it all started. Frequency Orchestra is proud to bring you this dynamic and emotional sonata.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 1
volumes.desc:
The Four movements of Beethovens Piano Sonata Number 1,  go through a variety of musical themes. The first movement is a peaceful piece of easy listening, where a sequence is played up and down the scales in a peaceful manner.
The 2nd movement is even more peaceful than the first, and would be considered the peak of relaxation in the entire sonata.From this point the Sonata gets more exciting and changes its color.The third movement introduces a mixture of a relaxed yet agitated feeling which is a turning point for the music and is expected at this time.the forth movement returns us to the original feeling we got in the first two movements.The structure of this music piece leaves us thinking about quiet before the storm, the acttual storm, and the quiet after the storm.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Ezekiel Honig releases his second volume of ambient/downtempo tracks with Ambient Figures Vol 4, utilizing found sounds, recording effects and rhodes piano he weaves otherworldly little tunes that are both unique and organic. On Proximity Of Objects" a  glitched beat and fuzzy static noises build a smooth, relaxed beat as ringing rhodes notes weave a warm, repeating melody. "Paper Fields Dub" features odd noises, pings and organ that echo and give the track a reggae dub feel. The found sounds that make up the rhythms really are key to what sets Ambient Figures Vol 4 apart- these tracks will bring a unique feel and lo-fi flavors that will bring your project an atmosphere that is different than any other.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 17
volumes.desc: The "Tempest" knickname is perfect for Beethoven's 17th Sonata, beginning peacefully the piece soon bursts with keyboard fireworks and virtuosic composition. This exemplary work is played with magnificence and joy by The Frequency Orchestra. Dave Greendale's reverent production brings this lively sonata to life, please click the link above to enjoy one of Beethoven's most dynamic compositions.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 23
volumes.desc:
Brilliant and stormy are words that come to mind when listening to Beethoven's 23rd sonata (Appassionata), this dynamic work, rivaled only by the Hammerklavier
sonata in it's intensity, leaps and bounds with an inexhaustible energy. It is said this composition was released as Beethoven was finally coming to grips with his complete deafness, the fire and wrath of this work at times seems immortal and inhuman, showing us the complexity and depth of his intellect and soul.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 27
volumes.desc: This short sonata, Beethovens 27th, was called "a contest of the head and the heart", the first movement speaks to the rationality of the mind, and the second soars with melodies of the heart and it's efforts to escape the chains of reason. This moving work is deftly executed by the Frequency Orchestra and will bring dynamic and engaging melodies to enrich your day!

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Piano Sonata 29
volumes.desc:
Beethoven's most dynamic and challenging composition, Sonata 29 (Hammerklavier),
is the genesis of Beethoven's late period themes and inspirations. Virtuosic and incredibly complex, this work bursts with energy and intellect that is unique beyond the reach of most mere mortals. The Frequency Orchestra attacks this piece with verve and joy, capturing it's many difficult and intensive passages with unforgettable reverence. This dynamic work will spark your imagination with it's vivid colors and intense musicianship.

volumes.title: Action And Adventure Vol 5
volumes.desc: Composer David Flavin's new volume, Action And Adventure Vol 5, features very good pieces for military movie soundtracks. There are pieces for every type of scene, something for sad moments, something for joyous moments. Something for drama or adventure, for a memorial or loss, or just downtime. Something for a victorious return. Built over a simple bass line, the tracks climax nicely featuring spot-on  use of classical instruments, and thematic styles. Please click the above link to check out this fabulous soundtrack music.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Bach Selections
volumes.desc:
Featuring some of Bach's most famous works, Frequency Orch. Bach Selections, brings you the composers most light pieces: Air On A G String as well as his most dark: Toccata And Fugue in Dminor. Burning with his eloquent style, these works hi-light Bach's dramatic and emotional writing.
The musicianship is unrivaled and the sound is fantastically pristine- The Frequency Orchestra is proud to bring you this volume of masterful selections.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Brahams Symphony 4
volumes.desc: Brahams' 4th symphony came late in his career, and Brahams' wisdom and sincerity shines in this dynamic work. The first movement is poignant and romantic, swelling and flowing with a heartwarming glow, the second piece, a lyrical extension of the first comes across as a dirge with contemplative feel. The vivacious and joyful third movement, is pushed forward by a ringing triangle rhythm. The final movement grows ever intricate and ornamented, a slightly distressed undercurrent flows beneath the panoptic melody. This introspective and melodramatic piece will add poignant flavors to your project or scene with it's intelligent composition and wizened outlook.

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 5
volumes.desc: Composer Christopher Holland, incorporates an interesting mixture of classic and rock styles in Rock Grooves Vol 5.This album combines upbeat urgent pieces along with quiet peaceful and easy listening tracks. The composer takes us by surprise, at times in the middle of a quiet and relaxed piece, introducing a rock beat that comes out of the blue and vice versa. Rock Grooves Vol 5 brings you energetic tracks that will add  positive momentum to your project.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 1
volumes.desc: Beethoven's first major symphony, No. 1, hints at his potental right from the beginning- his assertive use of winds, counterpoint and scales shows his trust in his abilites, and the result is a fantastic symphony that drives and sparkles with thematic grace. The Frequency Orchestra shines on Beethovens dynamic debut, please click the link above to enjoy it for yourself!

volumes.title: Promos Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Sheldon Conrich, uses an interesting musical build in the album Promos Vol 4. The compositions  are pretty jazzy and classical, yet he stays in the rock genre, not crossing many boundaries. Interesting effects used in a number of songs. interesting to note that the panning on some of these effects, comes at us from different directions, and is unexpected at times. There are some great pieces for a summery/breezy feeling and some quite emotional and spiritual pieces as well. Overall, a great album of easy listening with great music. Please click the link above to check out some of these great music pieces.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 2
volumes.desc: Beethoven's vivacious 2nd symphony is brought to vivid life by arranger Dave Greendale and The Frequency Orchestra. Although not as furious as his first or fifth this symphony still uses soft-loud juxtaposition with dynamic results, but overall there is a light hearted and airy feel that belies his troubled personal life at the time of composition. That the Symphony No. 2 was initially panned speaks to the ways that Beethoven redefined the rules of classical music forever with his unmatchable style. Please click the link above to check out this game changing work.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 9
volumes.desc: Composer Patrick James Slattery brings back the dark, heavy, eerie sounds on Dark Dimensions Vol 9. Check out "Black Chopper" which boasts an aggressive synth that lays waste to the track with pounding drums keeping rhythm to an adrenaline pumping rush, accenting the rock beat with techno flavored rage. "Resentment" contains ghostly synths set the tone for a skin crawling sound, speeding up into a full haunted feel, also containing eerie voice like sounds whispering in the background.  This set will bring deep, eerie, spooky sound to any scene.

volumes.title: Country Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Kelly Weeks brings a home strung feeling in Country Vol 2.  bringing a banjo, harmonica, and deep guitar warm smooth sounds radiate outwards towards the listener.  Most notable of this set include "Steamboat Pickin" What starts out as a ghost town gun fight quickly turns into a quick stream gushing forth with sounds of banjos and guitars mixing together before ending with resounding twang.  "Cottage Fever" Contains quick banjo strokes combined with rhythmic drums that set a laid-back mood , smooth guitar and a casual harmonica mix in to add to the relaxing sounds. This set is nice mix of new guitar sounds with the classic sounds of old banjo's and harmonica.  Great warm, smooth, and cozy music for any scene.

volumes.title: Spanish Guitar Vol 1
volumes.desc: Composers DJ MAR N Dean, switch up from their normal techno style with this new volume, Spanish Guitars Vol 1- bringing together interesting elements to create a mixture of latin pop with traditional latin melodic styles, as well as a touch of world music. The composers use a simple song build that is expanded by the variety of instruments used in the different pieces. These tracks will be perfect for scenes needing a latin touch, Mar and Dean again expand horizons with Spanish Guitars Vol 1, please click the link above to check it out.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 4
volumes.desc:
This Beethoven Masterwork, Symphony 4, is a bit of an enigma, in that such a triumphant and dynamic work should start with such a tragic and mournful introduction- with sublime strings singing sad lines then quickly changing to a dynamic and mesmerizing symphony. The Frequency Orchestra's faithful rendition 
captures Beethoven's arching, sky-scraping melodies with resounding thunder and Dave Greendale's reverent production gives life to the subtle and not so subtle 
dynamics of this masterpiece. Please click the link above to enjoy Beethoven's Symphony 4.

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 7
volumes.desc: Composer Jerome Langlois'  exciting new Volume, Orchestral Vol 7, is inspired by the beauty of nature and its dramatic facets. The composers pieces are inspired by different kinds of weather, and natural habitants of various parts of the world. For the most part, the composer sticks to the classic genre, while introducing  new and exciting elements, which drop us into the wonders of creation. This volume works nicely for nature thematic scenes. Please click the link above to check out this dramatic work.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 5
volumes.desc: Beethoven's famous fifth symphony defies all attempts at definition, it flies gracefully and mightily through the entire catalogue of human emotions in it's 4 concise movements. The first movement brings you the memorable thundering melody and works intense elaboration with ever rising exposition, as you move through the symphony it only gets more stunning and moving as the orchestra plays many characters and elaborates on many feelings. This work really speaks to Beethoven's unique ability to get his meaning across with music- beating with his blood and his soul. This work goes with pretty much anything, click the link above to feel it for yourself.

volumes.title: Orchestral Vol 8
volumes.desc: Composer Jerome Langlois' newest contribution, Orchestral Vol 8, features his imaginative instrumentation and techniques infused with love and respect for the natural world. Led mostly by clarinet and piano, the earnest melodies breathe with the wordless emotions of nature. "Calling Over Tension To Chopinesque"  is a dark track featuring piano and clarinet weaving a swooning melody that is both reflective and uncertain- a feeling that is enhanced by tolling bells and tense strings. "Life Of A Butterfly" gives you exactly that: the first section in chrysalis, a suspended but secretly growing spark of life that soon flowers, blossoming with organic rhythms as the piano and clarinet weave dancing, emotive lines. You can find more of Jerome's fantastic tracks on Orchestral Volumes 5, 6 and 7 - please click the link above to introduce yourself to this wonderful music.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Schumann Piano Concerto 1
volumes.desc: Schumann's first piano Concerto is an exhibition in 19th century Romantic style, with sweeping strings and powerful, yet subtle, piano.  The orchestra offers perfectly complementary support for the rich harmonic textures of the piano as this piece alternately glides and drives forward, working towards a powerful ending.  The Frequency Orchestra's performance of Schumann's Piano Concerto 1 is a stunning example of Robert Schumann's compositional skill and is essential listening for anyone interested in the Romantic period of Western Classical music.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 7
volumes.desc:
Beethoven's dynamic 7th Symphony, is faithfully reproduced by the magnificent Frequency Orchestra. By this time in his career Beethoven was getting the respect he felt he deserved and this symphony was very successful, no doubt because of the utter joy the performers had playing the magnificent piece.
It is said that Beethoven himself leapt with pride and happiness from the rostrum at the conclusion of the first performance. Utilizing Beethoven's Quiet-Loud motif, this dynamic work is for the most part fast and furious, the second movement is marked as "slow' but it is slow only in comparison to the other 3 movements, the full orchestra paints with bold, colorful strokes, strings and winds add gossamer ribbons between the towering blasts. The dynamics, melody, and rhythms conspire to produce such an emotive and catchy work that you can't help but get caught up in the explosive fun. Please click the link above to get a piece of the action!

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Beethoven Symphony 8
volumes.desc: When asked why the 7th Symphony was more popular than the 8th, Beethoven replied that it was because the 8th was so much better than the 7th- I'll leave that for you to decide- Keeping with Beethoven's M.O., this work features many loud-quiet dynamics- the sparkling strings and the orchestra work in call and response volleys, lifting the melody to ever higher bursts of ornamentation. Beethoven also eschews the "Classic" symphonic rules in that the final movement is the most elaborate of the four. There is a underlying wry sense of humor throughout this work that, coupled with the obvious joy the symphony is to play, feels as if the players have let you in on the joke. Please click the link above to check out this masterful symphony for yourself!

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Schumann Symphony 1
volumes.desc: Robert Schumann's first symphonic work came relatively late in the composer's career, but nevertheless is a beautiful piece of composition that displays all of Schumann's stylistic idiosyncrasies.  Schumann's Symphony 1 garnered the nick name "Spring Symphony" due to its pastoral themes and graceful harmonic motion.  This performance does the piece justice and displays the artistry of one of the greatest composers of the 19th century.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Smetana Moldau River (from Ma Vlast)
volumes.desc: Bedrich Smetana, the famous 19th Century Czech composer, is perhaps best known for his cycle of symphonic poems titles Ma Vlast, or My Country, and Moldau River is one of the most celebrated sections of the cycle.  Drastic dynamic shifts and powerful horns give drama and tension to the piece as surging strings lift the orchestra up and drive it to a powerful conclusion.  Smetana's Moldau River is one of the most engaging works by one of the greatest Czech composers of all time.

volumes.title: Electronic Fused Vol 5
volumes.desc: DJ Mar and Dean are back with a stomping new set of electronic tracks for Electronic Fused Vol 5. The production is a tight as it can get, featuring slamming kicks and snares working body rocking beats, as punchy synths swerve and collide with fresh sounds and intense arpeggios. Mar and Dean keep getting better with every release (as this, and their other new volume, Spanish Guitars Vol 1 will attest) Dig the intense synth work on "Final Showdown"- mind blowing synths and pulsing techno beats lead the charge. On "Best Kind Of Bliss" sweet dance beats percolate under charged up, poppy synth line that will get your head nodding! These motivational electronic tracks will add a banging, futuristic edge to your project or scene, click the link above to get the party started!

volumes.title: Gothic Atmospheres Vol 1
volumes.desc: This most excellent set of cinematic tracks, Gothic Atmospheres Vol 1, brings you evil, foreboding compositions featuring wicked bass strings, haunted choral voices and lonesome melodies from the dark side. "No Youth's" effected, echoing drums and slithering noises build an evil atmosphere while a lonely violin sings a forsaken melody from within the depths. "Old Monastery" features a demonic vocal chorus singing a somber melody as dark strings weave a harrowing background. This dark and eerie set is just in time for Halloween- the perfect soundtrack for the scariest day of the year!

volumes.title: ELECTION DAY SPECIAL!! Frequency Orch. Sousa Selections
Frequency Orch. Strauss Selections
volumes.desc: This collection of works by late 19th Century composer Johann Strauss II features some of the composer's best known works.  Strauss was famous for his waltzes above all else and the Blue Danube is perhaps the most well loved piece that Strauss composed.  Strauss' Operetta, Die Fledermaus, or The Bat, shows a different side of the composer, but one that is no less inventive and powerful.  The Frequency Orchestra's Strauss Selections is a fun and exciting introduction to the works of this highly influential composer.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Suppe Light Cavalry (Overture)
volumes.desc: Romantic period composer Franz von Suppe is best known for his operas and operettas and the overture to his opera Leichte Kavallerie, or Light Cavalry, is his best known work.  This piece is remarkable in its progression from subtly brooding strings to intense and triumphant horns and driving percussion as the piece drives to a close.  A perfectly representative work from a composer who perhaps does not get as much notice as he should and the Frequency Orchestra's performance of Suppe's Light Cavalry Overture is a testament to the composer's skill.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky 1812 Overture
volumes.desc: This famous piece by Russian composer Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky is one of the composer's most dramatic and triumphant works, featuring an epic conclusion that is no doubt one of the most recognizable slices of Classical composition.  The piece builds tension through the opening as the orchestra slowly builds up steam until the dramatic ending.  The Frequency Orchestra gives Tchaikovsky's 1812 Overture a faithful and powerful performance.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Nutcracker
volumes.desc: Tchaikovsky's Nutcracker Suite is surely one of the most iconic and well-loved pieces in the whole of Western Classical music, and the piece has a defined place in popular culture.  Aside from the Nutcracker's popularity, the piece displays some of Tchaikovsky's most beautiful work, with lush orchestration and amazing melodies.  These selections from the Nutcracker will no doubt show how deserved a place this piece has in the musical consciousness of the western world.

volumes.title: Cinematic Electronic Vol 5
volumes.desc:
Composer Michelangelo Sosnowitz brings upbeat melodies, punchy beats and transfixing arrangements to his electronic pop on Cinematic Electronic Vol 5.
Fully utilizing the stereo-field his panoramic melodies float and soar with vivid wide-angle emotion, as dynamic and dancable rhythms push the melodies forward. The epic "Never Forget You" has a dramatic, 80's feel, when the chorus opens up like rain clouds the melody shoots straight for your heart. "Skid Toward Victory" is a driving, champion piece featuring pounding drums and a riviting, winner-take-all orchestral melody with a heart-revving pulse.
You can find more of Michelangelo Sosnowitz's fantastic tracks in our Indie section: His solo album: "Love Songs" 
and his band, Rabbits Against Magic's album: "Daylight" Please click the links above to enjoy more of this fun and excellent composer!

volumes.title: Electronic Fused Vol 6
volumes.desc:
DJ Mar and Dean kick the beats up a notch for Electronic Fused Vol 6, Slamming, in your face beats are key to the exciting tracks found on this set- and these guys get synth sounds like you've never heard. Dig the explosive rhythm on "Dissolution"- the aggro beats push with aggressive, robotic abandon, giving a fantastically motivational track. "Turmoil Remixed" is absolutely off the hook,
the synth sounds warp, stretch, spin and mutilate in ways that will melt your headphones. Simply stunning. Electronic Fused Vol 6 will give you aggressive but danceable tracks flush with otherworldly sounds and dynamic, punchy beats. Click the link above to become a believer!

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Lizst Selections
volumes.desc: These selections from Liszt's seminal Hungarian Rhapsodies, presented by The Frequency Orchestra, show you both the serious and joyful sides of the talented and skillful composer. The Rakoczy March is a powerful and demanding orchestral work, rising to great and triumphal heights with dizzying energy and grand gestures. The Hungarian Fantasy is a soulful and dynamic work, exploding with joy and exuberance. The Frequency Orchestra shows off it's technical chops throughout this demanding work delighting in Liszt's complex imaginative composition, please click the link above to hear it for yourself.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Piano Concerto 1
volumes.desc: Tchaikovsky's first piano concerto is one of the composer's most popular works, and for good reason.  The piece is full of dramatic tension and features an epic structure that is held in place by furious, fleet-fingered piano.  Long stretches of graceful and subtle gestures are countered by powerful piano runs and dramatic strings.  Tchaikovsky's daring melodic and harmonic choices in this piece make it particularly exciting and historically significant.  One of the finest examples of late 19th Century composition, Tchaikovsky's Piano Concerto 1 is an essential listen.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Selections
volumes.desc: These selections from the works of Pyotr Tchaikovsky exhibit some of the key portions of some of the composer's finest works.  Tchaikovsky's opera Eugene Onegin is an adaptation of the verse novel of the same name by Aleksandr Pushkin and Tchaikovsky makes the perfect orchestral equivalent to Pushkin's timeless poetry.  Tchaikovsky's Sleeping Beauty is one of the composer's finest ballet's and has become a mainstay in modern ballet repertoire.  Tchaikovsky was one of the greatest composers of his time and these selections show just why.

volumes.title: Evil Intentions Vol 3
volumes.desc:
Evil Intentions Vol 3 brings you post-apocalyptic atmospheres and eerie, barren soundscapes. Featuring dark, growling cellos weaving tense bass melodies,
and cavernous, echoing timpani rolls that rumble like thunder in the distance, this quiet but threatening set of tracks delivers suspenseful dynamics that ooze evil intentions. From the morbid and eerie wasteland of "Hotel" to the slowly dying horns of "Street" Evil Intentions Vol 3 will add forlorn and frightening atmospheres to your project or scene with bone-chilling results.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Swan Lake
volumes.desc: This classic ballet from iconic Russian composer Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky is one of the composer's best and one of his most enduring works.  Graceful strings and playful melodies abound as the orchestra paints a vivid picture.  Tchaikovsky's Swan Lake is an absolute classic that will have you pirouetting like a Russian ballerina in no time.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Symphony 5
volumes.desc: Tchaikovsky might be most well-known today for his ballets, but he was a master of symphonic form, as his 5th Symphony properly displays.  The piece is full of tension and drama as the composer explores a wide range of moods throughout.  This performance of Tchaikovsky's Symphony 5 is a beautiful example of late 19th Century composition and the Frequency Orchestra lets the piece fully emerge, as the composer intended.

volumes.title: Thrills And Chills Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Just in time for Halloween, Freeplay brings you Thrills And Chills Vol 1, a haunting set of spooky tracks to flavor your project. These ethereal tracks feature stark, echoing piano lines, growling, haunted strings and evil, harsh synth sounds, weaving diabolically frightening music. Check the tense, hopless strings of "Passed Away" accenting it's dying embers of piano notes that echo away into infinity. "The Stakes" features a wicked harpischord weaving a morbid melody as choral voices, plucked strings and synth add nervous, tense accents.
Thrills And Chills Vol 1 is a delightful set that will add chilling atmospheres to your scenes with it's devilish music.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Chopin Selections
volumes.desc: The fluid and emotional solo piano of Chopin is featured on Frequency Orch. Chopin Selections, including works from Opus 28 and the seminal Revolutionary Study. The masterful playing shines with Chopin's sublime melodies and emotive dynamics. Romantic, engaged and joyful these beautiful solo piano pieces will provide a wealth of scenic moods for your project or production, please click the link above and enjoy!

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Mozart Great Mass In C Minor
volumes.desc:
The Frequency Orchestra is proud to present Mozart's eloquent and spiritual 
Great Mass In C Minor. This powerful and reverent work shines with glory and love. The playing and singing is stupendous and, as ever, David Greendale's production brings out the subtle and the monumental with equal respect.
Please click the link above to enrich your day with Mozart's masterful Mass.

volumes.title: Westerns Vol 1
volumes.desc: Westerns Vol 1 brings you exemplary cinematic moods full of the dusty spirit of the wild west. "American Spirit" is an excellent theme featuring shakers, hand drums and flute weaving a Native American theme with a suspenseful feel. "Gauchos" features castanets and flamenco guitar giving a distinctive Spanish flair to this melodic and atmospheric track. Westerns Vol 1 will add a distinctive flair to your project or production, please click the link above to taste the wild west.

volumes.title: Westerns Vol 2
volumes.desc: Westerns Vol 2 offers more cinematic western themes, featuring vivid tracks brimming with picturesque melodies and action packed rhythms. Check the aggressive and tenacious push of "Pistolero"- perfect for a showdown at the OK corral, "Sitting Bull" features a sparse, atmospheric melody, with a organic and uplifting feel. Westerns Vol 2 brings you high quality, dynamic tracks perfect for fleshing out your project with a touch of the wild west.

volumes.title: Promos Vol 5
volumes.desc:
New composer Hal Goldstein brings you an eclectic batch of tracks for Promos Vol 5, from the jaunty Cajun stomp of "Always Room For Dessert" to the upbeat funk of "How To Play The Game" this volume brings you many styles, the thread holding them all together is a feel good vibe throughout.
"Sundown Manipuri" is a driving raga with sitar and tabla weaving a delightful raga, "Friday Night Banjo" is a cinematic track with banjo and band taking a happy stroll, "Apple Cheeked Farm Girl" is a romping old-timey track replete with sawing violins, merry mandolin and jangly guitars. Promos Vol 5 is a wonderfully vivid set that will provide many flavors to spice up your scene or project with happy, upbeat songs.

volumes.title: Evil Intentions Vol 4
volumes.desc:
The fourth installment of Evil Intentions brings you dense, tense and dynamic tracks that will keep you on the edge of your seat. From the harrowing computerized flux of "Sweep Bass" to the driving horn blasts of "Mayday Mars"
These tracks will give your action/adventure scenes a sonic pulse with a dark and determined edge. Please click the link above to take a white knuckle ride.

volumes.title: Evil Intentions Vol 5
volumes.desc: Another excellent set of dynamic, dark and haunting tracks are found on Evil Intentions Vol 5, This volume features a full orchestra on most tracks, big echoing kettle drums and timpani deliver powerful rhythms as horns blow mighty blasts and ringing strings tremble. "Cannibals" is a pensive, humid track that feels like a walk through a steamy, overgrown jungle. "Dangerous Climbing" is a sneaky, rumbling track that feels as if it may tumble over the edge at any moment. Evil Intentions Vol 5 will fill your project with edgy soundscapes and thrilling orchestration.

volumes.title: Action And Adventure Vol 6
volumes.desc: Action And Adventure Vol 6 brings you driving victory themes and hard hitting action melodies- perfect for adding dynamic sonics to your scenes. Revved-Up synth drums are accented by timpani and kettle drums making for big, urgent rhythm beds, distorted, growling bass lines add a resounding bottom-end to the fast paced rhythms. Pealing, frantic strings, blaring horn blasts and grimy distorted guitars weave thrilling, edge-of-seat melodies, riding the dark rhythms with breathless determination. Action And Adventure will fill your scenes with exciting, pulse rasing beats and vivid, thrilling melodies.

volumes.title: Classical For Film Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Warm and engaging cinematic pieces are found on Classical For Film Vol 2,
From the heroic welcoming of "Fanfare" to the dark and sorrowful strings of Black Day" many moods are explored on this orchestral set. "Great Eye" combines grandiloquence with awe, conveying the feeling of confronting a foe much larger than one's self for the first time."Volcano"" is a dynamic piece spewing dynamic orchestration in a quick and blinding burst of confusion and anger. These cinematic classical works will provide delightful aural backdrops for your project or scene, please click the link above to enjoy this visual music.

volumes.title: Sports Highlights Vol 4
volumes.desc: Dynamic power rock tracks abound on Sports Highlights Vol 4, great for hard hitting cues and scenes. "Pits" and "Punks" are revved up punk rock tracks with popping So. Cal guitars and aggressive rhythms, "Solution" is a no-nonsense track with smoking guitars and sturdy, pummeling rhythms. Sports Highlights Vol 4 offers you crunching, body slamming cues and themes perfect for fleshing out sports oriented scenes and projects.

volumes.title:
Acoustic Guitar Vol 5gy to compliment any production. Come preview "Stars Don't Sleep" by clicking on the link above! 


 November 21, 2008 -
Promos Vol 6
volumes.desc:
Composer Hal Goldstein's new release Promos Vol 6 showcases his talents with a wide palate of styles, tight production and excellent musicianship.
The dark  "Fire On Ice" is an edgy post-rock track with an subtle but deadly drive, "Fishing Story" is a charming, picturesque slice of easy country featuring languid violin, mandolin and accordion swaying with a warm, summery earnestness. "Salsa After Siesta" is a charming, dancing Latin track with a sexy step. "Kiss For A Kiss" brings you a laid-back, soulfull slow-jam perfect for late Saturday nights. This vibrant and emotive set of tracks will provide great backdrops your scene or situation, please click the link above to hear these quality tracks.

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 2
volumes.desc:
New Composer Niklas Ahman brings graceful and delicate ambient works for Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 2, delayed guitars weave floating, sparkling atmospheres, accented by piano, celeste, synths, strings and bass. "In Balance" is a magical track with dulcimer, harp, celeste and strings weaving an enchanting melody. "Rain Window" sounds exactly like it's title, with delayed guitar notes descending like drips down a pane as a piano plays single, moody notes. "Marimdrama" is an ethereal spy theme played with a subtle yet engaging
pulse. These flowing and elegant tracks will add delightful and poignant atmospheres to your project or scene, please click the link above to enjoy these opalescent tracks.

volumes.title: Action And Adventure Vol 7
volumes.desc: This newest set of action tracks features big, grungy guitars and thrilling orchestral elements weaving grand, exciting melodies and rhythms to add push and pulse to your scene or project. "Hells On Wheels" features a distorted, filtered guitar riff as horns, synths and drums come in with a dynamic, propulsive backing. "Lower Westside's" skittering drum machine and rising strings push the track forward while an electric guitar weaves noise and notes into a wandering, moody melody. This punchy volume will add driving, adventurous sounds to your project, click the link to check it out.

volumes.title: Blues Vol 4
volumes.desc: Down-home, organic delta blues is featured on Blues Vol 4, sweet and earthy guitars pluck classic blues melodies as easy grooving drums and bass keep the rhythm. "I Go Alone" is a languid blues with hot, sultry guitar solos, "Time To Move On" features a solo knife-slide guitar laying poetic and stubborn lines with a moody grace. The excellent blues tracks on Blues Vol 4 will provide your projects with earthy, soulful melodies and gritty and earnest moods, please click the link above to hear these lovely tracks!

volumes.title: Classic Jazz Vol 5
volumes.desc: New FPM jazz composers Rick DellaRatta and Nikolay Levinovsky serve up a classy, brassy treat on Classic Jazz Vol 5, traditional in nature and voguish in spirit. On "As It Should Be," a muted trumpet blusters on gusts of brushed snare, then is politely chastened by a mannered piano. Bustling percussion and a handsomely dexterous double bass steer "Aging Gracefully," an elegantly tapered and prudent alto sax and piano-led saga. Sure to turn any deliciously grand affair a la mode, sample more by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Classic Jazz Vol 6
volumes.desc: On Classic Jazz Vol 6, their second set of elegant and timeless progressions, Rick DellaRatta and Nikolay Levinovsky crank up the spontaneity and romantic zeal even more for a stunning backdrop to any romantic scene, be it jolly or forlorn. On "Still Part Of Me," a heartbroken saxophone weeps a sorrowful melody over and over like one who cannot forget a lost love. On the other hand, "Pink Cocktail" is a sparkling elixir of zesty brass, briny percussion and rich piano, all clamoring to make the most of the last dance. Wistfully animated and plushly ornate, this collection is sure to arouse a twirling deluge of sentiment. Check out more by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: World Mix Vol 8
volumes.desc: World mix volume 8 features some fantastic ethnic tracks- from French folk to Middle Eastern disco, many vibes are touched in this exotic volume. Vivid, chanting voices, earthy world-beat rhythms and effervescent melodies on the rich volume- check "Les Enfants Naif" for a scenic French cafe soundtrack, "Dance For The Dead King" is an atmospheric and enigmatic piece featuring whispered female voices and an organic hand drum rhythm weaving a spooky, sublime piece. The bouncy disco of "Desert Dream" is accented by dual vocalists chanting- weaving a heartwarming melody over the fun dance beat. In search of modern sounding world-beat tracks for your project? Please click the link above to fill your prescription!

volumes.title: Country Vol 3
volumes.desc: Rural sensibility returns to the library with Country Vol 3, but these multi-genre fused acoustic folk ballads also tell tales from other lands. "In Her Arms" is a Spanish inflected love song, with a lightly cascaded guitar melody and a sensual bass line imbued with an accordion on harmony. And the suggestive "Off To Bed" is a diluted acoustic guitar night cap, with maracas flickering like candlelight and claves ticking like rain on the windowsill. Brimming with idyllic sincerity and hummable folk melodies, this collection adds humble honesty to any pastoral setting. Hear more of Country Vol 3 by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Country Vol 4
volumes.desc: Angel Perez's masterful comprehension of bluegrass is showcased here on Country Vol 4,  featuring rambling roots music of the best kind. "Tell It To The Banjo" is a weathered, all-knowing backwoods banjo hymn, dark in spirit but still with a sense of humor. The bubbly "Cool Your Strings" sets a dusky tone with warm fingerpickng and twinkling harmonics for a barefoot jig in a dewy evening. This collection, powerfully steeped in tradition, is truly country to the core. Check out more by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Country Vol 5
volumes.desc: The composers on Country Vol 5, all new to FPM, remember that country music is about tradition, yet still are open to modern conventions. "Where She Takes Me" is heavily contemporary but vaguely reminiscent of the Bakersfield sound, swaggering with confidence in rhythm and melody. And the classically structured "Heart In Deep Freeze" is a throwback to the new traditionalist movement of the 1980s, based on a beautifully articulated acoustic guitar and reverbed keyboards. This is a modern country collection without the gloss that tips its hat to the past. Check out more by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Action And Mystery Vol 1
volumes.desc: Excellent composer Hal Goldstein is back with this intriguing and dynamic new volume, Action And Mystery Vol 1, replete with white-knucke rhythms and and cinematic atmospheres this volume will provide brilliant backdrops for your scenes. Check out the driving and suspenseful "Bodies Of Evidence" for a thrilling soundtrack, "Final Transgression" is a chilling, menacing dirge, with piano and percussion weaving a terrorizing soundscape. Action And Mystery Vol 1 brings you cinematic sounds full of dynamic thrills and chills.

volumes.title: Jazz And The City Vol 2
volumes.desc: Rick DellaRatta returns with the sparkly Jazz And The City Vol 2, perfect for the holiday season. With slow, moody tracks like "Cinnamon And Mistletoe" you are guaranteed classy jazz fusions that are soothing to the ears and calming to the soul. And you can't help but roll back the rug for snappy, up-tempo numbers like "Through The Frosted Pines." These non-traditional progressions are great for any family gathering and for embracing the holiday spirit. Check out the clips by clicking on the link above.

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 6
volumes.desc: World Chill Vol 6 is an eclectic collection of mixed ethnic music with a kaleidoscope of different moods and instrumentation. The smooth and sexy "Under Burning Fire" includes suductive female vocals, while the nightmarish "Something In The Water" exudes feelings of gloom. This volume will transport you to far off places and set many different tones and moods. Click the link above to hear more!

volumes.title: World Chill Vol 7
volumes.desc: Traditional Arabian rhythms and dances blend with trance and techno beats on World Chill Vol 7, now on FPM. "Dance Of Devotion" is bewitching and seductive, and is also a duet of chants with transfixing male and female vocals. Banging and clanging with industrial rhythms, "India Undercurrent" is laden with sneering synth and woodwinds, and bustles like the streets of Bombay. Take a trip to the East without leaving home, and listen to the rest of World Chill Vol 7, by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Frequency Orch. Tchaikovsky Symphony 6
volumes.desc: This masterpiece of Romantic era composition by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky is packed with the graceful melodies and lush harmonic movement that Tchaikovsky is known for.  Tchaikovsky's 6th Symphony paints a vivid soundscape that brings the listener on an intense emotional journey.  The Frequency Orchestra's recording of Tchaikovsky's Symphony 6 is one of the composer's finest works, so click the link above to enjoy this masterful composition!

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Vol 3
volumes.desc: In the bleak mid-winter, Eclectic Beats Vol 3 arrives just in time to help listeners escape to other worlds, adorned with the collection's silken ambience and lacy electronica. The welcoming piano on "Something Next Door" provide a lovely melody that puts you in a quiet and peaceful state of nirvana. "Nectar" is a very sensual piece that puts your mind in a warm place, thanks to light and smooth electronic drums and faint melodies. The consummate backdrop for scenes thematically fraught with spiritual escapism, hear more of Eclectic Beats Vol 3 by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 6
volumes.desc: There is nothing like ringing electric guitars and classic rock rhythms to inspire and empower you, and Rock Grooves Vol 6 is chock full of enough driving melodies and booming percussion to lift anyone to the clouds. "Hope Glimmers" has the kind of build of that evokes the feeling one after accomplishing something important and special. Crisp acoustic guitars are corrupted with a dirty electric on "Past Always Present" and there is fervor in each note. For zen that is plugged in and bad to the bone, click the link above to sample more of Rock Grooves Vol 6.

volumes.title: Instrumental Visions Vol 2
volumes.desc: The sparse and darkly beautiful string arrangements on Instrumental Visions Vol 2 are exercises in raw, dissonant modernism that conjure the coarsest memories and bleakest feelings. "Burn Into Memory" is the glowering centerpiece, a two-part epic where a haunted cello, woefully draped over terse piano and cold synth, sobs a tragic melody. The grousing "Lonely At The Top" evokes the misery of ennui, finishing with a frenetic twitch of suspense. Despite the minimalist scheme, this collection summons an abundance of rapturing emotion. Hear more of Instrumental Visions Vol 2 by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Latin Fusion Vol 1
volumes.desc: Now introducing a new series, Latin Fusion Vol 1 sails the globe, speaking the foremost Romance language: music. The exotic duetting guitars on "Safe With Tradition" provide superb, uniquely edgy harmonies. "Pay Your Respects" is much slower and more tranquil, with beautifully articulated steel strings and subtle percussion. A collection that adds stirring depth to intimate lucidity, click on the link above to hear more from Latin Fusion Vol 1.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 8
volumes.desc: Just try escaping the dirty riffs and earworm choruses on Rocked Up Vol 8, a smorgasbord of rock 'n roll spanning blues, grunge and death metal. "Middle Of July" is a bluesy, groovy treat, with grinding acoustic power chords and an altered 12-bar blues structure. And "Head Held High" is lead by the prominent thump of the kick drum, an edgy ditty that gives off the ultimate bad boy feel. Browsing this collection is like flipping through a retrospective of '90s rock, a time when all old things were made new again. Click the link above to hear more.

volumes.title: Dark Drones Vol 2
volumes.desc: FPM vet Pete Calandra returns with Dark Drones Vol 2, a whimsical, ambient and often otherworldly collection of mood music. The sweet sounds of the reverberated piano and gentle synth pads on "Leave A Light On" give the song an earthy feel. "House Mouse" is a collage of adventuresome themes and unstructured melodies, as you would expect to hear in a child's dream. Adding a quick dose of suspense, mystery or caprice to any like-minded scene, hear more of Dark Drones Vol 2 by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 7
volumes.desc: Chris Holland is back in town with Rock Grooves Vol 7, a commanding set of progressive electric strains that will leave you winded. Quick to the punch, "Ready To Launch" wastes no time getting in your face and distinguishing a series of serious riffs. "The Weak Need Not Apply" blares with edge and attitude, projecting a hard rock image that demands caution. Sure to imbue any gritty environment with an edge that is bad to the bone, hear more of Rock Grooves Vol 7 by clicking the link above!

volumes.title: Country Vol 6
volumes.desc: Tennessee meets Kentucky via Hawaii and Louisiana on Country Vol 6, Kelly Weeks' latest set of roots music that bows to tradition but remains unhinged by geography. The tangy and tempered "Crawfish Jig" is Cajun to the core, with the zest of a peaceful accordion guiding the melody. Over at "The Pineapple Shanty," the earthy call of the lap steel and the response of a lively electric guitar create a friendly conversation on this Hawaiian ditty. This collection carries you thousands of miles while staying on the front porch. Check out more of the rambling Country Vol 6 by clicking the link above!

volumes.title: Old Fashioned Comedy Vol 1
volumes.desc: If you need to work the sillies out of your system, always-versatile composer Hal Gold offers Old Fashioned Comedy Vol 1, a jazzy, brassy guffaw machine that proves the Greatest Generation knew how to have the most fun. The bossa shuffle "Poolside Cooler" vividly conjures visions of beach full of striped bathing suits, finely coifed hairdos and large-rimmed sunglasses. And "Clever Little Gent" is a gawky vaudeville waltz led by the piano and an unwavering sense of grace. Sure to add a twinkle in the eye of any scene of yesteryear, sample more of Old Fashioned Comedy Vol 1 by clicking the link above!

Latin Fusion Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Composer Simon Brewer (see also: Digital Dreaming Vol 3, Promos Vol 3) pairs delicate acoustic guitar melodies with subtle percussion and synths to weave sparkling and emotive world-music flavored tracks for Latin Fusion Vol 2,
"Secret Romance" features bluesy acoustic riffing over a subtle percussion bed, smoldering with a secret and unnamed fever. "Sorry To Part" is a winsome track with a sparkling and heartfelt melody, bittersweet and introspective, with just the right amount of sun poking through the sad clouds. Simon's gentle playing and the subtle rhythmic accents make for a rich and warm set of tracks, perfect for fleshing emotive tones out of your project or scene- please click the link above to take a listen!

volumes.title: Circus Fun Vol 2
volumes.desc: Hal Goldstein brings a comedic genius to the compositions found on Circus Fun Vol 2- form the spooky theremin on the disco-y "Funky Haunted House" to the tumbling and topsy-turvy fun of "Confounded" there are many fun tracks to pick from. Hal Goldstein's excellent musicianship and bright, fresh production deliver top notch soundtrack music perfect for adding a humorous touch to your project or scene. Click above to download or stream tracks from the delightful Circus Fun Vol 2!

Moods And Grooves Vol 8
volumes.desc:
Simon Brewer brings a mixed palate of interesting soundtrack music for Moods And Grooves Vol 8, featuring his colorful, dexterous melodies and confident rhythms and dynamics. "Exploring The Outliers" is a dramatic, battle-worn track 
with sweeping strings and a military beat that evokes a smokey scene viewed in the light of day, "Pinstriped Hero" is a retro lounge jazz track with a smooth and kitschy flow, "Dark Sea Dive" is a cinematic, haunting ambient track replete with echoing flutes and humid synth pads. Moods And Grooves Vol 8's excellent sound and emotive dynamics make the tracks pop, providing luminous and dramatic music for your scenes and projects, please click the link above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 3
volumes.desc:
Composer Simon Brewer's introspective and theatrical melodies shine on Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 3, featuring euphonious flute lines, subtilely plucked acoustic guitars, dramatic piano and hazy, golden-hued synth atmospheres to weave beautiful and illuminating tracks. "Cardiff Docks" plucked acoustic strings build a sublime rhythm for an emotive flute melody as swirling synth pads create a humid, scenic backdrop. "Behind The Picket Fences" evokes a peaceful harmonious scene, that floats with a golden timelessness- really enthralling!
Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 3 is a great set of tracks that will flesh out the beauty of your scene or project without domineering the visiual flow.

volumes.title: Organ Hymns Vol 1
volumes.desc: Prolific composer Hal Goldstein (Old Fashioned Comedy Vol 1, Circus Fun Vol 2, Action And Mystery Vol 1, Promos Vols 5 and 6) brings his masterful soundtrack skills to Organ Hymns Vol 1, delivering a picturesque collection of spiritually edifying and uplifting compositions. "Morning Mass" is an illuminating and energizing piece with a rise and shine feel, "Hymn Of Temptation" is an oddly playful tune with a warm and airy feel that shows a side of the organ that you rarely hear. Organ Hyms Vol 1 is an enchanting collection of music that will add depth and resounding spiritual vibes to your project, click the link above to check it out!

Electronic Fused Vol 7
volumes.desc: DJ Mar And Dean bring you hip style and soul and back it up with slamming dance beats, Electronic Fused Vol 7 doesn't disappoint- stacked with bouncy, energetic synths, dynamic melodies, funky guitars and floor shaking beats Dj Mar And Dean can get your party started right. "Enlightenment" is a hypnotic track with a punchy kick drum beat leading the way for an in your face bass line and scary, alien synths. "Disco Rally" is a buzzing, funky track that builds and builds to a motivational, hip-shaking climax. "Dune To Dune" features some twisted, effected synths swirling over a pulsing bass line that pins powerful drums in a warped killer, headphone-candy track. Electronic Fused Vol 7 showcases Mar And Dean's production and synth skills and wraps them in fun, furious dance beats that will get the house rocking, click the link above to get your groove on!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Drama Vol 1
volumes.desc: We're pleased to introduce a new production library series, and even more so, a new FPM composer. Jason Livesay takes his Freeplay bow with "Soundtrack Drama Vol 1," a darkly beautiful and impeccably orchestrated set of theatrical themes. "Cul De Sac Tale" is a knowing and resonant piano piece, backed with chipper beats that glimmer like sunlight after a torrential rainstorm. A hollow sense of disconnection prevails over "Cruel Removal," with a shallow grave of synth at one end and soulful and airy piano at the other. Essential for scenes tackling matters of the heart and home, hear more of "Soundtrack Drama Vol 1" by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: - The Master Classics: Vivaldi The Four Seasons (Feat Vlcek)
Soundtrack Comedy Vol 1
volumes.desc: Jason Livesay's second orchestral collection in the Soundtrack series, Comedy Vol 1, is certainly lighthearted and at times silly, but always sophisticated and grand. "Monday Too Soon" is a slow building pep theme that stumbles into grace on a mixed breakfast of steel guitar, piano, vibraphone, and clarinet. And "Sky Fits Dream" is a lilting symphony, with twirling woodwinds, cascading strings, and a spirit of mannerly triumph. Click the link above to sample more of this classy treat that will only heighten your good humor.

volumes.title: - The Master Classics: Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595

- The Master Classics: Chopin Concerto for Piano and Orchestra 1 in E Minor Opus 11
World Mix Vol 9
volumes.desc:
Simon Brewer brings his dramatic and intuitive composing skills to World Mix Vol 9, with dynamic results, evoking exotic moods and weaving cinematic atmospheres this collection breathes with a worldly air and burns with an aggressive pulse- bringing you something a little different than the norm. 
"Inside The Hanamachi" weaves a gong sample into a dynamic rhythm as synth pads and floating strings provide a scintillating melody. "Temptation Is Ancient" 
features humid synth atmospheres as a strange synth and sparkling chimes build an otherworldly melody, "Sunrise On The Yangtze" is a stunning piece featuring kyoto and piano weaving a warm and shining melody evoking a colorful and romantic sunrise. World Mix Vol 9 brings you bright, punchy and dramatic world tracks that will add a distinctive edge to your project or scene.

volumes.title: - The Master Classics: Tchaikovsky Concerto for Piano and Orchestra 1 Opus 23
Soundtrack Suspense Vol 1
volumes.desc: On Soundtrack Suspense Vol 1, Jason Livesay blends tantalizing, trippy glitches and beats with stirring orchestral composititions, and then strikes with startling brass swells and booming percussion. A trilled piano quivers with a flourish on "Black Widow," then pulsing synth pads and throbbing bass strings creep up to a panic. And "Absent Presence," though understated, features eerily sneaky string plucks, chilling trills, and soughing clarinet. This collection will raise the fear factor in your suspense scene to mach ten. Click the link above if you dare.

volumes.title: New Orleans Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Composer Hal Goldstein brings spicy, upbeat Cajun and Southern blues together on New Orleans Vol 1, creating a tasty gumbo of dancing tracks, brimming with 
joy and eager fun. "All You Can Eat" features dueling accordions weaving a sunny, motivational melody as a happy snare adds the classic Cajun stomping backbeat. "Salt Water Waltz" is a charming number with a natural and loving melody, the easy sway of the beat brings good times and sunny days to mind.
"Strut Strut Strut" is a southern blues with a full horn section adding punchy hits and a warm soulful hammond adding it's melodious feel. This tight collection is produced beautifully- clean, clear and organic- full of style and soul, please click the link above to join the party, it's already in full swing!

volumes.title: - The Master Classics: Vivaldi Concerto In A Minor
- The Master Classics: Vivaldi Concerto In G Minor

- The Master Classics: Saint-SaIns Carnival Of The Animals
Electronic Fused Vol 8
volumes.desc:
Dj Mar and Dean bring a sophisticated European groove to their newest volume, Electronic Fused Vol 8, featuring subtle grooves and sublime atmospheres, this collection is easy on the ears yet full of catchy dynamics and textures. 
"Lights Go Down" is an atmospheric track with a warm vibe and a floating, inviting feel. "By The Book's" euro glide is accented by syncopated rhymic elements adding a fun, dancable groove to the bright and upbeat melodies.
"On Five's" slamming techno groove evokes a fashion runway at full tilt, while 
alien synths weave a fun, fractured melody. Electronic Fused Vol 8 shining and crystaline grooves will add refined and sublime grooves to your project or scene, please click the link above to check it out!

 Feb. 27, 2009 -
Soundtrack Action Vol 1
volumes.desc: There are thrills at every turn on Jason Livesay's latest FPM production release, Soundtrack Action Vol 1, but as always, there is also orchestral beauty all throughout. "Assembling Revolt" is a turbulent rocket of string and horn stings with percussive shrapnel, yet gilded with alluring piano. And the stately "Executive Power" begins tenderly with a soft string bed and clever clarinet, then takes flight on a brass sting and deep, punchy drums. No matter how charged or even volatile this collection becomes, it never loses its steadfast posture. Click the link above to hear more!

volumes.title: - The Master Classics: Bizet L Arlesienne Suite 1 Opus 23
- The Master Classics: Bizet L Arlesienne Suite 2 Opus 23
- The Master Classics: Stravinsky The Rite Of Spring
Drama Vol 4
volumes.desc:
Composer Ben Kopec takes a dramatic turn on the dynamic and emotive Drama Vol 4,
weaving orchestral elements into his somber industrial style, delivering tightly wound, edgy instrumentation built with aggressive synths, sinister strings and dynamic drum machines topped off with eerie atmospheres and dark emotions. "Brooding In The Dark" is a suspenseful track with a ticking hi-hat keeping a menacing beat as a morbid piano pounds a sullen melody. "Deepest Recesses" Features a furious drum machine pattern and a demonic, growling bass weaving a driving rhythm as a gritty distorted guitar lays mean, chunky chords.
The dark industrial orchestral tracks found on Drama Vol 4 will add a powerful and hard edge to your scenes or projects with it's punch and aggressive attitude, click the link above to go deeper.

American Roots Vol 1
volumes.desc: Consummate multi-instrumentalist Bill Derby gets back to basics with the always-versatile Hal Gold on "American Roots Vol 1," a patchwork of classic blues, rock, country and folk. "Jungle King" is as gritty and greasy as overcooked mash, led by a sassy harmonica and crunchy electric steel. And "Harvest Moon" is a light and folky lullaby which, with help from the lucid accordion, will arouse dreams of far off places. The no-nonsense craftsmanship in this collection could keep anyone honest. It is a bona fide summation of the steel string-based music that influenced many of the sounds of the 20th century and today. Click the link above to sample more.

volumes.title: Sports Themes Vol 2
volumes.desc:
New composer Emil Karol brings his excellent production skills and an ear for broadcast sports music to Sports Themes Vol 2, a powerful yet grooving collection of tracks with impact as well as style- "By The Bootstraps" features a lovely phased guitar, ringing and spatial, over a propulsive rhythm and a resonating bass line. A touch of country can be heard in the rocking guitar of "Love Of The Game" as it rips over a motivational, swinging rhythm section.
"In The Rink's" bluesy, dirty guitars are bolstered by slamming drums and a fat bass line pegging the beat. These solid rock tracks will add punch and energy to your sports scenes with their flavorful melodies and dynamic rhythms- click the link above to rock out!

"Sunset Harbor" is a charming, atmospheric track with a warm and gentle melody, evoking the sunlight glinting off calm waves. This uplifting collection of tracks will bring warmth and dulcet tones to your project or scene, please click the link above to take a listen.

Soundtrack Drama Vol 2
volumes.desc: Jason Livesay's second Drama volume in the Soundtrack series features impeccably constructed instrumentation and vast thematic breadth. The matrimonial vocal duet "Vow Of Honor" is deeply emotional and even darkly uncertain at times, but those moments are always thwarted with a flourish of confidence and grace. And the sanguine, yet resigned "Keeping Faith" is an organic orchestral functioning as both a coolant to a fretful situation and a comforting pall against the chill of uncertainty. Always sheer, cinematic and accessible, Livesay's compositions can enhance the aesthetic dimensions and augment the distinction of the most moving scenes. Click the link above to hear more from Soundtrack Drama Vol 2.

volumes.title: Spanish Guitar Vol 2
volumes.desc:
Composers Shan Patrick Kenner and Joel Chassan bring a unique and lovely style on their Freeplay debut: Spanish Guitar Vol 2, bold and jazzy acoustic guitar weaves colorful samba melodies as the percussionist plays engaging, syncopated rhythms on a cajon (a large block of wood played by hands) together creating breezy and sultry tracks with a fresh and different sound. "Catch You's" tumbling rhythms and eager fingerpicking bring an excited push to the moody samba, it's offbeat chords and loose structure bring a jazz feel to the front.
"Kaleidoscope" features a colorful guitar, weaving an enigmatic, ever shifting melody as earthy percussion keeps an organic beat, moving into the guitars space and out on it's own rhythm. The delightful tracks found on Spanish Guitar Vol 2 will add an exotic, sexy and worldly air to your project or scene, please click the link above to get a feel for this charming volume.

volumes.title: Techstep Vol 3
volumes.desc:
Composers Katy Walker and Michael Genato, (Techstep Vols 1 and 2) update and refresh their catalogue with Techstep Vol 3, an engaging and atmospheric set of electronic tracks. Featuring sultry female vocals and moody electronic backing, this collection shines with introspective and headphone friendly dynamics.
"Open Your Eyes" brings a funky, R&B; feel with it's emotional vocal while a stepping synth beat and warm, fuzzy bass add a soulful accompaniment, "Eastern Promise" is an exotic, humid track with a reggae feel in its moody melody, a sultry whispered vocal adds a spicy flavor to the mix. This colorful collection of electronic tracks will add a moody and voluptuous feel to your projects with it's fresh electronic sounds, please click the link above to check it out!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Suspense Vol 2
volumes.desc: Unlike most sequels in horror franchises, Jason Livesay's Soundtrack Suspense Vol 2 is even more blood-curdling than its forebear, with disturbingly cunning melodies and startling brass stings. On "Outbreak," ominous strings and piano crescendo and then fade out into a foreboding soundscape that ebbs and flows with volume and intensity. And "Wrongful Payback" evokes images of impending doom as creepy violins and piano meander through short but surprising accents from drums and brass. Warning: listening to this collection may result in several nights of sleeping with the lights on. Click the link above to hear more!

Electronic Fused Vol 9
volumes.desc:
DJ Mar and Dean open spring with a fresh and breezy set of tracks, brimming with bright, neon synths and percolating, hip shaking beats on Electronic Fused Vol 9. Dig the stylish tech disco of "On The Outside" an airy but driving rhythm vibrates underneath vibrant and shifting synths lines that weave an warm and happy melody. "Robotronics" features awesome filtered synths that weave and swerve across the stereo field over a popping, fresh techno beat.
The dynamic and colorful sounds on Electronic Fused Vol 9 will add a crystal
shine and a modern dance feel with it's punchy, bright production and modern, engaging sounds. The link above will take you there!

volumes.desc:
Composer Steve Kornicki's multihued and eloquent writing fuels the dramatic orchestral pieces found on Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 5, from vivid tracks accented lightly by vocal chorus, synths and electronic percussion to solo string pieces, this diverse set moves deftly through moods and feelings.
"Final Flight" features a warm and sparkling piano line that floats among a winding ribbon of ringing strings. On "Through The Stars" fluttering, echoing flutes and rising, filtered synths weave a majestic melody, floating like the birth of the night sky. Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 5 will fill your scenes with passion, energy and light, please click above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 6
volumes.desc:
New composer Steve Booke brings a marvelous temperament and engrossing, dramatic melodies to Acoustic Guitar Vol 6, featuring his excellently played and wonderfully recorded acoustic guitar. These earthy and warm tracks are accented by subtle synths and relaxed percussion elements, rounding out the sound-field and adding atmospheric touches. Check out the moody flat-picked guitar on "Into The Cloud," the pick style gives the guitar a middle eastern feel, like an oud, weaving a sultry and feverish melody- evoking nighttime on the desert plains.
"Summer Days'" acoustic guitar weaves a rhythmic and upbeat melody, while a second guitar brings bright and bluesy solos, playing sweetly with the rhythm guitar line. This delightful and engaging volume will add light but not lightweight moods to your project or scene- please click above to check it out!

"Model For Me" is a spacious and driving track that pulses with poise and determination, "Glamour Shots" features a cool, churning beat that struts with a more than healthy ego,
"Salon" features a vocoder voice repeating "You're Beautiful" over a banging beat, adding a self-obsessed sparkle to the bouncy track. If you need to practice your catwalk or add some groovy dance music to your scene, Freeplay has you covered- just click the link above!

volumes.desc:
Composers Katy Walker and Michael Genato are back with Techstep Vol 4, bringing you more fresh, driving and dynamic electronic tracks from the Brooklyn streets!
"Funky Chicken" is a driving dance funk with horns adding a Philly soul feel over a driving handclap beat, "Flickering" is a spaced out disco that features some twisted synths and samples that add a demented feel to the percolating groove, "Benchmark" is a moody electronic track with dark piano and a clipped violin sample together weaving a funky, rainy day track. Techstep Vol 4's vivid, dynamic and downright danceable tracks will add flair and style to your scene or project- please click the link above to get your groove on!

volumes.desc:
New Composer Jamahl Richardson hails from Brooklyn NY and you can hear some of that no-nosense city in the hard hitting tracks on Hip Hop Fused Vol 9, punchy and streetwise rhythms beat under gritty samples, earthy keys and funky, full figured bass lines. The majority of the tracks are instrumental- with dynamic melodies and tuff beats- check out the headphone magic on "Ricochet" featuring a funky guitar sample weaving a mesmerizing melody over an aggressive drum machine, octave changes keep the track fresh and provide a building tension, 
"Spirit Dance" is a relaxed dub track with reverberating rhythms and a smokey wah-wah guitar laying trippy, spaced out riffs. The gritty vocals on "Look In The Mirror" deepen the tense and cutting music with a powerful anti-gun message, while the summery, soulful "All The Way" speaks about love and changes that happen over time. The dynamic and serious tracks on Hip Hop Fused Vol 9 will provide you with street smart and gritty music to add edge and power to your scene or project. Hit the link and turn it up!

Soundtrack Action Vol 2
volumes.desc: Jason Livesay tells many tales of mystery, adventure and suspense on Soundtrack Action Vol 2, filled with frantically driving percussion, unnerving string themes, and chilling brass stings. A dystopian spirit pervades "Holy War," where a battle of synth and brass breaks an ominously stagnant string and woodwind arrangement, fought over a desolate landscape while a ghostly choir cries out. And on "Hunted," intense synth rhythms and terse strings sail above a dark piano underbelly, weaving a classic spy theme, but not of the farcical variety. Merciless thrills abound in this collection!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Action Vol 3
volumes.desc: The flourishing Soundtrack series is a smorgasbord of impeccably constructed and classically cinematic orchestrations, and on Action Vol 3, primary composer Jason Livesay puts listeners directly in the line of fire with bountiful percussive thrills and stirring string themes. Time is running out on "Prepare For Battle," ticking with dread and interspersed with brass stings, before eerily diffusing. And on "The Chase," a swarm of strings and synth are on the hunt and out for flesh, but it's a clean game game nonetheless, with pleasing tonality and impeccable texture. Check out more by clicking the link above ... and be on alert!

"Moon Dance" features a romantic and enthralling melody, passionately played by acoustic guitar, whirling percussion joins with talking drum and doumbek, the guitar plays fiery leads as the intense percussion rolls onwards. On "Across The Caucasus" phased double-tracked guitar and oud weave a romantic Eastern flavored track, as a passionate rhythm is played by doumbek, delivering an exotic and mesmerizing song. These delightful progressive tracks will provide colorful backdrops for your scene or project, please click above to get in a jazz mood.

And "Ride Across the Caucasus" is a stirring and melodic folk ballad, dramatically articulated on the acoustic guitar and driven by tribal hand percussion. No frills or gimmicks here, just pure, rootsy artistry. Click the link above to sample more.

"Turn The Volume Up" is an alt-rock rave up with a happy, carefree attitude, "Tape Delay" is a strange, tension building track featuring hypnotic, echoing guitar lines, the aforementioned "Unexploded Bomb" is an epic, sweeping track with layered guitars weaving a mystical and cinematic melody. This is a delightful collection of music that is a little left of center, with it's fresh and youthful sounds it will add something surprising to your day, your project or your scene, please click the link above to check it out!

And on "Imaginarium," all the world comes to a pause, and like a slow, shocking revelation, whirls into a light and dizzying trance before yielding to reality. Ideal for difficult scenes with elements of surrealism and morbidity, click the link above to sample more from Soundtrack Drama Vol 4.

The echoing clang of a metallic door opens "Danger Keep Out", as keening strings and backwards piano weave a frightening, encroaching atmosphere. "Rapscallion" is an intriguing atmospheric track, synth pads and cymbals build an alien, floating atmosphere that is interrupted by jarring, edgy guitar noises. "No Time To Lose" is an intense track based on a heartbeat rhythm- over the spooky thump, pizzicato strings weave a worried melody as piano, drum machine and synths add tense accents. A warm piano plays the leads as an easy-stepping rhythm section coyly keeps time. Hal's smooth and respectful arrangements bring out the soul of the song while adding fun and upbeat flavors to update the classic melodies. Please click the link above to sample these fun tracks!
