The Master Classics: Herbert MacDonough Babes In Toyland
The Master Classics: Mercadante Concerto For Flute And Orchestra In E Minor (VDP)
The Master Classics: Herbert Young Naughty Marietta
The Master Classics: Lehar-Sachs-Mandel The Merry Widow
Evil Intentions Vol 8
volumes.desc: This collection of gritty electronic tracks is moody and dark, but filled with smooth grooves.  Hard-hitting, streetwise drums drive these tracks as eerie synths and soaring electric guitars drift in and out, creating ominous moods.  Evil Intentions Vol 8 will no doubt supply you with a mysterious mood, so listen up.

volumes.title: Sports Extreme Vol 7
volumes.desc: If you like to live on the edge, then this collection of hard-rocking tracks will be the perfect compliment to your extreme lifestyle.  The drums hit hard and fast as the bass keeps pace, all while the guitars riff with furious energy.  You'll feel like you're jumping out of a helicopter with your board onto a snowy mountain top once you hear Sports Extreme Vol 7!!!

volumes.title: Sports Extreme Vol 6
volumes.desc: Have you ever surfed a 20-foot wave or gone base-jumping off a skyscraper?  If you haven't then this volume of hard-hitting rock songs will give you an idea of the adrenaline rush you'll experience.  Distorted guitars lead the way with ferocious riffs as the rhythm section drives forward with propulsive authority.  Check out Sports Extreme Vol 6 if you want to know what it's like to live life to the limit!

volumes.title: Sports Extreme Vol 5
volumes.desc: Get ready to get your socks rocked off!  This collection of heavy, hard-driving rock tunes is filled with crunchy guitars, rib-shaking bass lines and punishing drums.  Thes tracks are taken to the next level by the inclusion of spaced-out synth interludes that build tension with subtlety in these otherwise straight-up rockers.  If you're looking for intense and aggressive hard rock, then look no further than Sports Extreme Vol 5.

volumes.title: Rocked Up Vol 9
volumes.desc: I hope you're ready to rock!  This collection of rib-shaking rock songs has powerful riffs, thunderous drums and propulsive bass lines.  You can almost hear the evil laughter of the Rock gods as they look down from their castle of bones in the sky.  Rocked Up Vol 9 does not mess around, and neither should you, so listen up.... if you're ready to be rocked!

volumes.title: Hot Guitar Rock Vol 5
volumes.desc: If you're like me and you love the sound of an electric guitar, then you will surely get your fill in this collection of guitar-driven rock songs.  The riffs are funky and heavy as the bass and drums provide an interesting rhythmic drive.  These tracks are so hot you'll need oven mits for your ears!!!  But seriously, these tracks rock, so check out Hot Guitar Rock Vol 5!

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 10
volumes.desc: Get ready to kick things into overdrive!  This collection of edgy rock songs is led by distorted guitars that play paint-peeling riffs.  The rhythm section is heavy and propulsive, and subtle synths add contrast to the fuzzy guitars.  If you're looking for hard-driving rock tunes, look no further than Electro-Rock Overdrive Vol 10.

volumes.title: Dark Drones Vol 3
volumes.desc: Spooky synths swell with spine-chilling intensity in this collection of ambient tracks.  Dark and foreboding sounds drift in and out, creating a feeling of impending doom.  The sounds of creaking doors, laughing ghosts and evil winds swirl around with mysterious intent.  Dark Drones Vol 3 will have you sleeping with the light on, so check it out.... if you dare!

volumes.title: World Symphonic Vol 4
volumes.desc: You'll be instantly transported to an exotic, far-away land, full of romance and adventure, once you listen to this exciting volume.  Passionate guitars take the lead throughout as propulsive percussion and understated orchestral accompaniment assist in creating lush textures.  World Symphonic Vol 4 is not to be missed, so be sure to listen up.

volumes.title: Jazz And The City Vol 3
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Doug Munro makes his debut with this stunning volume of eclectic, modern jazz tunes.  Utilizing a guitar, organ, drums trio, the group hearkens back to the great organ trios of the 60s, but with a taste for modern sounds.  The improvisations are abundant and creative, with a solid sense of swing and an adventurous melodic drive.  Listen to Jazz And The City Vol 3 and you just might become as hip as these great tunes.

volumes.title: Moods And Grooves Vol 13
volumes.desc: This exciting collection of energetic tunes is remarkably eclectic.  "Dirty Dog" has the wide-open feel of the southwestern desert, "Favorite Weapon" is a nice piece of crunchy and aggressive electronica, and "You Got It" is straight-ahead pop/rock with an uplifting melody.  If you're not sure what you're in the mood for, but you want it to be engaging and original, then look no further than Moods And Grooves Vol 13.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Drama Vol 11
volumes.desc: Unique and creative, this collection of klezmer-inspired orchestral tracks is full of life and emotion.  From bright and cheerful to dark and mysterious, the tracks within this volume cover a wide range of moods.  Passionate violins lead the way throughout, but accordion and clarinet also share melodic duties.  If you're looking for something a little different to build an atmosphere, then be sure to listen to Soundtrack Drama Vol 11.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 7
volumes.desc: Dense and hazy soundscapes build and fade away in this remarkably creative collection of ambient electronica.  Effected guitars, warm analog synths and atmospheric noises create lush textures as eclectic percussion provides the pulse.  Ambient Figures Vol 7 is an excellent collection of electronic music that will amaze you with its creative power.

volumes.title: The Master Classics: Mendelssohn 3 Preludes Opus 104
The Master Classics: Pleyel Sinfonia Concertane For Violin, Cello And Strings In D Major
The Master Classics: Giuliani Serenade Opus 127
Ambient Figures Vol 8
volumes.desc: Eclectic, atmospheric soundscapes fill this exciting new volume.  Synths dominate the sonic landscape as images of subterranean caverns and barren landscapes are conjured up by the densely orchestrated arrangements.  Be sure not to miss out on Ambient Figures Volume 8!

volumes.title: Spanish Guitar Vol 3
volumes.desc: Spanish Guitar Volume 3, The debut album from composer Akihiro Yamamoto, is a thrilling display of guitar skill.  Flamenco stylings abound as romantic guitar melodies wind through the subtle growl of the rhythm guitars.  If you're a fan of guitar music, or are looking to lend a Spanish mood to your project, then you should check out Spanish Guitar Volume 3.  You will not be disappointed.

volumes.title: Electronic Fused Vol 11
volumes.desc: DJ Mar and Dean's latest release, Electronic Fused Volume 11, is an excellent collection of edgy electronica.  Warm analog drum machines find their foil in ice-cold synthesizers as these tracks pound and slide their way across the dance-floor.  With stylistic variations that go from Acid House to Hardcore Techno, Electronic Fused Volume 11 is sure to satisfy your need for exciting electronic music.

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 8
volumes.desc: Talented and versatile Freeplay composer Niklas Aman is back with Dramatic Soundscapes Volume 8.  These tracks are subtle in their execution but with memorable melodies and lushly orchestrated backing.  Warm synths, poignant pianos and crisp guitars work together to create soundworlds that work with a variety of projects, so be sure not to miss out on Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 8.

volumes.title: Alternative Rock Vol 6
volumes.desc: If you're looking for something that rocks to the beat of a different drummer, then look no further.  Alternative Rock Volume 6 features excellent musical interplay between guitars, synthesizers, and a whole lot more.  "Funky Coffee Shop" employs a chilled-out groove complete with some tasty horns, "Simply Smile" is a propulsive rocker with a driving beat, and "Tranquil Trance" is moody and understated.  With so much variety and talent, Alternative Rock Volume 6 is a real winner.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 9
volumes.desc: This collection of synth-heavy electronica contains a myriad of moods as well as some memorable melodies.  Warm synthesizers and percolating drum machines lead the way throughout as intricate soundscapes unfold.  "Stay Calm" is straight up ambient as washes of synth sounds build, "Ants Are Creeping" has a sophisticated electronic groove and a dark and dirty drum beat, and these are just two examples of the variety of music to be found herein.  Check out Ambient Figures Volume 9!

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 9
volumes.desc: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 9, the latest collection from composer Niklas Aman, is a varied and thought-provoking set of atmospheric instrumental music.  A wide range of textures and moods are conjured up by a variety of instruments, but synthesizers and guitars carry most of the tracks.  These tracks are filled with drama and emotion, so if you're looking to add a special atmosphere to your project, then be sure to listen to Dramatic Soundscape Volume 9.

volumes.title: Dark Dimensions Vol 10
volumes.desc: Subtle, synth-heavy tracks are to be found here in Dark Dimensions Volume 10.  Moaning synthesizers wind around, often backwards, making a menacing mood of mystery.  Subtle electric piano, guitar and bass appear, giving an organic feel to these atmospheric tunes.  If your project requires some quality ambient music, then be sure to check out Dark Dimensions Volume 10.

volumes.title: Alternative Rock Vol 7
volumes.desc: Get ready to for some smart and fun rock music!  Alternative Rock Volume 7 is eclectic and interesting, as the grooves prove unpredictable and the instrumental interplay will keep you on your toes.  Standard guitar/bass/drums instrumentation is augmented by tasteful tenor sax, clarinet and flute, adding to the offbeat vibe.  Make sure that you listen close to Alternative Rock Volume 7 and you will be pleasantly surprised.

volumes.title: Electronic Grooves Vol 1
volumes.desc: You best get on your dancing shoes and hit the club after you check out Electronic Grooves Vol 1.  Drum machines and synths lead the way throughout as different moods and styles are explored.  "Breakfast Beat" has an exotic tinge that is accentuated by the use of tablas.  "Gotta Learn" is a good-old-fashioned dance floor neck-snapper, with some nasty synths thrown in for good measure.  This collection of eclectic and hard-hitting tracks is not to be missed, so be sure to listen to Electronic Grooves Vol 1.

volumes.title: Sports Power Vol 2
volumes.desc: A rip-roaring set of tracks from the talented composer Pete Calandra, burning, eager rock tracks featuring big, bad guitars and a thundering rhythm section. Highlights include, "Good Ride"- a nasty blues, and "Barnstormer" an unforgiving blast with all the hooks and looks.

volumes.title: Modern Rock Vol 4
volumes.desc: This collection of bright pop/rock tunes is filled with soaring guitar melodies and sunny grooves.  Crunchy guitars lead the way as subtle keys offer perfect accompaniment.  The rhythm section is driving, yet not overpowering, as all of these tracks exude a feeling of optimism.  Modern Rock Volume 4 is a first-rate collection of confident and catchy songs that will have you ready to rock!

volumes.title: Electronic Grooves Vol 2
volumes.desc: You'll want to get yourself down to the discotheque after you get a listen of Electronic Groove Volume 2.  Prolific FPM composer Ernie Lake presents this collaboration with new composer Adam Katit for your listening pleasure.  These tracks will take you back to a day when dance music was all about the groove, with hard-hitting drum machines and fuzzy, sub-sonic bass lines leading the way.  Funky guitars and smooth keyboards make appearances throughout to lend an extra touch of originality and eccentricity to this collection of highly danceable tracks.  Do not miss out on Electronic Grooves Volume 2!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Action Vol 6
volumes.desc: New composer Andrew Oudot is here with his FPM debut, Soundtrack Action Volume 6!  This collection of stunning orchestral music features dense string arrangements and intense percussion as the music conjures feelings of terror, excitement and tension.  These tracks will keep you on the edge of your seat, so if your project is in need of some dramatic, tension-building music, then look no further.  Listen to Soundtrack Action Volume 6 today!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Action Vol 7
volumes.desc: FPM's latest addition to its roster of talented composers is Andrew Oudot (of Soundtrack Action Vol 6 fame) and he is here with Soundtrack Action Volume 7.  This stunning collection of dramatic orchestral tracks picks up right where the previous volume left off, with enough sweeping strings and intense percussion to create tension out of any scene.  Do yourself a favor and check out Soundtrack Action Volume 7!

volumes.title: Modern Rock Vol 5
volumes.desc: Feel good instrumental rock dominates this disc.  Catchy guitar melodies mixed with pleasant little surprises keeps these tracks bouncy and fun.  Like driving a convertible with the top down, all thats missing is the wind in your hair and an open highway.

volumes.title: Alternative Rock Volume 8
volumes.desc: Veteran Freeplay composer Joi Veer is here with a brand-new collection of excellent tunes! Alternative Rock Volume 8 is a collection of epic riffs and classic beats.  Drawing from the classic rock vocabulary and adding modern production and compositional twists, this collection is sure to get your feat tapping and your head nodding.  Check out "Sea Of Velvet," an anthem for desperado everywhere, and "Iron and Nickel" for a rockin tune with a surprising, mysterious bridge.

volumes.title: Electronic Fused Vol 12
volumes.desc: Another great, wild, mesmerizing collection from Australia's finest beat-breakers- DJ Mar N' Dean! This set features excellent, fresh synth sounds, wild, shifting rhythms and a intense, hypnotic style. These guys get better with every release, this aggressive collection will provide fantastic flavors of electronic music for your project or scene. Amazing stuff!!

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Volume 8
volumes.desc: Steve Glotzer's new volume "Acoustic Guitar Vol 8" is a delightful collection of blusey, folky tracks- featuring dobro, accordion, tuba and mandolin (along with the acoustic guitar) playing traditional tracks with anything but a traditional feel. "Coffee On The Stove" is a warm and embracing track imbued with a rich and loving spirit. "All Is Not Lost" is and uplifting track with sweet and languid melody. This sparkling, picturesque collection will add soulful and sweet sounds to your scene or project.

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 10
volumes.desc: New composer Robert Mann brings you an eclectic collection of sounds and spaces, Ambient Figures Volume 10 employs a plethora of sources, organic and inorganic to create tracks to fit any atmosphere.  "The Adventurer" gives a mysterious warmth to the void of outer space.  A more personal, emotional landscape is crafted in "Hours of Darkness," tailored for a heavy heart.  For an out of this world take, try the alien synths of "Disembark."

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Volume 4
volumes.desc: A collection of beats as diverse as they are original, Eclectic Beats Volume 4 has it all.  Composer Robert Mann has assembled many sounds and samples all with one goal in mind: Vibe.  Try "Obscure" for some outer space jazz (an unlikely sound!).  For a dubbed out horn sound, check out "Brass N Bold."  "Confined Sunlight" combines alarming synths and alien sounds to startling effect.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Suspense Volume 13
volumes.desc: New composer Robert Mann brings a diverse palate and inventive composing to his first volume for Freeplay- Soundtrack Suspense Volume 13 - will give you picturesque and atmospheric suspense tracks to bring out the edge of your scene or projects, his cunning use of synths and orchestral elements is fresh and intriguing yet organic and not overpowering. A vivid and dynamic collection.

volumes.title: Cartoon Stings Vol 1
volumes.desc: Prolific composer James Slattery is back- unlike his Dark Dimensions Volumes, this collection is quite silly and lighthearted! "Caffeine" is a blast of bass, flute and rock drums, skittering like a clown on fire. "Blinky And Tickle" is a tense tag featuring Stravinsky-esque strings popping in and out of a quick marching drum beat. This great, original and fun collection will add uproar and punch to your scene or project, please click the link to take a listen!

volumes.title: Tropical Vibes Vol 4
volumes.desc: Composer Joel Chassan is back with a delightful, rhythmic and sunny set of Latin inspired tracks for Tropical Vibes Vol 4- "Sand Snake" is a relaxed percussion track with a meditative groove, "Poolside Sunbeams" is a motivational track featuring piano and organ over percussive rhythms- the underscore version gives you the same minus the organ leads. This scenic collection will flavor your project with fun, sun-stoked melodies, please click the link to take a listen!

volumes.title: Country  Volume 9
volumes.desc: Slide guitars, harmonica and a whole lot of grit kick it hard on "Country  Volume 9."  With a mix of back road blues and folk  and more modern country-rock style, this album has it all for afternoons and evenings down south.  For a classic bluegrass themed dance, try "Joyful Daze," sure to get the feet tapping and the whiskey flowing.  For a more modern sound, "Everyone In Harmony" mixes alternative rock with classic country flavor.

volumes.title: Blues Volume 5
volumes.desc: An electric blues collection to fit any dive bar, "Blues Volume 5" features a spectrum of tempos and feels in each catchy tune.  One constant in this volume is attitude, and each of these tracks brings the swagger to each bent note.  Check out "Cheerful Soul" for a midtempo shuffle quintessential of any bar room in the wrong side of town.  For a more somber, reflective take on the blues give "Mesmerize Me" a try.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 8
volumes.desc: A collection of beats replete with all the classic trappings, "Hip Hop Volume 8" brings every element to the table.  Heavy drum beats, bouncing bass lines, orchestral samples, and killer keyboard work makes every track here a winner.  Perfect for rolling up to the club and dancing all night once inside, this volume will fuel the whole night all on it's own. Try "Twist Of Courage" for a timpani drum feature and orchestral sounds.  For an R&B; angle, "Unbreakable" features solid and delicate keyboard work. "Bump To This" is a classic club track.

volumes.title: Hip Hop Vol 9
volumes.desc: "Hip Hop Volume 9" collects a diversity of beats full of deep bass and clever samples.  From southern hip hop to west coast cool, this volume combines all these elements and melds them for a unique vibe.  Try "A Small Crowd" for a dramatic and sweet chord change atop a heavy beat.  "Set It Up" features a squeaky vocal sample and gunshot snare drums.  For a creepy vibe, try "Spiraling Downward."

volumes.title: Kool Grooves Volume 1
volumes.desc: Kool Grooves Volume 1 features the hippest and most modern sounds and grooves available today.  With grooves from afro-beat, reggaeton, and hip hop there are instrumental and stylistic nods towards jazz and classical here assuring that the tunes are as deep as the pocket.  "The New Year" offers a cinematic approach with classic Hollywood style orchestration.  For a taste of Nigerian Afro-Beat, try "On Your Feet."  "The Crazy Cat" brings a slower reggae groove to the mix while keeping the energy high.  All throughout this album tasteful and thoughtful trumpet playing leads the way.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Moods Volume 2
volumes.desc: An album with lots of character, "Soundtrack Moods Volume 2" will constantly surprise without becoming esoteric.  Each track has a particular mood and emotion and accomplishes this with creative orchestration and harmony.  For a modern rock song with a melancholy vibe, try "Pillow Talk."  More on the electronic side is "Resist The Flow" taking the listener into a constant stream of motion.  For a thoughtful, inspiring ballad "Finito" fits the bill.  Also check out "Great Feelings All Around" for a surprisingly satisfying mix of keyboards, synths, and harmonica.

volumes.title: Eclectic Dance Volume 1
volumes.desc: Eclectic Dance Volume 1' is a rock solid collection of dance and electronica perfect for any club.  With a variety of drum beats from drum and bass to jungle to classic hip hop there's no filler here.  Try the middle eastern tinged 'Taking Turns' for a surprising lead line.  'Get Together' features an unconventional lead synth sound coupled with dub style piano backbeats.  For distorted bass blasting its best, try 'Electro Funk.'

volumes.title: Eclectic Dance Volume 2
volumes.desc: With enough beats to pack clubs every night of the week, 'Eclectic Dance Vol 2' grooves like no other.  Plenty of synth and heavy bass keep things pumping in this volume.  Try the classic hip hop sound of 'Dancin' Everywhere' for a retro vibe.  'Don't Hold Back' will surround the listener with intense synth sound.  'Wild Times' uses fast drums for a chase scene vibe.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Moods Volume 3
volumes.desc: A mix of synth and orchestral sounds make up this edition of "Soundtrack Moods Volume 3."  With inspired chord changes, hip rhythms, and funky bass lines this volume also adds the occasional unexpected instrument.  Try "Cirque" for a sweet violin melody played with poise over an oddmeter groove.  "A Covering" provides an ominous vibe until an accordion makes a dramatic entrance.  Earnest guitar playing gives "Follow The Path" an inspiring character for a nice change of pace.

volumes.title: Electro-Rock Overdrive Volume 11
volumes.desc: Veteran Freeplay composer Paul Andrews (Dark Dimensions Vol. 2, Electro-Rock Overdrive Vols. 1, 2 and 5) is back with this brutal set of crunchy synth-inflected rockers.  The rhythm section hits hard as the guitars grind out tough-sounding chord progressions.  If you need a little more attitude in your ears, then be sure to check out Electro-Rock Overdrive Volume 11.

volumes.title: Manhattan Producers Alliance - Elizabeth Rose Collection
Manhattan Producers Alliance - Dan Carter Collection
Manhattan Producers Alliance - Andy Gabrys Collection
Electronic Grooves Vol 3
volumes.desc: Ernie Lake and the 912 crew are back with a new slamming collection of euro-inflected dance tracks. Sophisticated, sunny and bouncy rhythms are accented by sweet synths and a smattering of sampled sounds. From motivational Latin accents to hip hoppish floor fillers this collection will make you groove! Please click the link above to check it out.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Moods Vol 1
volumes.desc: Composer Stephen Akina brings you a new collection of emotive and dramatic tracks with Soundtrack Moods Vol 1- From funk, to electronica to dramatic- manny moods are touched in this exotic set- "Whirl N Twirl" is a cute ukulele tag, "Out Of It" is a dirty funk track and "Athens In The Summer" is a relaxed easy listening tune- The superb musicianship and mix really make this collection shine, please click the link above to take a listen!

volumes.title: Manhattan Producers Alliance - Steve Horelick Collection
Manhattan Producers Alliance - Frank Ferrucci Collection
Clubtronic Vol 1
volumes.desc: New composer Barrett Yeretsian brings you some bold and bad-assed hip-hop and dance tracks on this new collection- Clubtronic Volume 1. In The Dance department do check out "Jazzy Jazz" an organic trip-hop track with an excellent laid-back style, "In The Danceclub" is a perfect blend of hip-hop and techno dance, ROCKIN'.. In the Hip-Hop department check "Hustle N Bustle" a dark and brooding track with an ax to grind, "Speak Up" is a tension building track with dark melodies. This heavy set will give glue to your street shots and dance scenes, please click above to check it out.

volumes.title: Piano Solos Vol 5
volumes.desc:
New composer Andersen Viana brings imaginative composing and some serious chops
to Piano Solos Vol 5- flowing with emotion and soul, this collection takes solo piano to a new level. "Even Under The Ser, Elizabeth Rose, Andy Gabrys and Frank Ferrucci.  There are many more volumes of truly excellent music to come, so check back often and listen thoroughly!

volumes.title: Piano Solos Volume 6
volumes.desc:
Andersen Viana's second collection of piano solos, vol 6 (and Piano Solos Vol 5) show both his compositional talents as well as his serious chops, On "Greater Escape" a joyous melody feels improvisational, trundling and wheeling- at times regal and proud, at others just plain happy. Both modern and vintage as the melody flows, pointed yet easy- wonderfully contradictory and endlessly entertaining. The wonderfully emotive "To My Knees" brings a sad, but ultimately positive note. Calm in it's sorrow, the piece carries on with resolution and courage.
"Backstage Samba" is a discordant track that moves with a jazzy, bemused pulse- the resolve is always a chord away - pointed notes lead to the next in a tumble of melody. This refreshing collection of solos will add character and depth to your picture or project, click it to hear it!

volumes.title: Ethereal Movements Vol 2
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Louise Smart presents Ethereal Movements Volume 2: the perfect blend of 20th century classical music, modern world music and noise. The composer's use of exotic samples, such as the bathroom sound found in Inner Beauty and the chirping birds of Amber, are really the foundation of this album. Most songs begin with quiet effects and build, shaping the tunes, creating an eerie, or ethereal, atmosphere. Her orchestral writing is beautiful, while equally as frightening.  Be sure to check out Ethereal Movements Vol 2 for a unique and engaging musical experience.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 4
volumes.desc: This ecclectic group of songs always remains somewhat true to the classical tradition and has strings on almost each track. Orchestral Dimensions Vol 4 also has subgenres such as carnatic, klezmer, folklore, etc., that take it out of the realm of traditional classical music. These tracks are primarily on the shorter side but range in style, feeling and mood.

volumes.title: DJ Sets Volume 1
volumes.desc:
The venerable DJ Mar N Dean present this mind-blowing set of floor-pounding and face-melting electronica.  Time seems to slip away as the surging synths and thunderous drums twist and turn.  The thematic unity of each set is remarkable as every layer of sound seems to have its purpose.  "Late Night Insomnia" will transport you directly to the dance floor as
 August 5, 2010 - Orchestral Dimensions Vol 4 
This ecclectic group of songs always remains somewhat true to the classical tradition and has strings on almost each track. Orchestral Dimensions Vol 4 also has subgenres such as carnatic, klezmer, folklore, etc., that take it out of the realm of traditional classical music. These tracks are primarily on the shorter side but range in style, feeling and mood.

volumes.title: Video Game Music Vol 1
volumes.desc: Video Game Music Volume 1 is a delightful set from new composer Sergei Stern. Completely 8bit fun, the sounds and rhythms could have come from your favorite video game, I laughed out loud as I tried to describe the tracks- really a blast! "Land We Love" is a sunny calypso track, "Chicago Blues" is a keystone kops style song, there are plenty of styles reflected in 8bit on this collection- Find one that works for you by clicking the link above- and have fun!

volumes.title: Alternative Rock Vol 9
volumes.desc:
New composer Daniel Dombrowsky pulls out the stops for Alternative Rock Vol 9-
absolutely bombastic tracks featuring huge guitars, guttural bass and speaker shredding drums. These mostly mid-tempo dirges veer from alternative to grunge to full on metal attacks. The resounding mix really leaps out and makes these tracks stick in your craw. "Bottles And Chains" is a strutting burner that takes no prisoners, "Get Serious" is an evil, neck-breaking dirge that will wipe your hard drive and shatter all the windows, neat! Please click the link above to do a little Friday shredding, courtesy of Freeplay Music!

volumes.title: Percussion Vol 2
volumes.desc: Prolific composer Joel Chassan is back with an eclectic collection of rhythm tracks on Percussion Vol 2. These dynamic tracks pulse and push with a earthy collection of instruments: congas, hand-drums, cowbell and more- providing urgent and organic beats to drive your scene or project; "Crashing Waves" is a busy track that brings to mind bees and ants building their hives. "Greenhouse" is a dreamy track that is perfect for a Sunday afternoon. "The Search" is a dynamic reconstructed funk featuring organs and a careening arrhythmic vibe. This fun, motivational volume will get your head and hips swinging with its upbeat ways- please click above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Eclectic Dance Vol 3
volumes.desc: NYC composers Grady Walker and Ann Marie Sargolini are back with another dance floor banger: Eclectic Dance Vol 3, this collection brings you upbeat and motivational pop tracks from the bleeding edge. Great synth sounds, big beats and a feel good vibe combine to deliver some catchy, hook filled songs: "Domination" is industrial dance featuring big, spooky drum lines, "Round Of Applause" is a hip hop track with bouncy beats and buttery synths, "Sweet Fantasy" is dreamy electronica with a lovely synth melody. The dynamic beats on Eclectic Dance Vol 3 will get you moving, the hooky synths will keep you coming back for more. Hit the link above to get a taste!

volumes.title: Funk Grooves Vol 2
volumes.desc: New composer Dave Lionelli serves up a heapping platter O' funk on Funk Grooves Vol 2- 10 slamming tracks that really tear the roof off! Excellent production, excellent musicianship and a bunch of players obviously having a blast, make this set really primo! "Hidden Guilt" features styling clav leads over a hefty rhythm section, "Carefree Living" brings fantastic leads from piano, organ and synth- all working together to deliver you the best possible funk available. "Put Up Your Claws" could be the theme to an awesome detective show, featuring a jacked up camaro and giant platform shoes. This is a delightful set, and these action packed tracks will add soul, substance and fun to your project or scene.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 5
volumes.desc: Prolific composer Stephen Akina is back with an new orchestral set, "Orchestral Dimensions Volume 5". A diverse collection of cinematic tracks featuring orchestral instrumentation, embellished by synths and modern styles- "Charge" is a bold and barreling track with horns blowing full bore- like an out of control fire engine. "The Sting" is an evil track that starts out spooky and gets even spookier, "Betwixt & Between" is a fun, lounge track featuring plucked strings and a busy feel- perfect for power shopping in the 1950's. There is a track just for you on this delightful, dynamic and interesting volume, please click the link to check it out!

volumes.title: Manhattan Producers Alliance: D.D. Jackson Collection
Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 6
volumes.desc:
Composer Eric Bolvin's Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 6 is an delightful collection of vivid orchestral tracks spiked with modern touches such as guitar and drums, or just in the tracks feel. "Industrial Espionage" is an intriguing thriller track, pulsing with excitement, "Homeland Homage" is a heartwarming track that is equal parts orchestral and Americana, and 100% uplifting.
These tracks will add a riveting and dramatic appeal to your project. Please click the link and take a listen!

volumes.title: Rock Grooves Vol 8
volumes.desc: New composer Jon Gilbert Leavitt brings fun, hooky melodies and a top-of-the-line band to Rock Grooves Volume 8, spunky R&B; inflected rock and straight up rock styles are featured here- "Fantastical" is a tuff funk track with motivational rhythms and a sweet wah-wah synth providing a thick lead. "Avenue 101" is a propulsive track perfect for highway scenes with a popping, distorted guitar clearing the path, "East Side" is a crunchy, ear-catching track made huge by the sizzling synth leads. This ambitious, dynamic and pop filled collection will add sunny motivation to your scene or project, click the link to take a listen!

volumes.title: Hot Guitar Rock Vol 6
volumes.desc: New composer Jason Moore swings the hammer down on this new collection of hot, heavy and potent tracks, Hot Guitar Rock Vol 6. Brilliant guitar work, in the pocket bass and big, big drums are key to the dynamic tracks found on this collection- The slow burner "Piece Of Me" is a weighty slab, slowly pounding down any door, "Broken Down" is an eager, gritty track, built for speed and mass destruction. Just to switch it up- "Devoid" is a thoughtful acoustic track featuring brushed drums and a relaxed feel. This colorful collection will bring hard hitting sounds to your scene- please click and listen!

volumes.title: Manhattan Producers Alliance: Rick Baitz Collection
Electronic Fused Vol 13
volumes.desc:
Prolific composers DJ Mar N Dean (who pioneered the Electrofied and Rock/Electronic Fused collections) keep growing creatively, keep bringing out great volumes and Electronic Fused Volume 13 shows them hitting the decks hard. 
"Break Out" features face-melting synths and heavy heavy drums to weave an intense and locked in the groove electronica track, The whirlwind synths and eager rhythms give "Good N Plenty" it's persistent push, surging forward with a fevered drive. "Full Of Life" shows Mar N Dean really hitting a stride in a dark and shadowy groove that stretches out it's metal synth fingers and reaches into the deep abyss.
This awesome collection hits fast and hard, pumping out the beats and dynamic synth-work like nobodies business! Please, Click above to take a listen!

volumes.title: Clubtronic Vol 2
volumes.desc: Prolific composer Barrett Yeretsian brings a huge update to the Clubtronic line with this 2nd volume, 25 tracks of slammin', club bangin' songs! This streetsmart collection hits hard with fresh sounds and big production, dig the urban sounds of "The Bravery", a colorful and hooky blast. The gritty anthem "Hi In The Sky" puts baby in a corner with all it's dope beats. Moody horns and a head nodding beat weave an insular track on "Fairy Tale" - spooky and alone. This dynamic and dance-able collection has a fit for you, please click and check it.

volumes.title: Hot Guitar Rock Vol 7
volumes.desc: New composer Jason M. Moore, brings his energetic compositions and epic style to this brash new collection of heavy duty guitar tracks. From slow and smoldering to fast and furious this hot set delivers you guitar power at all speeds, check the frenzied pace of "No Worries"- a hellish groove featuring ripping guitars. "Should Have Done It" is a mid-tempo stadium rocker with massive drums that put all other "massive drums" to shame. "Speedy" is a sol-mo burner that has an 80's feel with it's moody synth. This vibrant collection shines with it's glossy, yet sharp production and it's vital tracks will add a bombastic heft to your project or scene- please click the link and remember to buckle up!

volumes.title: Cinematic Electronic Vol 11
volumes.desc: Composer Stephen Akina brings his vivacious style and smart melody writing to Cinematic Electronic Volume 11, a colorful collection of synth based tracks that will add a cinematic pulse to your project, "Blow The Lid Off" has a sneaky, dark vibe that glides smoothly yet bubbles underneath, with it's driving bass line juxtaposed against a floating synth line. "In The Distance" features fuzzed out guitar dueling with folksy oud lines, as warped synths add distorted accents and a machine drum thumps along. "Rastafari" is a spooky atmospheric track with a darkly pulsing heartbeat and drill-like synths weaving a constricting, foreboding track. This visual collection will flesh out dramatic scenes where a robotic touch is needed. Please click the link above to check out Cinematic Electronic Volume 11.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Drama Vol 12
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Alena Liakh-Tarasava brings imagination, grace and an ear for drama to Soundtrack Drama Vol 12, dynamically juxtaposing styles and instruments to create some very fresh and evocative music, The icy "Flurry" weaves bell-like synths over a subliminal bass, the sparkling synth glimmers like dust motes caught in mid-day sunbeam as the deep bass adds an earthy touch. "In The Open" brings orchestral elements and a chorus together over a modern synth beat weaving a gentle and cinematic track that is epic yet not booming. "Karma" features  Melancholy strings aching with longing and desire. Piano and synth add subtle support to the blue melody. Soundtrack Drama Vol 12 will add dynamic and colorful moods to your scene or project, please click and check it out!

volumes.title: Modern Jazz Vol 1
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Aaron Henry brings his heart and soul to this great collection- Modern Jazz Volume 1, his impressive skills will delight your senses and help define your projects with it's mature yet spicy tracks. "Breakup" features impressive jazz drumming in the intro of this track, That only foreshadows the wild jazz guitar and upright bass solos later in the song- mad exploration while maintaining a cool, contemporary groove.  "Red Switch" begins with happy and bouncing jazz groove of an intro, leading into an uplifting horn lead melody. Guitar solos and a wild drum solo give the track a very groovy feel- leading to a sense of achievement and accomplishment. The seeming mellowness of "Shades Of Black " slowly builds to a deep groove with intricate guitar and horn solos. This exemplary collection will add vivacious and grooving feelings to your picture or scene, please click above to take a listen!

volumes.title: Dub Vol 1
volumes.desc: Excellent composer Paul Andrews (who pioneered the Dark Dimensions and Electro-Rock Overdrive volumes) brings his magic to Dub Vol 1, and excellent results are obtained! Big, wide reverbs, psycho-acoustic delays and a relaxed, laid-back vibe are comely features of these smokey dub tracks. "Bombaclat" starts things off with echoing aplomb and spacey rhythms, as a groovy organ adds a dusky melody. "Irie Time" is a super chill-out track- it's slow drums weaving a tribal beat as piano and congas add warped accents. "Journey to Jah:" takes you on an organic, slo-mo joy ride- featuring enigmatic beats and earthy piano and organ lines. This excellently produced, recorded and played collection has just what you need dub-wise- please click the link (on the left hand side) to check it out!

volumes.title: Clubtronic Vol 3
volumes.desc: Barrett Yeretsian delivers another fly set of gritty club tracks on Clubtronic Vol 3, Fine production, fresh sounds and streetsmart composition are hallmarks of Barrett's work, and the trend continues on this impactful set. "Unusual Means" features an infectious bassline, on which a shiny snare and earworm synths add a glossy and groovy layer, weaving a punchy, mid-tempo track. Exotic synths give "The Scandal" a humid hook, a huge beat with Mid-Eastern flair adds a head-nodding rhythm, "Into The Deep End" has a classic feel- upright bass and an old-school beat merged with jazz inflected horn and piano samples, together weaving a groovy, relaxed track. This collection of club bangers will get you up and get you going, please check it out by clicking the link above!

volumes.title: Brazilian Nights Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Composer, and Freeplay fave, Eric Roberts is back with a rich and charming collection of Brazilian tracks; "Latin Sunshine" is a lush, serene tune featuring a romantic flute lead, bubbling percussion and a warm outlook.
"Carnivale" features sumptuous guitars weaving a spirited samba. "Sao Paulo After Dark" is a moody and seductive track with an air of intrigue on the high seas (or a sunny beach at least) The musicianship is impeccable, the style is enchanting and the tracks breathe with a natural warmth that will add flair and joy to your day, or project. Please click above to listen to this romantic set.

volumes.title: World Acoustic Vol 1
volumes.desc: Artful composer Steve Booke's new collection, World Acoustic Vol 1, is a masterful tour of genres and styles from around the world- filtered through his melodic and dynamic acoustic guitar. "Erroneous" is a moody piece, with a raga style, enchanting percussion and a hypnotic lilt. "A Tribute To Brightness" is a fantastic, dreamy track that defies classification, a sparkling acoustic and a chanted female vocal weave a floating and romantic melody, backed by gentle percussion and angelic synths. "Divine Design" is an earthy, urgent track that falls somewhere between Irish folk, American blues and Indian raga, vibrant and spiritually awake. This is a fantastic collection, I highly recommend clicking above and checking it out!

volumes.title: Sports Themes Vol 3
volumes.desc: New composer Richard Hyland, part of the Listen Here Now production group, brings his furious rocktronic stylings to Sports Themes Vol 3. This collection brings you hard hitting tracks perfect for hi-lights and openings- "Houserocker" is exactly that: punishing metal, featuring blistering guitar work and in your face rhythms. "Crushing Afternoon" is a throbbing slab that rocks and pushes with gutsy style. "Runnin A Train" is an ominous chunk of LA rock- dirty and propulsive. This collection will add flash and smash to your project or scene, please click above to check it out!

volumes.title: Sports Themes Vol 4
volumes.desc:
Richard Hyland's second set raises the heavy bar (see "Master Of Darkness")
and adds some more electronic based tracks: The urgent "Intergalactic Planetary Noise" and the glitched madness of "Polygrip Flip Trip". These dynamic tracks really fit the sports bill- careening and raging with dynamic intensity.

volumes.title: Orchestral Dimensions Vol 6
volumes.desc: New composer Steve Chan has put together an excellent collection or original orchestral soundtrack music for "Orchestral Dimensions Vol 6", touching a variety of feelings and instrumentation: "Limited Aim" features piano and choir voices weaving a sad lament over a funeral timpani beat, "William Tell Me About It" is a joyous piece with it's merry piano and strings weaving a calm, seasonal melody, "Divine Right" is a royal march, featuring pizzicato strings, military drums and a haughty step. Steve's talents shine in his ability to write effectively for any style, plus the recording and playing are top notch. This collection will add depth and expressive style to your scene or project, click above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Sports Themes Vol 5
volumes.desc: Composer Kenny Korade, who hails from the Listen Hear Now production group, is the the composer on this short but bombastic set. Explosive drums, blistering guitars and aggressive dynamics are key features of this sports oriented collection, "Determined To Win" starts up with dirty guitar riffing, building a good tension, that comes to a head with the rapid fire slapping of the snare as the band joins in, full blown. "Ready To Rumble" features a grungy bass line and big wide drums backing an echoing slightly 80's guitar riff, excellent stadium feel, "Warp Speed" is a punky rave-up with a happy bounce and eager drive. These rocking tracks will kick your clips up a notch with vibrant and dynamic push, click above to get it.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 9
volumes.desc: Composer Sergei Stern, who put together the fantastic set "Video Game Music Vol 1", shows us more of his talent, this time on "Acoustic Guitar Vol 9". This collection shows him as a versatile writer, tackling the acoustic guitar with ease and weaving gentle, upbeat tracks. "Feathers In The Air" is a warm, organic track, hi-lighted by a jangly guitar and piano line, with rich bass and brushed drums keeping a gentle syncopation. Sleigh-bells and bouncy piano chords fuel the seasonal sounds of "Holiday Cheer" - a happy, glowing track. The slow building blues of "Lazy Bronco" sighs and stutters with cowpoke ease, -mellow rock for mellow times. The pristine recordings and tight musicianship gives this set a great feel and Sergi's melodies will hook the ear with gentle warmth, please click above to hear these fine songs.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 10
volumes.desc:
Insightful composer Steve Booke is back, this time with a charming collection of easy grooving tracks tracks on "Acoustic Guitar Vol 10". As ever, Steve's melodies and stylings make for great tracks, this set has them in spades:  The track "Spring Up" opens like a cool spring morning, with acoustic strings ringing like sunbeams and an easy beat to get the day started. "Pitch Black" is a fun track that pushes the bounds of the genre- with synths and electronic drums adding a diverse mix of tones. "Light Of Day" is an upbeat Latin flavored track with spritely guitar and percussion paving the way for excitement and adventure.
This dynamic and vivacious collection will fill key moments with key sounds. Please click above to check it out!

volumes.title: Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 7
volumes.desc: New composer Matt Campana brings to Freeplay a diverse and intriguing collection of soundtrack music featuring orchestral elements, modern instruments, and cinematic composition. "No Longer Hazy" is a lovely orchestral piece with swooping strings and flutes weaving a heavenly melody, timpani and rhythmic elements add a bit of pop structure to the piece and a lovely female vocal adds wordless accents to the swelling, ascending melody. "Early Evening" is a  vivid string and piano melody that grows and swells as flute and other orchestral elements join the swoon, conveying a feeling of warmth and safety. "Under The Moon" features xylophone and percussion, weaving  a clockwork rhythm with an odd yet endearing flair. "Brick Wall" implements orchestral elements in an ambient  good. Have a listen now by clicking the link at the top!

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 10
volumes.desc:
Composer Jon Gilbert Leavitt's second set for Freeplay (the first being: Rock Grooves Vol 8) changes gears for the cinematic and emotive "Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 10". This sparkling collection features mostly orchestral instruments and percussion, with occasional hi-lights from guitar and synth.
"Hitting The Beat" has a thriller feel, with a driving drum line accented by smoky, coiling strings and crushing sound effects. "Field Of Vision" has a motivational military feel in the punctual snares and gleaming horns- the piece soars as a winner take all theme. Guitar and piano weave a warm Americana feel on "Outer Layer" an easy groove that pauses and swells with an organic pace. The strange but intriguing mix on "Head On" takes the salsa track a step further into outer space with very interesting and arresting results. This creative collection really breaks out of the genre game and has fun with the music, and that is what makes this a great set, please click the link to check it out!

volumes.title: Ambient Figures Vol 11
volumes.desc: Composer Daniel Dombrosky's second effort (His other; the boisterous "Alternative Rock Vol 9") shows the quieter side of Daniel's colorful skills, treading a melodic line between atmospheric Ambient and the more beat-fueled Electronica, these tracks share a little of both genres, "Dim The Lights" begins with a solo guitar line and is joined by sparkling keys adding belled notes, "Dim The Lights Part Two" takes those elements and builds on them, fleshing out the track with a full band. "Broodingly Bittersweet" sees strings, synth and keys building gently over a brooding guitar line, growing and glowing. This creative set will give a mysterious and edgy feel to your project or scene, it's sublime unstructured feel will enhance without overwhelming. Please take a chill and click the link above!

volumes.title: Holiday Cheer Vol 1
volumes.desc: New composer Neil Cross brings a delightful spirit and joyful sounds to Holiday Cheer Vol 1, an excellent collection of original seasonal music. Bells, strings and synths weave happy melodies into picturesque tracks, brimming with holiday spirit! "Holiday Happiness"  features bells chiming a happy, pulsing dance as synth strings and percussion add just the right amount of kitsch to make this a classic holiday melody. "Effervescent" features a marching beat and bubbling bells as synths add breezy, flowing lines. "Kriss Kringle's" sparkling bells and snowy synths weave a frosty, wintertime melody with a heartfelt yet kooky hook. This delightful collection will warm your heart, cheer you up, and get you in a holiday mood. Just click the link above!

volumes.title: Dark Drones Vol 4
volumes.desc: This new collection of dark tracks, Dark Drones Vol 4, features orchestral elements weaving haunted soundtracks for the bloodthirsty. Clanging metal shards, growling cello and bassy synths weave a reverberating evil atmosphere on "Closed After Dark" as belled synths add a sparse melody the halting track moves like frightened steps into the unknown. A growing, claustrophobic melody weave a supreme sense of suspense on "Coming To" plucked violins add sharp accents to the urgent hush. "Wrong Message" weaves a tangled web of aggressive percussion accented by mysterious synths and action and adventure string lines. This bright and impactful collection will give your work a searing, dynamic edge, flush with fear and suspense. Please take a listen by clicking above!

volumes.title: Lounge Vol 3
volumes.desc: New composer Michael Kakhiani brings a laid-back and soulful sway to this new collection "Lounge Volume 3". This collection goes beyond "R&B;" and "Smooth Jazz" on the strength of the musicianship and the sparkling production, and, it's easy vibe and cool demeanor give this refreshing collection a great feel. "12 O Clock" features a groovin' funk guitar laying smooth lines as the band sways behind, "Slinky Groove" is an upbeat track with a timeless, soulful feel and melody that will put a smile on your face, Strings and keys give "Before Sunrise" a classic, sexy R&B; feel, as the rhythm section effortlessly grooves and moves. This beautiful collection will give your project a fun, groovy, sensual, laid-back feel. Brighten your day by clicking the link above.

volumes.title: Soundtrack Rock Vol 1
volumes.desc:
Composer Michael Kakhiani's second Freeplay effort: Soundtrack Rock Vol 1 opens this new volume collection with a great set of cinematic rock tracks-  
"Swing And Toss"  shows Michael's imaginative composing with it's unusual drum pattern and an infectious guitar melody, pulsing and happy, the off-kilter beat really hooks the ear. On "Stagger" a snappy guitar line builds into a propelling, upbeat rocker with a motivational Rhythm, "Ecstatic" is exactly that- pulsing acoustic guitars intro a warm and motivational groove that will get your blood pumping and your head nodding to the beat. This excellent collection features bright and glowing rock that will breathe positive life into your scenes, please clic

volumes.title: Modern Rock Vol 7
volumes.desc: Versatile composer Steve Booke is back, this time lending his many talents to this collection of modern rock tracks: "Modern Rock Vol 7". This set features big guitars, uplifting melodies and assured, no-frills rocking.  "Rocky Times" is a punchy track, with ringing guitars weaving a wistful, yet self-reliant melody as the rhythm section keeps a steady, straight-ahead beat. "High Sign" features a bit of a punky edge, as snarling guitars weave an edgy, yet happy melody- the bounding rhythm section keeps the beat squared, "Endless Possibilities" is an easy-swaying slice of Americana, with acoustic guitars adding a rich melodic rhythm, ringing electric guitar adds ringing solos across the mellow, yet expansive track. This vital and colorful collection will add depth and a warm, rocking vibe to your project or scene- please click above to sample these track

volumes.title: Holiday Classics Reloaded Vol 1
volumes.desc: Breakout composer Neil Cross flexes his musical muscles once again in his beautiful arrangement of classic Christmas songs on Holiday Classics Reloaded Vol 1. Just in time for the holiday season. These timeless masterpieces are arranged with a new and energetic twist. Neil brings us a Rock 'n Roll Christmas with powerful tracks like "Deck The Halls 1" and "Joy To The World 1" with driving electric guitars and hard-hitting drums. While tracks like "We Three Kings" and "Good King Wenceslas" ma

volumes.title: Holiday Cheer Vol 2
volumes.desc: Composer Neil Cross is back to provide more seasonal fun with Holiday Cheer Vol 2, this mix of old classics and some now originals will put you in a cheerful mood and provide war

volumes.title: Moving Images Volume 1
volumes.desc: Sensational composer Michael Kakhiani brings us an expertly arranged and masterfully executed collection of orchestral "tags" or "bumpers" in Moving Images Volume 1. These short, tension building pieces are the ultimate companion for your cinematic creations, great for segways or just before fade-outs. These brilliantly orchestrated tracks will simply blow you away. Some pieces have a mysterious and ghostly feel provided by a dissonant string section, while others give off a sense of elegance and class with a lone piano melody. The Moving Images collection will surely be your "go-to" album for any production. The quality of this volume is over-the-top, but don't take my word for it, click the link above to have a listen.

volumes.title: Piano And Strings Volume 1
volumes.desc: Long-time Freeplay composer Ben Kopec delivers another slam-dunk with Piano And Strings Volume 1, a definitive collection of emotional and somber piano and string oriented tracks. Pieces like "A Remote Place" instantly set a mood of painful loss and deep traumatic emotion, and "Green Eyed" where a grand piano presents us with a very peaceful yet moody introduction, as an acoustic guitar melody brings in subtle warmth and a feeling of thoughtful reflection. Each track compliments the next in such a way that you are guaranteed to have a difficult time choosing which track is the best for your dark and depressing scene, because honestly, they are all THAT good. Have a listen now by clicking the link at the top!

volumes.title: Holiday Cheer Vol 3
volumes.desc: Fresh composer Ruth Polcari brings us her brilliant interpretations of some timeless Christmas classics in Holiday Cheer Volume 3! This flute driven album is packed with perfect backing tracks for any calm and delicate winter or holiday scene. While most of the songs have the traditional instrumentation we expect from a Holiday album, some have a diverse and exotic array of instruments such as a shruti box, bells, and ambient synths, giving tracks like "Ding Dong Merrily On High" a unique flare, something not found on your average christmas track. The delightful flute melodies will soothe your soul as sparkling bells and shimmering chimes shatter and burst through the mixes like frosty icicles. Ruth Polcari's superior composing is sure to shine brightly in this classic Holiday arrangement. Check out Holiday Cheer Volume 3 now by clicking the link at the top!

volumes.title: Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 8
volumes.desc: New Composer Simon Power contributes some amazing and cohesive work for "Orchestral Soundscapes Vol 8"  well paced, efficient yet emotive, soundtrack compositions that range from epic orchestral to grooving, propulsive electronica.  "Music In The Middle Of The Night" is a brilliantly orchestrated with a magical and child-like feel, like silently tip-toeing down the stairs to sneak in some midnight snacks. "Remains Of The Day" is a dark and tense track, with dramatic strings growing and progressing slowly- accented by an epic horn section and heavy bass swells. "Head Trip" washes over you like a sea of warmth, as an electronic drumbeat provides a unique sound for this carefully progressing track. This electric and orchestral collection will add vibrant colors and emotion enhancing sounds to your project or scene, please click above and check it out!

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Volume 7
volumes.desc: Top-notch composer Michael Genato strikes again with another skillfully composed collection of songs in Tech Grooves Volume 8. A collection of high-energy, balls-to-wall, breakbeat and house electronica tracks. Notable tracks like "Up In The Air" present us with a serene landscape of  breakbeat wonder, fast drums, grooving synths, and powerful bass. Not to mention impressive tracks like "Aeon", a bass-fueled progressive house tune with pumping tribal drums and vocal samples. This collection of electronic goodness will flawlessly compliment any hi-tech or futuristic action/adventure scenes, but don't take my word for it, click the link up top to have a listen!

volumes.title: Holiday Beats Vol 1
volumes.desc: An all-star lineup of hot Freeplay composers bring us this mixed bag of holiday goodies with Holiday Beats Volume 1, just in time for Christmas. From bouncy and uplifting holiday tracks to calm and intimate tracks with passionately sung vocals, perfect for that midnight fire-side rendezvoux. You'll know Santa is right around the corner the instant these joyous holiday tunes hit your ears. Click the link of above to have a listen!

volumes.title: Percussion Vol 3
volumes.desc: This new and vibrant set from Joel Chassan and crew, Percussion Vol 3, features lively, exotic and fun rhythmic tracks perfect for adding thump and drive to your scenes. "Ahead Of Time" is a sexy, Latin hued song with quirky rhythms and spunky horn hits, together weaving an unusual track. "The Roman Blues" is a smoky, earthy track with a jazz piano and tight bass jamming with unruffled ease. "Cascade", a solo percussion track, opens with a grooving intesity. Latin percussion hits, whistles, and a rainstick are just a few of the exotic instruments used to construct this unique and interesting percussion track. This is an exciting collection featuring creative and unique songs. please click above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Clubtronic Vol 4
volumes.desc:
Beat-Master Barrett Yeretsian is back with a new bombastic collection on "Clubtronic Vol 4"- a gritty, streetwise set of hip-hop and dance tracks.
"The Next Generation" is a hard-hitting, hi-energy track with sumptuous bass lines kicking an ear-candy beat- bouncing, bawdy and boisterous. "Independent Being" mixes up delayed guitars and pizzicato strings to weave a sneaky, ghostly hip-hop track. "Illumination" is a raw and unabashed club banger, with an infectious beat, booming bass and spacey synths weaving a classic dancefloor smash. This crushing collection will bring a streetwise sheen to your project, Please click above and prepare to groove.

volumes.title: Eclectic Dance Vol 4
volumes.desc: Brooklyn Beatsmiths Grady Walker and Ann Marie Sargolini team up for this kaleidoscopic collection of electronic tracks on "Eclectic Dance Vol 4" swerving from disco to house to electro, this duo is fluent is dancefloor and has a masters in grooving. In fact "Groove To This" is a prime example: a pulsing house beat, wicked synth lines, a smattering of guitar loops and wham! you got a thumping track that will get your body popping. "Always Shining" features a super bouncy and uplifting beat with a delightful harp melody and warm organ-like synths. Delayed vocal clips and a punchy drum beat make this track a stand-out. "Groovytown's" funk blast features live drums and a funkified Wurlitzer organ, jamming away on a super groovy beat, weaving an action-packed and driving feel. This dynamic and punchy collection will impress with it's edgy feel and rhythmic grooves. Please click above and check it out!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Drama Vol 13
volumes.desc:
Composer extraordinaire Ben Kopec, brings his talent and style to bear on the insightful "Soundtrack Drama Vol 13" weaving intense and emotive tracks with all the punch and verve necessary for todays broadcast standards.  On "Break In The Clouds" ambient synths swell with a deep presence, providing a rich yet creepy backdrop for the punchy drum beat. With aggressive drums setting the stage for "Headliner", the tight bassline and reversed synth weave into the rhythm, creating an upbeat and driving melody. "Its A Toss Up" features warped synth effects, creating a futuristic vibe. A touch of piano, giving the piece a unique sound, and big bass swells- giving this tune a large presence. This excellent and emotional collection will add depth and feel to your project. Please click the link above.

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Vol 5
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Ionics brings wicked production skills, smart, punchy rhythms and a great ear for a bass line to this dynamic new collection of electronic tracks: "Eclectic Beats Vol 5".  The sinister "Graceful Destroyer" moves like a slow and smothering river, the track creeps up with careful intensity as the ambient synths build along with the heavy bass groove and evil delayed guitar riffs. "Twisting The World" is a mind-bending journey through time and space, centered around a deep and infectious groove, that is accented by spooky guitar melodies and sequenced synth effects. A fresh and crispy drum beat opens "Breaking Dawn", ambient synths, epic trumpets, and big distorted guitars chime in with pure intesity creating a diverse blend of sounds and weaving a triumphant piece. This cinematic and colorful collection will add great dynamics and a modern atmosphere to your project, please click above to check it out!

volumes.title: Soundtrack Moods Vol 4
volumes.desc: New Freeplay Composer Michael McLaughlin brings excellent production skills and a professional ear for both structure and melody- not only are the pieces recorded well, they are played very well and are lovingly placed within the stereo field, thus this collection moves the listener with every subtlety available to the composer. The aptly named "Puppy " soothes an exact itch- synth vocals and a piano introduce us to this cute flute oriented piece, with it's peaceful and uplifting sounds weaving a motivational feel. On "During The Darkness",  a calm, ambient string section lays down a bed of sound for a dark and dissonant piano melody. Spooky synths add a tense accent to the brooding piece. "Imagine" is a somber and moody piece with no shortage of dramatic intensity. With building tension, the string section, acoustic guitar and piano create a rich and interesting texture of dark tones in this moody instrumental. Soundtrack Moods Vol 4 is a delightful set that will enliven and texturize your scene or project. Please give it a listen!

volumes.title: Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 11
volumes.desc: New Freeplay composer Mike Newport brings style, winning ways and a natural talent to this new collection of cinematic, emotional soundtracks "Dramatic Soundscapes Vol 11". "Downrush" opens with a spacey synth senction progressing slowly to a punchy electronic beat, the song slowly morphs into an infectious and dark cinematic breakbeat with lots of spooky effects. "Brokenhearted" is a slowly building orchestral piece, featuring ringing bells and somber strings weaving with tension and drama into a slow and epic melody, the bells blasting through the track. The peaceful and moody track "A Brave Wish" features a lush string section providing a dense backdrop for the triumphant horn melody. Weaving an overall sense of accomplishment, joy, and wonder. This excellent collection will add depth and vivid color to your scene or project, please click above to take a listen!

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Volume 8
volumes.desc: Mike Genato and crew are back with another set of smashing, hip and fun electronica- the same team that brought you "Techstep" Vols 1 and 2 have upgraded and updated for this dynamic set: "Wickedness" is a face melting tribal track with a propulsive edge, "Chinook" hefty breakbeat is accented by misty, ambient synths. This is a dynamic and impactful collection that will add a spicy punch to your scene!

volumes.title: Funk Grooves Volume 3
volumes.desc: With fresh Freeplay composer Zilo Groove, the name really says it all. Bringing us a solid volume that is utterly dripping with pure funk, Funk Grooves Volume 3. His over-the-top compositions are infected with a deep groove that you definitely won't be able to shake. Tracks like Just Luck have a downbeat afro-funk groove with unusual vocals and a cool organ setting that relaxed and sexy vibe. Check out Funk Grooves Vol 3 now by clicking the link above!

volumes.title: Tech Grooves Volume 9
volumes.desc: Prolific composer Mike Genato is back for Tech Grooves Vol 9, packed with some of his most impressive tracks to date. The depth and and attention to detail in these tracks is truly astonishing, and the possible uses for these tracks are endless. Words can almost not describe the intensity and character of these sonically brilliant tracks. Check out tracks like Wild Blue Yonder; with explosive force this track bursts through your speakers with spaced-out synths, a fat bass groove, and hi-energy breakbeat electronica drums. Click the link above to have a listen!

volumes.title: Music For Pictures Volume 10
volumes.desc: Talented composer Chris Truitt bangs out an epic volume of tracks perfect for motion picture soundtracks in Music For Pictures Volume 10. A wide range of sounds and moods can be found here, from full orchestral tracks with intense moods to tracks like Pitch Black Street, which feature an eerie bass line and an epic horn section, this simple yet creepy electronic beat has an underlying intensity and a hidden darkness. Click the link above to enter a world of cinematically masterful sound!

volumes.title: Promos Volume 9
volumes.desc: Among Freeplays finest composers, the masterful Ben Kopec brings us another fine collection of compositions perfect for promos or any production requiring subtle and effective backing music. Tracks like the The Upshot have etheral and ambient synths saturating the stereo field with heavenly warmth, and epic tracks like Superior, with Sonar-like synth effects creating an eerie vibe as the grooving bassline enters the scene. Click the link above to experience all that is Promos Volume 9.

volumes.title: Dance & Pop Volume 9
volumes.desc: Ernie Lake creates, glossy, seductive tracks with seeming ease, his minimal and refined touch coaxes the the rhythm and the melody to move in a subtly entrancing manner, embracing the listener with gentle, refreshing hooks. Always modern yet wholeheartedly classic, the jams just keep coming.

volumes.title: Electric Love Volume 2
volumes.desc: Dj Mar and Dean deliver their most ambitious record in Electric Love Volume 2, this collection sees the team firing on all cylinders, serving up danceable and dynamic electronic tracks topped off with excellent male and female vocals- " Down In The Bunker" is a slamming track featuring wicked electric cowboy rhythms, booming bass and chanted yeah, yeah, yeahs together to weave a motivational and hip urban track, "Love (DJMars mix)" is a hyper dance pop track featuring hefty beats, buzzing bass and an aggressive but upbeat feel, zooming synths add sparse melodic accents as female vocals add rhythmic textures. This dynamic collection will add danceable beats, in your face vocals and upbeat melodies to your scene, project or Friday night- Please click above to check it out!

volumes.title: Hot Guitar Rock Vol 8
volumes.desc: New composer Jason M. Moore brings wicked guitars and smart composing to bear on Hot Guitar Rock Vol 8,  The moody yet resolute "Dynamite" has a bit of an late 80's underground feel, with its fat, popping bass-line, roomy drums and acoustic and electric guitars using a quiet/loud format. "Euphoria" has a similar feel, acoustic/electric guitar weaving a moody line as the bass follows the melody, the drums keep an easy pace- the moody verse gives way to an upbeat chorus and back again. "Mind The Gap" is a rough and tumble track- frayed guitars and big, walking bass-lines. Slide guitar weaves a psychedelic line on "The Standpoint" as the bass and drums work at a dirge pace. "Unconventional" is a serious rocker with an action groove, punchy drums and big, resounding bass-lines. The groovy chorus will take you right to 1997, loud, prod and slightly deranged. This great collection will add moody rock textures to you images- Please click above to get a piece.

volumes.title: Cosmic Tronic Volume 2
volumes.desc: New composer Ben Fisseler brings wit and serious chops to Cosmic Tronic Volume 2- a delightful and diverse collection of out of the ordinary electronic music. "Dinero" features glitched sounds and banging percussion to create a chaotic soundscape that builds with intensity, The pop drum line of "The Pursuit" gives motivational push as funky synths weave soulful melodies, with a sunny and upbeat feel. "Willing To Oppose" is a fuzzed out electronic dirge, with a dark and purposeful drive. "Nocturnal" is an eerie atmospheric track, featuring rising pads, digital sounds and warm heartbeat rhythms. This expressive, imaginative and unique collection will as a distinct shine and modern sense to your visuals, please click above to take a listen.

volumes.title: Battle Themes Volume 6
volumes.desc: Battle Themes Volume Six brings you tense, energetic, and urgent tracks mixing orchestral settings with large percussion ensambles and synth accents to weave some dramatic and dynamic results: "Rare Bird" Features melodic flutes and percolating layers of hand drums seething with a wild and animalistic edge, The wicked "Waylayed Enforcements" features expressive and terrifying horn lines over jumbled and panicked rhythms. The percussion and bleating horn hits on "Here To The End" provide dynamic rhythmic accents- Picture an angry elephant destroying a tank. This impactful collection will add powerful sounds to your imagery, click the link to check it out.

volumes.title: Action And Adventure Vol 8
volumes.desc: The newest addition to the action line: Action And Adventure Vol 8 brings you cd quality sound and movie quality music, a dynamic collection of hard hitting, dramatic and cinematic tracks for hi-lighting any action or adventure scenes. "More Than It Seems" is a short but but to the point track with thundering rhythms and dark, burning bass. Tense strings and choral voices bring a ringing end to the tag. "The Decider" features freaky synth sounds and massive beats, on this huge and aggressive track, clanging percussion and waves of choral voices combine to weave a dynamic and pummeling track, full of bravado. On "Venom To The Veins" spacey breaks give way to pummeling rhythms, playing a game of chase or hide and seek- crouching in the shadows only to spring to life and run to the next sheltered place. This set will bring intrigue and controlled mayhem to your setting or scene, please check it out!

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 12
volumes.desc: Freeplay composer Peter Hawkes (of Acoustic Guitar Vol 4 fame) has returned triumphantly with Acoustic Guitar Vol 12, an expertly crafted collection of acoustic masterpieces.  The guitar is, of course, the centerpiece throughout, as crisply finger-picked melodies unfold.  Tasteful accompaniment from violin, flute and trumpet makes this eclectic collection all the more interesting and creative.  If you're looking for some beautifully played acoustic music with a truly original presentation, then look no further than Acoustic Guitar Vol 12.

volumes.title: Acoustic Guitar Vol 11
volumes.desc: New composer Michael Kakhiani brings a subtle pop twist and a warm embracing style to Acoustic Guitar Volume 1. This charismatic collection features warm acoustic guitars, accented at points by strings, piano and drums. The composed melodies flow with wise restraint, seasoned and easy- "Down And Out" envelops the listener, as the gentle acoustic guitar harmonizes with the powerful grand piano, weaving a thoughtful piece. "Compatibility" is a very calm and collected piece with delicate strings, light congos, and a warming acoustic guitar melody producing an effortless track that is deceptively simple sounding. The full band on "Chipper" fleshes out the guitar with an infectious joy- the strings come in and lift the piece in a scenic and inspiring way. This sparkling collection will add composed yet colorful melodies to your images. Please click above to check it out!

volumes.title: Chamber Music Vol 1
volumes.desc: Composer Peter Hawkes, who also brought us the delightful Acoustic Guitar Volume 4, brings Freeplay a new look in Chamber Music Vol 1, this great collection features acoustic guitar paired with a violin ensemble, playing Peter's imaginative and picturesque melodies. "Cambloux" gently shifts with kaleidoscopic melodies swirling and swelling as the guitar and violins dance a complex and reflective dance. The relaxed playing on "Disturbance" suggests a conversation between the instruments, slowly weaving a melancholy tune. "Aunties Berceuse" is a fantastic reel that slowly swings out and steps like a gentle breeze, flavored with fresh earth and the damp chill of early spring. This eloquent and introspective volume will add character, depth and earthy elegance to your scene, please click the link and take a listen!

volumes.title: Eclectic Beats Vol 7
volumes.desc:
Fresh new composer Mike Cyr, brings talent, imagination and some dope beats to Eclectic Beats Volume 7, waxing and milking like a professional, dude rocks the decks.
"Black Light" is an atmospheric electronic track with a cool, lightly swinging beat and some bubbly synth work together building an eerie track with a tense feel. Lurching rhythms and zooming, flashing synths give a spaced-out feel to "Twine" a dark bit of electronica with a brooding energy. The effervescent neon synths on "Stringer" weave a complex and thoughtful melody, chiming, buzzing and creating a hazy summery feel. With it's interesting sounds this fun and futuristic collection will add dynamic and colorful electronics to your scene or situation- as ever, please click the link to check it out!

tracks.title: Chopin Piano Concerto 1 (2nd movement)
tracks.desc: Eloquent piano lines weave a calm but intense romantic vibe, swaying with heartfelt warmth and passion.

tracks.title: Chopin Piano Concerto 1 (3rd movement)

tracks.title: Delibes Sylvia Pizzicato

tracks.title: Delibes Waltz from Coppelia

tracks.title: Delibes Flower Duet (from Lakme)

tracks.title: Delibes Coppelia Prelude and Mazurka
tracks.desc: A Mazurka is a Polish celebratory dance- the prelude features rising, warming strings that turn commanding as the orchestra joins in with leaps and bounds. With a whirling, wintery feel the piece climaxes with resounding aplomb.

tracks.title: Chopin Nocturne Opus 9 No 1
tracks.desc: This introspective Nocturne moodily unfolds with calm, purposeful melody and ornimentations, delightfully ruminative.

tracks.title: Chopin Nocturne Opus 9 No 2
tracks.desc: This thoughtful piece calmly dances with a slightly melancholy feel, but, it's earthy rhythm adds hints of warmth and the promise of brighter days.

tracks.title: Chopin Nocturne Opus 15 No 2
tracks.desc: Wandering piano lines resolving with emotion and grace bring this gentle lullaby charm and warmth beyond words.

tracks.title: Chopin Nocturne Opus 27 No 2
tracks.desc: This moving, emotional piece sparkles with a singular happiness and a warm sense of trust. Wise and unhurried.

tracks.title: Chopin Grand Waltz Brilliant Opus 18
tracks.desc: A captivating waltz with a confident air, the rolling melodic explorations resolving and dancing around the theme with coy pleasure.

tracks.title: Chopin Grand Waltz Opus 42

tracks.title: Chopin Mazurka Opus 7 No 1
tracks.desc: A hesitant waltz, perhaps timid at the prospect of love, but longing for it none the less.

tracks.title: Chopin Mazurka Opus 24 No 2
tracks.desc: A warm and melodic dance with charming trills and ornamentation, refined and relaxed.

tracks.title: Chopin Mazurka Opus 30 No 3
tracks.desc: Commanding notes and chords accent this introspective waltz, with a dynamic and expressive use of volume and resonance.

tracks.title: Chopin Mazurka Opus 33 No 2
tracks.desc: This jolly and undulating waltz brings smiles and effervescence with it's twirling, warm melodies.

tracks.title: Chopin Waltz Opus 64 No 2
tracks.desc: A melancholy waltz infused with wisdom and regret, resolving with just enough strength to carry on.

tracks.title: Chopin Waltz Opus 69 No 1 (Adieu)
tracks.desc: A sad and regretful waltz, it's moody lines falling like rain on a grey sunday.

tracks.title: Chopin Waltz Opus 69 No 2
tracks.desc: A tumbling, descending melody speaks of sadness and life lessons learned, with a somber air.

tracks.title: Chopin Waltz Opus 70 No 1
tracks.desc: A laughing, dancing waltz with melodic lines full of love and longing. Poignant and charmed.

tracks.title: Chopin Ballade No 1 Opus 23
tracks.desc: A moody and reflective piece, reaching vigorous crescendos with emotive chords and filigree.

tracks.title: Chopin Berceuse Opus 57
tracks.desc: Moody, remorseful lines open this emotional track, it's poignant ornamentation full of apology and promises.

tracks.title: Chopin Black Keys Study Opus 10

tracks.title: Chopin Butterfly Study Opus 25 No 9

tracks.title: Chopin Etude Tristesse Opus 10 No 3

tracks.title: Chopin Etude Winter Wind Opus 25 No 11

tracks.title: Chopin Fantasie Impromptu Opus 66

tracks.title: Chopin Grande Polonaise Brillante Opus 22

tracks.title: Chopin Polonaise Opus 40 No 1

tracks.title: Chopin Polonaise Opus 53

tracks.title: Chopin Piano Concerto 2 (2nd movement)

tracks.title: Chopin Piano Concerto 2 (3rd movement)
tracks.desc: This vibrant Allegro vivace movement is led by a sparkling, inventive piano with strings and winds providing dynamic atmospheres, in the finale the strings add rhythmic accents by playing col legno, striking the strings with the wood of their bows.

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 1 (1st movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 1 (2nd movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 1 (3rd movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 1 (4th movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 2 (1st movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 2 (2nd movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 2 (3rd movement)
tracks.desc: Triumphant horns and driving piccolo violin lead this attention-grabbing track, it's regal, energizing melody beaming like the sun.

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 3 (1st and 2nd movements)
tracks.desc: Dynamic rhythms and bold melodic strokes give the 3rd concerto an Italian air, the charming theme ornamented with elegant performance.

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 3 (3rd movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 4 (1st movement)

tracks.title: Bach Brandenburg Concerto 4 (2nd movement)
