tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Concerto in G for Two Mandolins Second Movement
tracks.desc: Timid mandolins, accented by pizzicato strings slowly rework and embellish the main theme, bringing a bit of mystery and complexity to the 2nd movement.

tracks.desc: The orchestra opens with a strident pace, the mandolins step in with complex and sparkling ornamentation. The orchestra answers with magnanimous responses closing the piece with charm and dexterity.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 617 One
tracks.desc: A sweet and subtle prayer backed by a sparse and reverent orchestra.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 617 Two
tracks.desc: A lively orchestra backs a soaring female vocal, resplendent in exalt and spiritual love.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 617 Three
tracks.desc: A consummate and reverent piece, with a complex melody and lofty female vocal.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 617 Four
tracks.desc: Worshipful strings weave a emotional melody, brimming with spiritual patience and grace, the sweet, arching vocal full of warmth and love.

tracks.title: MC Strauss Jr A Thousand And One Nights Waltz Opus 346 A

tracks.title: MC Strauss Jr A Thousand And One Nights Waltz Opus 346 B
tracks.desc: This exuberant reprise moves with pride and manly grace, it's reverberant melody ringing with pomp and grandiloquence.

tracks.title: MC Strauss Jr Tales From The Vienna Woods Opus 325 B
tracks.desc: This delightful reprise brings the memorable melody fully to the front, with the orchestra ringing and swinging with robust exuberance.

tracks.title: Behind The Picket Fences

tracks.title: Cardiff Docks
tracks.desc: Warm acoustic guitar weave a gentile rhythm of plucked chords, a flute weaves relaxing, peaceful melodies, evoking a scenic landscape. Warm synths add delicate gossamer veils of atmosphere.

tracks.title: Garden Lullaby
tracks.desc: If you could hear the smells of wildflowers wafting off a summers breeze, this would be it: charming flute line weaves a gentle melody, accented by french horn as synths and bass provide a lilting atmospheric backdrop.

tracks.title: Dark Sea Dive
tracks.desc: Slow and atmospheric melodies played by warm synth pads, gives you a flowing motion of timelessness and fantasy.

tracks.title: Discotheque Wallflower
tracks.desc: Electronic drums, smooth bass, and cordial synth sounds presenting a piece that conveys a smooth forward motion.

tracks.title: Eleventh Hour Victory
tracks.desc: A dramatic drum line and proud violins march with an aggressive fury, preparing you for a victorious climax.

tracks.title: Exploring The Outliers
tracks.desc: A prominent drum line and strong string section build a firm base for the theatrical melody, delivering a dynamic feeling of drama and propulsion.

tracks.title: Fly Away Home
tracks.desc: Pronounced drums and thumping bass lay a grooving foundation for the organic sounding  synths and eager piano to weave a moving melody into a dramatic and uplifting tune.

tracks.title: Opportunity Knocks

tracks.title: Planned Community

tracks.title: Pinstriped Hero

tracks.title: Who Will Take Us

tracks.title: Winter At The Shore
tracks.desc: Warm synth pads add a dramatic atmosphere to a lonesome, fluttering piano line, sad twinkling like sun off the waves on a cold, grey, blustery day.

tracks.title: Fare Thee Well
tracks.desc: A nocturnal sounding organ with dramatic chord changes in a constant slow moving rhythm keeps you in suspense.

tracks.title: Down The Aisle
tracks.desc: Cinematic and dancing melodies of the bright organ gives you the sense of a sudden dawn in a dark and medieval time.

tracks.title: Kyrie Eleison

tracks.title: O Gloria

tracks.title: Penitence Canon

tracks.title: MC Brahms Sonata in F Minor Opus 5 Third Movement

tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Sonata in F Minor Opus 5 Fourth Movement

tracks.title: MC Brahms Sonata in F Minor Opus 5 Fifth Movement
tracks.desc: This dance-like closing movement really brings out the virtuosity of both Brahms and the soloist.  Once again combining energy with emotion, the contrast between sections is more dramatic in this movement than any of the others, really rounding out the en

tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Sonata in D Minor Opus 108 Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: This allegro final movement still features interchangeable solo parts in a 4/4 structure that varies in dynamic level and tempo throughout, with the fluid violin and choppy piano.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 1
tracks.desc: A moving section invoking feelings of poignancy and mourning amidst soaring vocal solos, intense choral sections, and orchestrations that fit perfectly with the vocals.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 2
tracks.desc: A highly powerful, fortissimo movement with sections of quiet, serene solos, but its characteristic features are the suspenseful, allegro sections where the orchestra, choir, and soloists are all performing simultaneously.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 3
tracks.desc: This setting of Offertorio features various soli throughout from all vocal parts, over a peaceful orchestra that uses woodwinds more heavily in this movement than in other movements.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 4
tracks.desc: The Sanctus movement of the Verdi requiem features contrapuntal vocal lines over lush, arpeggiated string and woodwind sections.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 5
tracks.desc: This tranquil setting of Agnus Dei features a choral and orchestral unison section reminiscent of the Gregorian chant of the Medieval era.  This movement remains fairly stable throughout in its adagio tempo and mezzo-piano to mezzo-forte dynamics.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 6
tracks.desc: Lux aeterna is another solo-driven movement of Verdi's Requiem that is mostly at a mezzo-piano dynamic level and features interwoven solos from soprano, alto, tenor, and baritone/bass.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Verdi Requiem 7
tracks.desc: Libera me begins with a soprano solo that ushers in a recapitulation of the "Dies irae" theme - arguably one of the most recognizable themes from any mass ever written.  The movement continues with a soaring soprano solo, and revisits various themes of pr
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Funeral March
tracks.desc: Appropriately reverent and mournful, long streams of organ chords open the mortal landscape for public memorial and private recompense.

tracks.title: MC Haydn Concerto for Trumpet and Orchestra in E Flat First Movement
tracks.desc: A full orchestra lays an allegro backdrop for an ornamented, scalar trumpet solo that hearkens back to baroque Purcell-like stylings.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Concerto for Trumpet and Orchestra in E Flat Second Movement
tracks.desc: This more andante movement in 3/4 time features a beautiful flute solo in the beginning that eventually blends into the entirety of the orchestra and leads once again to a more serene, pastoral trumpet solo.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Concerto for Trumpet and Orchestra in E Flat Third Movement
tracks.desc: A vivacious ending movement to this concerto brings the rest of the piece together in a thrilling climax, featuring a bombastic orchestral section and an virtuosic trumpet solo interchanging seamlessly.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn German Dances HOB IX Part A
tracks.desc: This waltz-like set of eight dances features strings, harpsichord, and winds, and sets the tone very well for a courtly dance or masquerade ball.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn German Dances HOB IX Part B
tracks.desc: Part B is an abbreviated version of Part A, featuring only three dances from Part A.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 1
tracks.desc: This light and lilting setting of the Kyrie moves from beautiful harmonies between all four vocal parts into a lovely fugal counterpoint over powerful strings.  This interchange continues throughout the entirety of the movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 2
tracks.desc: The organ and string section create a very regal feel to this setting of the Gloria. The arpeggiated strings during the forte sections create a very energetic feel to the movement. Vocal solos in a slower, more mournful setting are also featured.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 3
tracks.desc: This setting of the Credo has stark contrasts between bright and majestic choral features and slow, mournful solos.  The solos become more closely integrated with the entirety of the choir, almost like a vocal concerto.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 4
tracks.desc: This brief setting of Sanctus is very powerful, and brings an immediate feel of intensity when the solos finally climax into a fortissimo choral section.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 5
tracks.desc: This setting of Benedictus continues in similar manner to the four previous movements, including bright, powerful strings and choral sections in stark contrast with solo sections.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 6
tracks.desc: The Agnus Dei begins in a mysterious, powerfully sacred tone, then rests. Then the choir heralds steadfast, unwavering praise for a truly rousing finish.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Come Spring
tracks.desc: A tempered and reassuring piano theme slowly emerges from a murky, tentative bed of strings, like a dandelion after the last frigid rainfall of a long winter.

tracks.title: Covert One
tracks.desc: Pulsing clicks, hisses and drips build suspense as a distant piano murmurs a clue. Ensuing brass and string trills really get the heart pumping.

tracks.title: Cruel Removal
tracks.desc: A hollow sense of disconnection prevails over this track, with a shallow grave of synth at one end and soulful, airy piano at the other. Trippy sparks of beats enter halfway, banded with haunting synth pads.

tracks.title: Cul De Sac Tale
tracks.desc: A beautiful, knowing, and heady piano theme, backed with chipper beats which glimmer like sun light after a torrential rainstorm.

tracks.title: Exiled
tracks.desc: A timid, minimalist piano and synth piece. Gloom pervades at first, then clipped beats shift in and the overall tone turns a lighter shade of blue.

tracks.title: Facing Twilight
tracks.desc: A gentle, sweeping flute and string theme, with ornate harp. Uncondtionally peaceful but with a hint of sadness, like the last sunset of a holiday at the shore.

tracks.title: Facing Twilight (Reprise)
tracks.desc: A dreamier version of its predecessor, heavier on strings, more ethereal, and somewhat darker.

tracks.title: Tempting Fate
tracks.desc: Cool-headed and cunning, this perfectly measured and mysterious piece has many secrets in the background, from muted trumpet to vibraphone.

tracks.title: Through Thick And Thin
tracks.desc: A weathered and sentimental piano ballad, moving in its world-weariness and inspiring in the glints of hope it emits.

tracks.title: Unwanted Spawn
tracks.desc: Subtle, stony ambience of synth and piano, bearing uncertainty and suspicion.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Spring First Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: The highly recognizable first movement of Spring features brilliant strings, which indicate new life and vibrancy of spring.  The strings are highly ornamented in Baroque fashion.  A courtly ball would be the perfect setting for this movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Spring Second Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: A flawless violin solo is the centerpiece of this slower, sadder movement.  The background strings are played in a lilting fashion, giving the movement a bit of a bounce.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Spring Third Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: Violins in high register are featured in this movement, as well as a brilliant violin solo.  This movement has feelings of both jubilation and animosity.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Summer First Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: Summer rushes in on a virtuosic violin solo, backed by intense strings and a plucky harpsichord line, with various breaks that feature a much slower, more fluid solo line.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Summer Second Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: A summer storm seems to be approaching in the second movement of Summer, which features an ominous violin solo and random outbursts of energy from the orchestra, possibly signifying lightning or thunder.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Summer Third Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: This brilliant third movement finds Summer in the onslaught of a violent storm.  The strings are full of rushing downward scales, indicating falling rain and crashing thunder.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Autumn First Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: Autumn starts off with a colorful bang, full of glorious strings and harpsichord lines.  Toward the end, the mood changes to a more somber one, perhaps indicating the oncoming death of some of summer's foliage.  The intial joyous mood is reintroduced at t
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Autumn Second Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: Slow contemplation is the theme of this movement.  Now that the listener is in the throes of autumn, the death of the leaves begins, indicated by long, slow string lines and measured harpsichord lines.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Autumn Third Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: A harvest festival seems to be underway in this cheery final movement of Autumn.  Dancelike structure predominates the piece, demonstrated through the staccato, playful strings.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi The Four Seasons - Winter First Movement (Feat Vlcek)
tracks.desc: A stormy winter seems to be ahead in this first movement of Winter.  Slower passages give way to intense, agitated sections, possibly indicating the blustery windstorms of early winter.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Symphony 4 First Movement
tracks.desc: This thunderous first movement features intense strings who often resort to loud plucking, and features solos from flute, oboe, and trumpet.  Whimsical, sweet areas are combined with powerful angry sections in this exciting opening.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Symphony 4 Second Movement
tracks.desc: Pizzicato string plucking is even more prominent in this relaxing second movement.  The mood changes toward the end with a suspenseful, raucous string section, but quickly changes back to the initial tranquility.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Symphony 4 Third Movement
tracks.desc: The bright third movement has the energy of the first movement, but has a more joyous feel than the darker first movement.  Vibrant strings are accented by triangles and floating woodwind lines.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Brahms Symphony 4 Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: The fourth movement is a return to the agitated intensity of the first movement.  Loud brass sections accent brilliant string lines in an exciting ending.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Violin and Orchestra Opus 35 First Movement
tracks.desc: This courtly first movement features thrilling violin soli and regal orchestral sections.  It has the feel of an important societal or political event or an exciting, fast-paced scene.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Violin and Orchestra Opus 35 Second Movement
tracks.desc: This movement starts out slow, but gradually increases in speed to end at a breakneck pace.  The violin solo goes from sweet and melodic to rapid and scalar, making the moods of this movement quite versatile.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Violin and Orchestra Opus 35 Third Movement
tracks.desc: The most exciting of the three movements, the final movement ends in a bombastic finale full of rushing strings and rambunctious violin soli.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 One
tracks.desc: Contrapuntal strings begin this movement, which are then joined by a harpsichord and graceful alto solo.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Two
tracks.desc: An ornamented alto solo, strings, and organ make up this intense second movement.  Forceful, loud instrumentation is featured.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Three
tracks.desc: This quiet and brooding movement once again features strings and an alto soloist, singing at a slower, more contemplative tempo.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Four
tracks.desc: Woodwinds are more prominent in this movement than the others, with the previous staples of strings and an alto soloist still being used.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Five
tracks.desc: The pace slows for the somber fifth movement, which brings the harpsichord into prominence.

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Six
tracks.desc: The work ends in a slow, solemn manner, with the alto soloist singing at a quiet volume over sparse orchestration.
